{"type":"text","timestamp":1782998142479,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22f86314001q4Zlf1Riv8PZ5S","messageID":"msg_f22f7fae1001V2dIdygcPLKQIB","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"text","text":"SKILL ROUTING: User directed → `deep-review`. I’ll load the named workflow contract first, bind the provided lineage artifact directory directly, then restrict writes to the requested lineage path.","time":{"start":1782998131476,"end":1782998142472},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f475826e9339bdd016a46647366b0819887b689b409fa8e51","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998142544,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_X4405s2aYgMhYrzFFmQ6UOIj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"deep-review"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"deep-review\">\n# Skill: deep-review\n\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n- Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n- Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n- Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n- Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n- Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n- Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n- Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n- Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n- Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n\n### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n\nThis skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n- Invoke cli-opencode / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n- Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n- Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n- Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n- Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n\n**COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n\n**ALWAYS:**\n- Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n- Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n- Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n- Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n- Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n\n### Trigger Phrases\n\n- \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n- \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n- \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n- \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n- \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n- \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n- \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n\n### Keyword Triggers\n\n`deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n}\n\nNOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n}\n\n# RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nPHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n}\n\nNON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n    \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n    \"Confirm the review phase\",\n    \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n]\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n    phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n    if phase:\n        return phase\n    text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if \"recovery\" in text:\n        return \"stuck\"\n    if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n        return \"synthesis\"\n    if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n        return \"iteration\"\n    return \"init\"\n\ndef route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n    scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    phase_resources = PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP.get(routing_key, [])\n    if routing_key == \"unknown\" or not phase_resources:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"notice\": f\"No review resources found for routing key '{routing_key}'\",\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    for intent in intents:\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    for relative_path in phase_resources:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    return {\n        \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n        \"intents\": intents,\n        \"resources\": loaded,\n        \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n    }\n```\n\n### Phase Detection\n\nDetect the current review phase from dispatch context to load appropriate resources:\n\n| Phase | Signal | Resources to Load |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| Init | No JSONL exists in `review/` | Loop protocol, state format, state outputs, review contract |\n| Iteration | Dispatch context includes dimension + iteration number | Loop protocol, convergence, convergence signals, review contract |\n| Stuck | Dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY\" | Convergence, convergence signals, loop protocol, reducer registry |\n| Synthesis | Convergence triggered STOP | Review contract, state format, state outputs, reducer registry |\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Resource Map Coverage Gate\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep review treats it as a first-class audit input instead of optional prompt wiring.\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-review-config.json`.\n- Add a resource-map snapshot to `Known Context` so later iterations inherit the packet inventory baseline.\n- Promote `Resource Map Coverage` to a first-class audit angle alongside correctness, regression risk, test coverage, cross-runtime parity, observability, and docs-vs-code drift.\n- Reserve at least one loop iteration to cross-check `target_files` from `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md` against `resource-map.md`.\n- Treat that pass as mandatory coverage work, not an optional traceability extra.\n- Classify results into three buckets: entries touched, entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n- Findings emitted from that audit use the `resource-map-coverage` category.\n- Synthesis inserts `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` into `review-report.md` when the map was present at init.\n- Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from review delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n- Log `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` in `Known Context`.\n- Skip the coverage-gate pass and omit the report section without failing the loop.\n\n### Architecture\n\n`/deep:review` owns the loop. The YAML workflow initializes state, dispatches one LEAF review iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `review-report.md`, and saves continuity. The LEAF agent reads state, reviews one dimension, writes `iteration-NNN.md`, updates strategy, and appends JSONL.\n\n### State Packet Location\n\nThe review state packet always lives under the target spec's local `review/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/review/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/review/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `review/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\nExample (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n\nExample (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n\nCore artifacts: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `.deep-review-pause`, `resource-map.md`, `review-report.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n\n### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Data Flow\n\nInit creates config, strategy, and JSONL state. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches one dimension, records findings, and reduces state. Synthesis compiles the final report and saves continuity.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\nThe four primary review dimensions (configured in `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`):\n\n| Dimension | Focus | Key Questions |\n|-----------|-------|---------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, behavior, error handling | Does the code do what it claims? Are edge cases handled? |\n| **Security** | Vulnerabilities, exposure, trust boundaries | Are inputs validated? Are credentials exposed? |\n| **Spec-Alignment / Traceability** | Spec vs. implementation fidelity | Does code match spec.md? Are all planned items present? |\n| **Completeness / Maintainability** | Coverage, dead code, documentation | Are TODOs resolved? Is the code self-documenting? |\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\nReview mode is lineage-aware. Supported lifecycle modes are `new`, `resume`, and `restart`. Required lineage fields include `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, and `releaseReadinessState`. The reducer consumes the latest JSONL delta, the new iteration file, and prior reduced state, then emits finding registry, dashboard metrics, and strategy updates.\n\n### Severity Classification\n\n| Severity | Criteria | Blocking |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **P0** | Correctness failure, security vulnerability, spec contradiction | Yes, blocks PASS verdict |\n| **P1** | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation | Conditional, triggers CONDITIONAL verdict |\n| **P2** | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps | No, PASS with advisories |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **PASS** | No P0/P1 findings, P2 findings recorded as advisories (`hasAdvisories: true`) |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | P1 findings present, remediation plan included in report |\n| **FAIL** | Any P0 finding confirmed after adversarial self-check |\n\n### Verdict Lock and Advisory Risk Score\n\nAlways emit exactly one parseable verdict. A confirmed active P0 locks the verdict to `FAIL`; do not soften it to `CONDITIONAL`, `partial`, or any other phrasing. Truncated or partial iteration output is not a valid substitute for the final verdict line. Review narratives and JSONL details may include an optional advisory `riskScore` for relative risk calibration, but it never changes the `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` mapping.\n\n### Acceptance-Coverage Signal\n\nWhen the review target is a spec folder, deep review reflects the `AC_COVERAGE` validation signal in synthesis for Level 2+ folders only after both lifecycle conditions are true: `checklist.md` exists and `implementation-summary.md` is in-progress or later. Level 1 folders and fresh scaffolds are exempt. The signal is advisory while the validation rule remains INFO/default-off; it can add traceability context and planning-seed work, but it must not alter the exact iteration final-line contract below unless a later enforcement rollout explicitly changes severity.\n\n### Iteration Final-Line Contract (MANDATORY)\n\nEvery `iteration-NNN.md` MUST end with exactly one of the following plain-text lines as the **absolute final line** (no trailing whitespace, no variation):\n\n```\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\n**Mapping rule:** PASS if no P0 or P1 findings in this iteration. CONDITIONAL if any P1 (but no P0) findings. FAIL if any P0 findings. P2-only findings → PASS.\n\n**VERDICT_LOCK:** Any confirmed active P0 forces the exact final line `Review verdict: FAIL`. Do not relabel that state as conditional, partial, mixed, or advisory.\n\nDownstream automation (including the synthesis phase and CI gate parser) parses this final line via exact string match, do not vary the format.\n\n### Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta. The full contract -- per-iteration invariants, failure modes, JSONL audit field, config surface and precedence, executor-invariant guarantees, and the four-value code-graph readiness TrustState surface -- lives in `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Read JSONL and strategy before review action.\n2. Review one dimension per iteration and write findings to `iteration-NNN.md`.\n3. Append JSONL with severity counts, finding detail, and `newInfoRatio`.\n4. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`. Reject inference-only findings.\n5. Re-read cited code before recording any P0.\n6. Keep target files read-only.\n7. Use `generate-context.js` for continuity saves. **Owner**: the YAML workflow (`deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) calls `generate-context.js` at the save phase. The reducer (`scripts/reduce-state.cjs`) does NOT call it directly. Operators should not invoke the reducer expecting continuity-save side effects.\n8. Emit setup `BINDING:` lines before workflow output.\n9. Refuse nested dispatch with: `REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.`\n\n### ❌ NEVER\n\n1. **Dispatch sub-agents**, `@deep-review` is LEAF-only. It cannot dispatch additional agents. When dispatch is requested, use the canonical REFUSE wording (ALWAYS rule 14).\n2. **Hold findings in context**, Write everything to iteration files. Context is discarded after each dispatch.\n3. **Exceed TCB**, Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle.\n4. **Ask the user**, Autonomous execution. The agent makes best-judgment decisions without pausing.\n5. **Skip convergence checks**, Every iteration must be evaluated against convergence criteria before the next dispatch.\n6. **Modify config after init**, `deep-review-config.json` is read-only after initialization.\n7. **Modify files under review**, The review loop is observation-only. No code changes during audit.\n8. **Use WebFetch**, Review is code-only. No external resource fetching is permitted.\n9. **Implement fixes during review**, Report findings only. Implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n\n### Iteration Status Enum\n\n`complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight`\n\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important finding that changes the verdict trajectory.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **3+ consecutive timeouts**, Infrastructure issue. Pause loop and report to user.\n2. **State file corruption**, Cannot reconstruct iteration history from JSONL or iteration files.\n3. **All dimensions covered with P0 findings remaining**, Human sign-off required before shipping.\n4. **Security vulnerabilities discovered in production code**, Escalate immediately. Do not defer to report synthesis.\n5. **All recovery tiers exhausted**, No automatic recovery path remaining in convergence protocol.\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/protocol/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`, `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md`, `assets/deep_review_strategy.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\nScripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n\nDetailed contracts: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (executor invariants, failure modes, config surface) and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` (two-tier content-hash dedup).\n\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for investigation loops, `sk-code-review` for single-pass review doctrine, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state and continuity saves.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Loop Completion\n\nA review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n\n- The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n- Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n- Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n- All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n- `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n- `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n- Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n\n### Quality Gates\n\nEach gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n\n- **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n- **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n- **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n- **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n- **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n- **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n- **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n- **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n- **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n- **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n\n### Validation Success\n\nThe release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n\n- The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n- Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n- `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n- `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n- `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: deep review, code audit, iterative review)\n- **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3. The spec folder determines the `{spec_folder}/review/` state packet location\n- **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface. Canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n- **Command**: `/deep:review` is the primary invocation point\n\n### Continuity Integration\n\nRecover context via `/speckit:resume` in the order `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During review, the agent writes iteration, strategy, and JSONL state. After synthesis, run `generate-context.js`.\n\n### Code Graph Integration\n\n`code_graph_query + Grep` is available to `@deep-review` for semantic code search when Grep/Glob exact matching is insufficient. Use for:\n- Finding all usages of a pattern by concept/intent\n- Locating implementations when exact symbol names are unknown\n- Cross-referencing behavior across unfamiliar code paths\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/baselines/claude-baseline.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-007-delegation-route-proof.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-004-concise-natural-ask.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-005-orchestrate-handoff.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-008-absorption-probe.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-006-auto-missing-inputs.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-001-auto-run-specified.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-002-bare-command-halt.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RVB-003-vague-natural-ask.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/behavior_benchmark/behavior_benchmark.md</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"deep-review","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: deep-review","time":{"start":1782998142524,"end":1782998142541}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f475826e9339bdd016a46647e5f508198bbacdbee7cbffbb3"}},"id":"prt_f22f88e380013NwD1i23V4bZPJ","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f7fae1001V2dIdygcPLKQIB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998142557,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dwYZJNrgVIfsLMEZy2z2DKJA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-review\n3: description: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\n5: argument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations]\"\n6: version: 1.11.0.0\n7: ---\n8: <!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n9: \n10: <!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n11: \n12: # Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n13: \n14: Iterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n15: \n16: Runtime path resolution:\n17: - OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n18: - Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n19: \n20: Convergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n21: \n22: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n23: \n24: ### When to Use This Skill\n25: \n26: Use this skill when:\n27: - Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n28: - Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n29: - Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n30: - Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n31: - Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n32: - Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n33: - Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n34: \n35: ### When NOT to Use\n36: \n37: - Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n38: - Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n39: - Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n40: - Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n41: - Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n42: \n43: ### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n44: \n45: This skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n46: \n47: **NEVER:**\n48: - Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n49: - Invoke cli-opencode / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n50: - Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n51: - Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n52: - Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n53: - Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n54: \n55: **COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n56: \n57: **ALWAYS:**\n58: - Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n59: - Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n60: - Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n61: - Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n62: - Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n63: \n64: ### Trigger Phrases\n65: \n66: - \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n67: - \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n68: - \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n69: - \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n70: - \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n71: - \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n72: - \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n73: \n74: ### Keyword Triggers\n75: \n76: `deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n81: \n82: \n83: ### Resource Loading Levels\n84: \n85: | Level | When to Load | Resources |\n86: |-------|-------------|-----------|\n87: | ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n88: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n89: | ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n90: \n91: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n92: \n93: - Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n94: - Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n95: - Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n96: - Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n97: \n98: ```python\n99: from pathlib import Path\n100: \n101: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n102: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n103: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n104: \n105: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n106:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n107:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n108:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n109:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n110: }\n111: \n112: NOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n113:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n114:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n115:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n116:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n117: }\n118: \n119: # RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\n120: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n121:     \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n122:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n123:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n124:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n125:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n126:         \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n127:     ],\n128:     \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n129:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n130:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n131:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n132:     ],\n133:     \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n134:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n135:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n136:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n137:     ],\n138:     \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n139:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n140:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n141:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n142:         \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n143:     ],\n144: }\n145: \n146: LOADING_LEVELS = {\n147:     \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n148:     \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n149:     \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n150:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n151:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n152:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n153:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n154:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n155:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n156:     ],\n157: }\n158: \n159: PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n160:     \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n161:     \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n162:     \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n163:     \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n164: }\n165: \n166: NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n167:     \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n168: }\n169: \n170: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n171:     \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n172:     \"Confirm the review phase\",\n173:     \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n174:     \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n175: ]\n176: \n177: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n178:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n179:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n180:     if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n181:         raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n182:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n183: \n184: def discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n185:     docs = []\n186:     for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n187:         if base.exists():\n188:             docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n189:     return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n190: \n191: def get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n192:     phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n193:     if phase:\n194:         return phase\n195:     text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n196:     if \"recovery\" in text:\n197:         return \"stuck\"\n198:     if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n199:         return \"synthesis\"\n200:     if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n201:         return \"iteration\"\n202:     return \"init\"\n203: \n204: def route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n205:     inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n206:     routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n207:     scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n208:     intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n209: \n210:     loaded = []\n211:     seen = set()\n212: \n213:     def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n214:         guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n215:         if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n216:             load(guarded)\n217:             loaded.append(guarded)\n218:             seen.add(guarded)\n219: \n220:     for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n221:         load_if_available(relative_path)\n222: \n223:     if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n224:         return {\n225:             \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n226:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n227:             \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n228:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n229:             \"resources\": loaded,\n230:         }\n231: \n232:     phase_resources = PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP.get(routing_key, [])\n233:     if routing_key == \"unknown\" or not phase_resources:\n234:         return {\n235:             \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n236:             \"notice\": f\"No review resources found for routing key '{routing_key}'\",\n237:             \"resources\": loaded,\n238:         }\n239: \n240:     for intent in intents:\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 500. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\nargument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations]\"\nversion: 1.11.0.0\n---\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: \"Autonomous iterative code-review loop with externalized state, convergence detection, P0/P1/P2 findings, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query]\nargument-hint: \"[target] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations]\"\nversion: 1.11.0.0\n---\n<!-- Note: Task is for the command executor (loop management); @deep-review agent is LEAF-only (no Task). No WebFetch: review is code-only. -->\n\n<!-- Keywords: deep-review, code-audit, iterative-review, review-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, review-agent, JSONL-state, severity-findings, P0-P1-P2, release-readiness, spec-alignment -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Review Loop\n\nIterative code review and quality auditing protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, convergence detection, and severity-weighted findings (P0/P1/P2).\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n\nConvergence threshold semantics and sibling-parity notes (deep-review 0.10 vs deep-research 0.05 vs deep-ai-council 0.20) live in `references/convergence/convergence.md` §1 under \"Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\".\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### When to Use This Skill\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Code quality audit requiring multiple rounds across different review dimensions\n- Spec folder validation requiring cross-reference checks between docs and implementation\n- Release readiness check before shipping a feature or component\n- Finding misalignments between spec documents and actual code\n- Verifying cross-references across documentation, agents, commands, and code\n- Iterative review where each dimension's findings inform subsequent dimensions\n- Unattended or overnight audit sessions\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple single-pass code review (use `sk-code-review` instead)\n- Known issues that just need fixing (go directly to implementation)\n- Implementation tasks (use `sk-code` or `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick one-file checks (use direct Grep/Read)\n- Fewer than 2 review dimensions needed (single-pass suffices)\n\n### FORBIDDEN INVOCATION PATTERNS\n\nThis skill is invoked EXCLUSIVELY through the `/deep:review` command. The command's YAML workflow owns state, dispatch, and convergence.\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Write a custom bash/shell dispatcher to parallelize iterations (ad-hoc shell fan-out)\n- Invoke cli-opencode / cli-claude-code directly in a loop to simulate iterations\n- Manually write iteration prompts to `/tmp` and dispatch them via `copilot -p`\n- Dispatch the `@deep-review` LEAF agent via the Task tool for iteration loops (the agent is LEAF, a single iteration, and MUST be driven by the command's workflow)\n- Skip the state machine: `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-config.json`, `deltas/`, `prompts/`, `logs/`\n- Manage iteration state outside the resolved local review packet under `{spec_folder}/review/`\n\n**COMMAND-DRIVEN FAN-OUT IS SUPPORTED:** use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on `/deep:review`. The command's YAML `step_fanout_spawn` owns multi-lineage dispatch; `fanout-merge.cjs` applies strongest-restriction (any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL). This is not ad-hoc shell dispatch — it is the canonical fan-out path. Intra-lineage wave orchestration remains deferred.\n\n**ALWAYS:**\n- Invoke via `/deep:review :auto` or `/deep:review :confirm`\n- Let the command's YAML workflow own dispatch (auto: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`)\n- Let `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` be the SINGLE state writer\n- Require every iteration to produce BOTH the markdown narrative AND the JSONL delta (dispatch scripts must fail if either is missing)\n- Use `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs` to locate the canonical review root\n\n### Trigger Phrases\n\n- \"review code quality\" / \"audit this code\"\n- \"audit spec folder\" / \"validate spec completeness\"\n- \"release readiness check\" / \"pre-release review\"\n- \"find misalignments\" (between spec and implementation)\n- \"verify cross-references\" (across docs and code)\n- \"deep review\" / \"iterative review\" / \"review loop\"\n- \"quality audit\" / \"convergence detection\"\n\n### Keyword Triggers\n\n`deep review`, `code audit`, `iterative review`, `review loop`, `release readiness`, `spec folder review`, `convergence detection`, `quality audit`, `find misalignments`, `verify cross-references`, `pre-release review`, `audit spec folder`\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | `references/protocol/quick_reference.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop protocol, convergence, state format, review contract |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full protocol docs, detailed specifications |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards markdown paths, checks `inventory`, and uses `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - `get_routing_key()` derives the review phase from dispatch context.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` returns review disambiguation and missing phases return a \"no review resources\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/protocol/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"deep review\", \"review mode\", \"code audit\", \"iterative review\", \":review\", \"audit spec\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"review iteration\", \"dimension review\", \"review findings\", \"P0\", \"P1\", \"P2\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review convergence\", \"coverage gate\", \"verdict\", \"binary gate\", \"all dimensions\"]},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"review report\", \"remediation\", \"verdict\", \"release readiness\", \"planning packet\"]},\n}\n\nNOISY_SYNONYMS = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       {\"audit code\": 2.0, \"review spec folder\": 1.8, \"release readiness\": 1.5, \"pre-release\": 1.5},\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   {\"review dimension\": 1.5, \"check correctness\": 1.4, \"check security\": 1.4, \"check alignment\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": {\"all dimensions covered\": 1.6, \"coverage complete\": 1.5, \"stop review\": 1.4},\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      {\"review results\": 1.5, \"what to fix\": 1.4, \"ship decision\": 1.6, \"final report\": 1.5},\n}\n\n# RESOURCE_MAP: local markdown assets + local review-specific protocol docs\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"REVIEW_SETUP\":       [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_strategy.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_ITERATION\":   [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_CONVERGENCE\": [\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n    ],\n    \"REVIEW_REPORT\":      [\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\":            [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all templates\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep review\", \"deep-review wave\", \"review artifact\", \"release-readiness audit\", \"convergence-tracked\", \"same session lineage\", \"P0\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\":         [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nPHASE_RESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"init\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"iteration\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"stuck\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"synthesis\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\", \"assets/deep_review_dashboard.md\"],\n}\n\nNON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES = {\n    \"review_contract\": \"assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\",\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm the review target or spec folder\",\n    \"Confirm the review phase\",\n    \"Provide one concrete file, diff range, or expected finding class\",\n    \"Confirm the verification command set before final review\",\n]\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef get_routing_key(dispatch_context) -> str:\n    phase = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"phase\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n    if phase:\n        return phase\n    text = str(getattr(dispatch_context, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if \"recovery\" in text:\n        return \"stuck\"\n    if \"convergence\" in text or \"synthesis\" in text:\n        return \"synthesis\"\n    if \"iteration\" in text or \"dimension\" in text:\n        return \"iteration\"\n    return \"init\"\n\ndef route_review_resources(task, dispatch_context):\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    routing_key = get_routing_key(dispatch_context)\n    scores = score_intents(task, INTENT_SIGNALS, NOISY_SYNONYMS)\n    intents = select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)\n\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    phase_resources = PHASE_RESOURCE_MAP.get(routing_key, [])\n    if routing_key == \"unknown\" or not phase_resources:\n        return {\n            \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n            \"notice\": f\"No review resources found for routing key '{routing_key}'\",\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    for intent in intents:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":500,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782998142546,"end":1782998142555}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f475826e9339bdd016a46647e5f5c81989da0a68e46006913"}},"id":"prt_f22f88e4f0017lKXCiF6p2NBWC","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f7fae1001V2dIdygcPLKQIB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998144415,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers","callID":"call_KPlinFp0WIMhFNoEHM7rf0nz","state":{"status":"error","input":{"prompt":"You are orchestrating the deep-review workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage. Read .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md and execute the review loop with provided spec_folder, artifact_dir override, session_id, executor, maxIterations 10. Write all outputs only to .opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/review/lineages/gpt and output FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:gpt when complete.","specFolder":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved","tenantId":"","userId":"","agentId":"","limit":5,"session_id":"fanout-gpt-1782998103426-5a2g5w","turnNumber":1,"include_cognitive":true},"error":"{\n  \"summary\": \"Error: sessionId \\\"fanout-gpt-1782998103426-5a2g5w\\\" does not match a server-managed session. Omit sessionId to start a new server-generated session and reuse the effectiveSessionId returned by the server.\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"error\": \"sessionId \\\"fanout-gpt-1782998103426-5a2g5w\\\" does not match a server-managed session. Omit sessionId to start a new server-generated session and reuse the effectiveSessionId returned by the server.\",\n    \"code\": \"E_SESSION_SCOPE\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"requestedSessionId\": \"fanout-gpt-1782998103426-5a2g5w\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"hints\": [\n    \"Omit session_id to start a new server-generated session, or reuse the effectiveSessionId returned by memory_context.\"\n  ],\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"tool\": \"memory_match_triggers\",\n    \"tokenCount\": 221,\n    \"cacheHit\": false,\n    \"isError\": true,\n    \"severity\": \"error\",\n    \"tokenBudget\": 3500\n  }\n}","time":{"start":1782998142519,"end":1782998144413}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f475826e9339bdd016a46647e5f3481989d5a3892c0611608"}},"id":"prt_f22f88e0d001D1xgsSyUiGEPMf","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f7fae1001V2dIdygcPLKQIB"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782998144802,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22f8971f001lkqe9EbwCE6k0C","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","messageID":"msg_f22f7fae1001V2dIdygcPLKQIB","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28870,"input":28038,"output":316,"reasoning":516,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782998147101,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22f8a01b001ig0W633yOlnaWX","messageID":"msg_f22f89885001iInzGWJjhNp1H1","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1782998182991,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22f8eddc001t5INuSdb0prjOs","messageID":"msg_f22f89885001iInzGWJjhNp1H1","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"text","text":"The memory trigger lookup rejected the provided detached `session_id` because it is not a server-managed memory session; I’m retrying without binding that MCP session id and keeping the user-provided id only in the lineage artifacts.","time":{"start":1782998167004,"end":1782998182989},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02701d36d99158ea016a466496f84881918f1c73543e30f445","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998183084,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_YaYRoTxV7qcBPYT4HvCXA8Kb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","offset":241,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n241:         for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n242:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n243: \n244:     for relative_path in phase_resources:\n245:         load_if_available(relative_path)\n246: \n247:     task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n248:     if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n249:         for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n250:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n251: \n252:     return {\n253:         \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n254:         \"intents\": intents,\n255:         \"resources\": loaded,\n256:         \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n257:     }\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ### Phase Detection\n261: \n262: Detect the current review phase from dispatch context to load appropriate resources:\n263: \n264: | Phase | Signal | Resources to Load |\n265: |-------|--------|-------------------|\n266: | Init | No JSONL exists in `review/` | Loop protocol, state format, state outputs, review contract |\n267: | Iteration | Dispatch context includes dimension + iteration number | Loop protocol, convergence, convergence signals, review contract |\n268: | Stuck | Dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY\" | Convergence, convergence signals, loop protocol, reducer registry |\n269: | Synthesis | Convergence triggered STOP | Review contract, state format, state outputs, reducer registry |\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n274: \n275: ### Resource Map Coverage Gate\n276: \n277: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep review treats it as a first-class audit input instead of optional prompt wiring.\n278: \n279: - Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-review-config.json`.\n280: - Add a resource-map snapshot to `Known Context` so later iterations inherit the packet inventory baseline.\n281: - Promote `Resource Map Coverage` to a first-class audit angle alongside correctness, regression risk, test coverage, cross-runtime parity, observability, and docs-vs-code drift.\n282: - Reserve at least one loop iteration to cross-check `target_files` from `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md` against `resource-map.md`.\n283: - Treat that pass as mandatory coverage work, not an optional traceability extra.\n284: - Classify results into three buckets: entries touched, entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n285: - Findings emitted from that audit use the `resource-map-coverage` category.\n286: - Synthesis inserts `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` into `review-report.md` when the map was present at init.\n287: - Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from review delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n288: \n289: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n290: \n291: - Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n292: - Log `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` in `Known Context`.\n293: - Skip the coverage-gate pass and omit the report section without failing the loop.\n294: \n295: ### Architecture\n296: \n297: `/deep:review` owns the loop. The YAML workflow initializes state, dispatches one LEAF review iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `review-report.md`, and saves continuity. The LEAF agent reads state, reviews one dimension, writes `iteration-NNN.md`, updates strategy, and appends JSONL.\n298: \n299: ### State Packet Location\n300: \n301: The review state packet always lives under the target spec's local `review/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/review/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/review/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `review/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n302: \n303: Example (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n304: \n305: Example (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n306: \n307: Core artifacts: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `.deep-review-pause`, `resource-map.md`, `review-report.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n308: \n309: ### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n310: \n311: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n312: \n313: ### Data Flow\n314: \n315: Init creates config, strategy, and JSONL state. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches one dimension, records findings, and reduces state. Synthesis compiles the final report and saves continuity.\n316: \n317: ### Review Dimensions\n318: \n319: The four primary review dimensions (configured in `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`):\n320: \n321: | Dimension | Focus | Key Questions |\n322: |-----------|-------|---------------|\n323: | **Correctness** | Logic, behavior, error handling | Does the code do what it claims? Are edge cases handled? |\n324: | **Security** | Vulnerabilities, exposure, trust boundaries | Are inputs validated? Are credentials exposed? |\n325: | **Spec-Alignment / Traceability** | Spec vs. implementation fidelity | Does code match spec.md? Are all planned items present? |\n326: | **Completeness / Maintainability** | Coverage, dead code, documentation | Are TODOs resolved? Is the code self-documenting? |\n327: \n328: ### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n329: \n330: Review mode is lineage-aware. Supported lifecycle modes are `new`, `resume`, and `restart`. Required lineage fields include `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, and `releaseReadinessState`. The reducer consumes the latest JSONL delta, the new iteration file, and prior reduced state, then emits finding registry, dashboard metrics, and strategy updates.\n331: \n332: ### Severity Classification\n333: \n334: | Severity | Criteria | Blocking |\n335: |----------|----------|---------|\n336: | **P0** | Correctness failure, security vulnerability, spec contradiction | Yes, blocks PASS verdict |\n337: | **P1** | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation | Conditional, triggers CONDITIONAL verdict |\n338: | **P2** | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps | No, PASS with advisories |\n339: \n340: ### Verdicts\n341: \n342: | Verdict | Condition |\n343: |---------|-----------|\n344: | **PASS** | No P0/P1 findings, P2 findings recorded as advisories (`hasAdvisories: true`) |\n345: | **CONDITIONAL** | P1 findings present, remediation plan included in report |\n346: | **FAIL** | Any P0 finding confirmed after adversarial self-check |\n347: \n348: ### Verdict Lock and Advisory Risk Score\n349: \n350: Always emit exactly one parseable verdict. A confirmed active P0 locks the verdict to `FAIL`; do not soften it to `CONDITIONAL`, `partial`, or any other phrasing. Truncated or partial iteration output is not a valid substitute for the final verdict line. Review narratives and JSONL details may include an optional advisory `riskScore` for relative risk calibration, but it never changes the `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` mapping.\n351: \n352: ### Acceptance-Coverage Signal\n353: \n354: When the review target is a spec folder, deep review reflects the `AC_COVERAGE` validation signal in synthesis for Level 2+ folders only after both lifecycle conditions are true: `checklist.md` exists and `implementation-summary.md` is in-progress or later. Level 1 folders and fresh scaffolds are exempt. The signal is advisory while the validation rule remains INFO/default-off; it can add traceability context and planning-seed work, but it must not alter the exact iteration final-line contract below unless a later enforcement rollout explicitly changes severity.\n355: \n356: ### Iteration Final-Line Contract (MANDATORY)\n357: \n358: Every `iteration-NNN.md` MUST end with exactly one of the following plain-text lines as the **absolute final line** (no trailing whitespace, no variation):\n359: \n360: ```\n361: Review verdict: PASS\n362: ```\n363: \n364: ```\n365: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n366: ```\n367: \n368: ```\n369: Review verdict: FAIL\n370: ```\n371: \n372: **Mapping rule:** PASS if no P0 or P1 findings in this iteration. CONDITIONAL if any P1 (but no P0) findings. FAIL if any P0 findings. P2-only findings → PASS.\n373: \n374: **VERDICT_LOCK:** Any confirmed active P0 forces the exact final line `Review verdict: FAIL`. Do not relabel that state as conditional, partial, mixed, or advisory.\n375: \n376: Downstream automation (including the synthesis phase and CI gate parser) parses this final line via exact string match, do not vary the format.\n377: \n378: ### Executor Selection Contract\n379: \n380: Executor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta. The full contract -- per-iteration invariants, failure modes, JSONL audit field, config surface and precedence, executor-invariant guarantees, and the four-value code-graph readiness TrustState surface -- lives in `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## 4. RULES\n385: \n386: ### ✅ ALWAYS\n387: \n388: 1. Read JSONL and strategy before review action.\n389: 2. Review one dimension per iteration and write findings to `iteration-NNN.md`.\n390: 3. Append JSONL with severity counts, finding detail, and `newInfoRatio`.\n391: 4. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`. Reject inference-only findings.\n392: 5. Re-read cited code before recording any P0.\n393: 6. Keep target files read-only.\n394: 7. Use `generate-context.js` for continuity saves. **Owner**: the YAML workflow (`deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) calls `generate-context.js` at the save phase. The reducer (`scripts/reduce-state.cjs`) does NOT call it directly. Operators should not invoke the reducer expecting continuity-save side effects.\n395: 8. Emit setup `BINDING:` lines before workflow output.\n396: 9. Refuse nested dispatch with: `REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.`\n397: \n398: ### ❌ NEVER\n399: \n400: 1. **Dispatch sub-agents**, `@deep-review` is LEAF-only. It cannot dispatch additional agents. When dispatch is requested, use the canonical REFUSE wording (ALWAYS rule 14).\n401: 2. **Hold findings in context**, Write everything to iteration files. Context is discarded after each dispatch.\n402: 3. **Exceed TCB**, Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle.\n403: 4. **Ask the user**, Autonomous execution. The agent makes best-judgment decisions without pausing.\n404: 5. **Skip convergence checks**, Every iteration must be evaluated against convergence criteria before the next dispatch.\n405: 6. **Modify config after init**, `deep-review-config.json` is read-only after initialization.\n406: 7. **Modify files under review**, The review loop is observation-only. No code changes during audit.\n407: 8. **Use WebFetch**, Review is code-only. No external resource fetching is permitted.\n408: 9. **Implement fixes during review**, Report findings only. Implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n409: \n410: ### Iteration Status Enum\n411: \n412: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight`\n413: \n414: - `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important finding that changes the verdict trajectory.\n415: \n416: ### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n417: \n418: 1. **3+ consecutive timeouts**, Infrastructure issue. Pause loop and report to user.\n419: 2. **State file corruption**, Cannot reconstruct iteration history from JSONL or iteration files.\n420: 3. **All dimensions covered with P0 findings remaining**, Human sign-off required before shipping.\n421: 4. **Security vulnerabilities discovered in production code**, Escalate immediately. Do not defer to report synthesis.\n422: 5. **All recovery tiers exhausted**, No automatic recovery path remaining in convergence protocol.\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n427: \n428: The router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/protocol/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`, `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md`, `assets/deep_review_strategy.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n429: \n430: Scripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n431: \n432: Detailed contracts: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (executor invariants, failure modes, config surface) and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` (two-tier content-hash dedup).\n433: \n434: Related skills: `deep-research` for investigation loops, `sk-code-review` for single-pass review doctrine, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state and continuity saves.\n435: \n436: ---\n437: \n438: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n439: \n440: ### Loop Completion\n441: \n442: A review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n443: \n444: - The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n445: - Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n446: - Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n447: - All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n448: - `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n449: - `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n450: - Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n451: \n452: ### Quality Gates\n453: \n454: Each gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n455: \n456: - **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n457: - **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n458: - **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n459: - **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n460: - **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n461: - **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n462: - **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n463: - **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n464: - **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n465: - **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n466: \n467: ### Validation Success\n468: \n469: The release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n470: \n471: - The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n472: - Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n473: - `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n474: - `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n475: - `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n476: \n477: ---\n478: \n479: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n480: \n481: ### Framework Integration\n482: \n483: This skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md).\n484: \n485: Key integrations:\n486: - **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: deep review, code audit, iterative review)\n487: - **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3. The spec folder determines the `{spec_folder}/review/` state packet location\n488: - **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface. Canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n489: - **Command**: `/deep:review` is the primary invocation point\n490: \n491: ### Continuity Integration\n492: \n493: Recover context via `/speckit:resume` in the order `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During review, the agent writes iteration, strategy, and JSONL state. After synthesis, run `generate-context.js`.\n494: \n495: ### Code Graph Integration\n496: \n497: `code_graph_query + Grep` is available to `@deep-review` for semantic code search when Grep/Glob exact matching is insufficient. Use for:\n498: - Finding all usages of a pattern by concept/intent\n499: - Locating implementations when exact symbol names are unknown\n500: - Cross-referencing behavior across unfamiliar code paths\n\n(End of file - total 500 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    for relative_path in phase_resources:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    return {\n        \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n        \"intents\": intents,\n        \"resources\": loaded,\n        \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n    }\n```\n\n### Phase Detection","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","text":"        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    for relative_path in phase_resources:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    task_text = str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")).lower()\n    if any(keyword in task_text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    return {\n        \"routing_key\": routing_key,\n        \"intents\": intents,\n        \"resources\": loaded,\n        \"non_markdown_references\": NON_MARKDOWN_REFERENCES,\n    }\n```\n\n### Phase Detection\n\nDetect the current review phase from dispatch context to load appropriate resources:\n\n| Phase | Signal | Resources to Load |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| Init | No JSONL exists in `review/` | Loop protocol, state format, state outputs, review contract |\n| Iteration | Dispatch context includes dimension + iteration number | Loop protocol, convergence, convergence signals, review contract |\n| Stuck | Dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY\" | Convergence, convergence signals, loop protocol, reducer registry |\n| Synthesis | Convergence triggered STOP | Review contract, state format, state outputs, reducer registry |\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Resource Map Coverage Gate\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep review treats it as a first-class audit input instead of optional prompt wiring.\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-review-config.json`.\n- Add a resource-map snapshot to `Known Context` so later iterations inherit the packet inventory baseline.\n- Promote `Resource Map Coverage` to a first-class audit angle alongside correctness, regression risk, test coverage, cross-runtime parity, observability, and docs-vs-code drift.\n- Reserve at least one loop iteration to cross-check `target_files` from `{spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md` against `resource-map.md`.\n- Treat that pass as mandatory coverage work, not an optional traceability extra.\n- Classify results into three buckets: entries touched, entries not touched (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n- Findings emitted from that audit use the `resource-map-coverage` category.\n- Synthesis inserts `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` into `review-report.md` when the map was present at init.\n- Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from review delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n- Log `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` in `Known Context`.\n- Skip the coverage-gate pass and omit the report section without failing the loop.\n\n### Architecture\n\n`/deep:review` owns the loop. The YAML workflow initializes state, dispatches one LEAF review iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `review-report.md`, and saves continuity. The LEAF agent reads state, reviews one dimension, writes `iteration-NNN.md`, updates strategy, and appends JSONL.\n\n### State Packet Location\n\nThe review state packet always lives under the target spec's local `review/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/review/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/review/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `review/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\nExample (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../006-continuity-refactor-gates/003-gate-c-writer-ready/` → `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/` (flat, no subfolder).\n\nExample (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `003-gate-c-writer-ready/review/003-gate-c-writer-ready-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n\nCore artifacts: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, `.deep-review-pause`, `resource-map.md`, `review-report.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n\n### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Data Flow\n\nInit creates config, strategy, and JSONL state. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches one dimension, records findings, and reduces state. Synthesis compiles the final report and saves continuity.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\nThe four primary review dimensions (configured in `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml`):\n\n| Dimension | Focus | Key Questions |\n|-----------|-------|---------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, behavior, error handling | Does the code do what it claims? Are edge cases handled? |\n| **Security** | Vulnerabilities, exposure, trust boundaries | Are inputs validated? Are credentials exposed? |\n| **Spec-Alignment / Traceability** | Spec vs. implementation fidelity | Does code match spec.md? Are all planned items present? |\n| **Completeness / Maintainability** | Coverage, dead code, documentation | Are TODOs resolved? Is the code self-documenting? |\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\nReview mode is lineage-aware. Supported lifecycle modes are `new`, `resume`, and `restart`. Required lineage fields include `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, and `releaseReadinessState`. The reducer consumes the latest JSONL delta, the new iteration file, and prior reduced state, then emits finding registry, dashboard metrics, and strategy updates.\n\n### Severity Classification\n\n| Severity | Criteria | Blocking |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **P0** | Correctness failure, security vulnerability, spec contradiction | Yes, blocks PASS verdict |\n| **P1** | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation | Conditional, triggers CONDITIONAL verdict |\n| **P2** | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps | No, PASS with advisories |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **PASS** | No P0/P1 findings, P2 findings recorded as advisories (`hasAdvisories: true`) |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | P1 findings present, remediation plan included in report |\n| **FAIL** | Any P0 finding confirmed after adversarial self-check |\n\n### Verdict Lock and Advisory Risk Score\n\nAlways emit exactly one parseable verdict. A confirmed active P0 locks the verdict to `FAIL`; do not soften it to `CONDITIONAL`, `partial`, or any other phrasing. Truncated or partial iteration output is not a valid substitute for the final verdict line. Review narratives and JSONL details may include an optional advisory `riskScore` for relative risk calibration, but it never changes the `PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` mapping.\n\n### Acceptance-Coverage Signal\n\nWhen the review target is a spec folder, deep review reflects the `AC_COVERAGE` validation signal in synthesis for Level 2+ folders only after both lifecycle conditions are true: `checklist.md` exists and `implementation-summary.md` is in-progress or later. Level 1 folders and fresh scaffolds are exempt. The signal is advisory while the validation rule remains INFO/default-off; it can add traceability context and planning-seed work, but it must not alter the exact iteration final-line contract below unless a later enforcement rollout explicitly changes severity.\n\n### Iteration Final-Line Contract (MANDATORY)\n\nEvery `iteration-NNN.md` MUST end with exactly one of the following plain-text lines as the **absolute final line** (no trailing whitespace, no variation):\n\n```\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\n**Mapping rule:** PASS if no P0 or P1 findings in this iteration. CONDITIONAL if any P1 (but no P0) findings. FAIL if any P0 findings. P2-only findings → PASS.\n\n**VERDICT_LOCK:** Any confirmed active P0 forces the exact final line `Review verdict: FAIL`. Do not relabel that state as conditional, partial, mixed, or advisory.\n\nDownstream automation (including the synthesis phase and CI gate parser) parses this final line via exact string match, do not vary the format.\n\n### Executor Selection Contract\n\nExecutor settings are owned by the YAML workflow and rendered prompt pack. Do not bypass the workflow by hand-dispatching review iterations; each iteration stays LEAF-only and produces the required markdown plus JSONL delta. The full contract -- per-iteration invariants, failure modes, JSONL audit field, config surface and precedence, executor-invariant guarantees, and the four-value code-graph readiness TrustState surface -- lives in `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ✅ ALWAYS\n\n1. Read JSONL and strategy before review action.\n2. Review one dimension per iteration and write findings to `iteration-NNN.md`.\n3. Append JSONL with severity counts, finding detail, and `newInfoRatio`.\n4. Cite every finding with `[SOURCE: file:line]`. Reject inference-only findings.\n5. Re-read cited code before recording any P0.\n6. Keep target files read-only.\n7. Use `generate-context.js` for continuity saves. **Owner**: the YAML workflow (`deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) calls `generate-context.js` at the save phase. The reducer (`scripts/reduce-state.cjs`) does NOT call it directly. Operators should not invoke the reducer expecting continuity-save side effects.\n8. Emit setup `BINDING:` lines before workflow output.\n9. Refuse nested dispatch with: `REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.`\n\n### ❌ NEVER\n\n1. **Dispatch sub-agents**, `@deep-review` is LEAF-only. It cannot dispatch additional agents. When dispatch is requested, use the canonical REFUSE wording (ALWAYS rule 14).\n2. **Hold findings in context**, Write everything to iteration files. Context is discarded after each dispatch.\n3. **Exceed TCB**, Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12). Breadth over depth per cycle.\n4. **Ask the user**, Autonomous execution. The agent makes best-judgment decisions without pausing.\n5. **Skip convergence checks**, Every iteration must be evaluated against convergence criteria before the next dispatch.\n6. **Modify config after init**, `deep-review-config.json` is read-only after initialization.\n7. **Modify files under review**, The review loop is observation-only. No code changes during audit.\n8. **Use WebFetch**, Review is code-only. No external resource fetching is permitted.\n9. **Implement fixes during review**, Report findings only. Implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n\n### Iteration Status Enum\n\n`complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight`\n\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important finding that changes the verdict trajectory.\n\n### ⚠️ ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **3+ consecutive timeouts**, Infrastructure issue. Pause loop and report to user.\n2. **State file corruption**, Cannot reconstruct iteration history from JSONL or iteration files.\n3. **All dimensions covered with P0 findings remaining**, Human sign-off required before shipping.\n4. **Security vulnerabilities discovered in production code**, Escalate immediately. Do not defer to report synthesis.\n5. **All recovery tiers exhausted**, No automatic recovery path remaining in convergence protocol.\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/protocol/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`, `assets/deep_review_dashboard.md`, `assets/deep_review_strategy.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n\nScripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n\nDetailed contracts: `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` (executor invariants, failure modes, config surface) and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` (two-tier content-hash dedup).\n\nRelated skills: `deep-research` for investigation loops, `sk-code-review` for single-pass review doctrine, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state and continuity saves.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Loop Completion\n\nA review loop is considered complete when every item below holds:\n\n- The loop reached convergence (composite stop score above `compositeStopScore`, with required gates green) OR hit `maxIterations` without false-positive STOP.\n- Every configured review dimension has at least one full iteration of coverage recorded in `deep-review-state.jsonl` and reflected in `deep-review-strategy.md`.\n- Required traceability protocols (`spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`) executed at least once. Overlay protocols that apply to the target type ran or were explicitly marked N/A.\n- All canonical state files exist and parse cleanly: `deep-review-config.json`, `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, `deep-review-strategy.md`, `deep-review-dashboard.md`, and one `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` per dispatched iteration.\n- `review/resource-map.md` was emitted from converged delta evidence unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag `--no-resource-map`).\n- `review/review-report.md` carries all 9 core sections (Executive Summary, Planning Trigger, Active Finding Registry, Remediation Workstreams, Spec Seed, Plan Seed, Traceability Status, Deferred Items, Audit Appendix) plus the conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present == true`.\n- Canonical continuity surfaces updated via `generate-context.js` (description.json, graph-metadata.json, indexed memory entries).\n\n### Quality Gates\n\nEach gate is binary: pass or block. STOP cannot be legal until every gate passes.\n\n- **Config validity**: `deep-review-config.json` parses, names every required field, and lineage block matches the current run (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`).\n- **Strategy initialization**: `deep-review-strategy.md` carries the Files Under Review table, Cross-Reference Status grouped by core vs overlay, Known Context, and Review Boundaries.\n- **State consistency**: `deep-review-state.jsonl` opens with the config record and appends one iteration record per dispatched iteration. Reducer-owned fields in `deep-review-findings-registry.json` reconcile against JSONL totals.\n- **Iteration completeness**: every dispatched iteration produced both an `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` (non-empty, ending with the canonical `Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL` line) AND a JSONL delta record with `findingDetails[]`, `findingsSummary`, `newFindingsRatio`.\n- **Severity coverage**: every reported finding carries `severity` in {P0, P1, P2}, `category`, `file:line` evidence, `finding_class`, and a `content_hash` for synthesis dedup.\n- **Advisory numeric score**: `riskScore` may appear in finding details as non-gating context only; verdict logic must ignore it.\n- **Adversarial replay**: every P0 finding survived adversarial self-check. Rejected P0s downgraded with rationale recorded in the iteration narrative.\n- **Coverage threshold**: `dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count` AND required traceability protocols covered, stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations.\n- **Acceptance coverage**: when the spec-folder lifecycle predicate is active, the final report records `AC_COVERAGE` status, covered/total, floor, and next action; default-off INFO output is advisory and does not by itself block STOP.\n- **Security-sensitive override**: when the run targets security, path handling, env precedence, schema boundaries, persistence, or shared policy, the gates from `references/convergence/convergence.md` \"Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\" apply (`minStabilizationPasses=2`, closed-finding replay required, fix-completeness gate enforced).\n\n### Validation Success\n\nThe release-readiness handoff is valid when:\n\n- The final report records stop reason, iteration count, dimension coverage, severity counts (P0/P1/P2), verdict (PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL), and release-readiness state (`in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking`).\n- Verdict logic matches: PASS = no P0/P1 findings (P2 advisories permitted with `hasAdvisories: true`). CONDITIONAL = P1 findings present with remediation plan. FAIL = any P0 confirmed after adversarial self-check.\n- `resource-map.md` Phase-5 Augmentation section (if present) lists novel logic gaps with iteration source links, or explicitly records the empty-result case.\n- `skill_advisor.py \"run a deep review loop\" --threshold 0.8` still surfaces the skill after any graph-metadata edits.\n- `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <spec-folder> --strict` exits 0 on the target spec folder.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: deep review, code audit, iterative review)\n- **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3. The spec folder determines the `{spec_folder}/review/` state packet location\n- **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface. Canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n- **Command**: `/deep:review` is the primary invocation point\n\n### Continuity Integration\n\nRecover context via `/speckit:resume` in the order `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During review, the agent writes iteration, strategy, and JSONL state. After synthesis, run `generate-context.js`.\n\n### Code Graph Integration\n\n`code_graph_query + Grep` is available to `@deep-review` for semantic code search when Grep/Glob exact matching is insufficient. Use for:\n- Finding all usages of a pattern by concept/intent\n- Locating implementations when exact symbol names are unknown\n- Cross-referencing behavior across unfamiliar code paths","lineStart":241,"lineEnd":500,"totalLines":500,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782998183072,"end":1782998183082}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02701d36d99158ea016a4664a4fed081919f64cda200b73db4"}},"id":"prt_f22f92c9d001MzaWIAGNnjW77j","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f89885001iInzGWJjhNp1H1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998183092,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1x3DEl7qbkbqKIR2KH2A47iv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   session_id: \"[SESSION_ID] - Optional caller-supplied session id for fan-out lineages. Default: timestamp.\"\n34:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n35:   max_iterations: 7\n36:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n37:   stop_policy: \"[convergence|max-iterations] - Stop behavior. Default: convergence. max-iterations treats convergence as telemetry until the hard iteration ceiling.\"\n38:   config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: \"[optional internal path] - Fan-out lineage artifact override for command-owned single-lineage execution.\"\n39: \n40: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n41: # CONTEXT LOADING\n42: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n43: context_loading:\n44:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n45:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n46:   mcp_integration:\n47:     tool: memory_context\n48:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n49:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n50:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n51:   behavior:\n52:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n53:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n54: \n55: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n56: # SKILL REFERENCE\n57: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n58: skill_reference:\n59:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n60:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n61:   references:\n62:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n63:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n64:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n65:   templates:\n66:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n67:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n68: \n69: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n70: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n71: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n72: agent_config:\n73:   agent: deep-review\n74:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n75:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n76:   mode: subagent\n77:   model: opus\n78:   leaf_only: true\n79:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n80:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n81:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n82: \n83: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n84: # STATE FILE PATHS\n85: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n86: state_paths:\n87:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n88:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n89:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n90:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n91:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n92:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n93:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n94:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n95:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n96:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n97:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n98:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n99:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n100:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n101:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n102:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n103:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n104:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n105:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n106:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n107:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n108:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n109:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n110:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n111:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n112:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n113: \n114: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n115: # WORKFLOW\n116: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n117: workflow:\n118: \n119:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n120:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n121:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n122:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n123:     if_present:\n124:       bind:\n125:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n126:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n127:         artifact_subfolder: null\n128:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n129:     if_absent:\n130:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n131:       outputs:\n132:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n133:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n134:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n135:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n136: \n137:   step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n138:     description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n139:     skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n140:     instructions: |\n141:       This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n142:       immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n143:       cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n144:       fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n145:       authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n146:       second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n147:       the packet directory.\n148:     command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n149:     outputs:\n150:       - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n151:       - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n152:     on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n153: \n154:   step_fanout_spawn:\n155:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n156:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n157:     instructions: |\n158:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n159:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n160:       A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n161:       session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n162:       self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n163:       first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n164:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n165:       deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n166:       deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n167:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n168:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n169:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n170:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n171:     sub_steps:\n172:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n173:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n174:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n175:         command: |\n176:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n177:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n178:             --loop-type review \\\n179:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n180:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n181:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n182:             --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n183:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n184:         wait_for_completion: true\n185: \n186:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n187:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n188:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n189:   phase_init:\n190:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n191:     steps:\n192: \n193:       step_preflight_contract:\n194:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n195:         verify:\n196:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, stop_policy]\n197:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n198:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n199:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n200:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n201: \n202:       step_create_directories:\n203:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n204:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n205: \n206:       step_detect_resource_map:\n207:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n208:         inspect:\n209:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n210:         classify:\n211:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n212:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n213:         outputs:\n214:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n215:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n216: \n217:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n218:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n219:         detect:\n220:           canonical_review_state:\n221:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n222:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n223:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n224:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n225:           legacy_review_state:\n226:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n227:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n228:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n229:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n230:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n231:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n232:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n233:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n234:           legacy_review_markers:\n235:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n236:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n237:         migrate_only:\n238:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n239:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n240:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 1603. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the dispatch-context check before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (dispatch-context check) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: DISPATCH-CONTEXT CHECK\n\n**STATUS: ☐ CHECKED**\n\n```\nThis gate checks actual dispatch context, not self-reported capability -- the prior\nself-assessment version of this check produced a confirmed false-positive block (a\ncapable agent judged itself \"uncertain\" on an abstract question and hard-stopped).\n\nCHECK: was this file invoked directly as /deep:context (typed by the user, or an\nexplicit Task delegation naming this exact command) -- as opposed to another agent\npasting this file's raw content into a Task-dispatch prompt as inline ad hoc\ninstructions for a worker to follow (that worker should follow its own dispatch\nprompt, not re-run this command's full setup contract)?\n\n├─ YES, or no concrete evidence of the pasted-inline case:\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ NO, with concrete evidence this file's content was pasted inline rather than\n   invoked as the command itself:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ DIRECT INVOCATION REQUIRED                              │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:context [arguments]                                │\n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Must be invoked directly, not pasted as inline sub-agent instructions\"\n\nDefault on ambiguity: PROCEED. Do not block on an inability to introspect abstract\ncapability (e.g. \"can I orchestrate a workflow\") -- that question is unanswerable\nfrom the inside and is what caused the original false-positive block. Block only on\nconcrete evidence of the pasted-inline case above.\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  session_id: \"[SESSION_ID] - Optional caller-supplied session id for fan-out lineages. Default: timestamp.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n  stop_policy: \"[convergence|max-iterations] - Stop behavior. Default: convergence. max-iterations treats convergence as telemetry until the hard iteration ceiling.\"\n  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: \"[optional internal path] - Fan-out lineage artifact override for command-owned single-lineage execution.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n    description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n    skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n    instructions: |\n      This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n      immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n      cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n      fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n      authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n      second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n      the packet directory.\n    command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n    outputs:\n      - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n      - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n    on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n      session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n      self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n      first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n            --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, stop_policy]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":1603,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998183075,"end":1782998183091}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02701d36d99158ea016a4664a4fee48191803893f7203b30cf"}},"id":"prt_f22f92ca1001gsr1ZJLtUHtqKK","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f89885001iInzGWJjhNp1H1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998183094,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aI1XFbUo69w760sjjmKmiZtL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review quick reference\"\n6:   - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n8:   - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n9:   - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: version: 1.11.0.16\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Quick Reference\n16: \n17: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Use this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n30: - Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n31: - Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n32: - Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n33: \n34: ### Commands\n35: \n36: | Command | Description |\n37: |---------|-------------|\n38: | `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n39: | `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n40: | `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n41: \n42: ### Parameters\n43: \n44: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n45: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n46: | `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n47: | `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n48: | `--stop-policy` | convergence | Use `max-iterations` when convergence must not end the run before the iteration ceiling |\n49: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n50: | `--restart` | off | Archive the current review packet and start a fresh lineage |\n51: | `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 2. WHEN TO USE\n56: \n57: | Scenario | Use |\n58: |----------|-----|\n59: | Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n60: | Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n61: | Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n62: | Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n63: | Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n68: \n69: ```\n70: /deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n71:     |                    |                      |\n72:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n73:     |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n74:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n75:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n76:     |                    |\n77:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n78:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n79:     |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n80:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 4. STATE FILES\n86: \n87: Review mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n88: \n89: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n90: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n91: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n92: | State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n93: | Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n94: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n95: | Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n96: | Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n97: | Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n98: | Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n99: \n100: ### Lifecycle Modes\n101: \n102: | Mode | Effect |\n103: |------|--------|\n104: | `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n105: | `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n106: | `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n107: | `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n112: \n113: | ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n114: |----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n115: | D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n116: | D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n117: | D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n118: | D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n123: \n124: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n125: |---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n126: | FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n127: | CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n128: | PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n129: \n130: ### Release Readiness\n131: \n132: `releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n133: \n134: | State | Meaning |\n135: |-------|---------|\n136: | `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n137: | `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n138: | `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n143: \n144: | Gate | Rule |\n145: |------|------|\n146: | Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n147: | Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n148: | Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n153: \n154: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n155: |--------|--------|-------------|\n156: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n157: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n158: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n159: \n160: **Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n161: \n162: **P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n167: \n168: Each @deep-review iteration:\n169: 1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n170: 2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n171: 3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n172: 4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n173: 5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n174: 6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n175: 7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n180: \n181: | # | Section | Purpose |\n182: |---|---------|---------|\n183: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n184: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n185: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n186: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n187: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n188: | 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n189: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n190: | 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n191: | 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n196: \n197: | Goal | Adjustment |\n198: |------|------------|\n199: | Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n200: | Forced iteration ceiling | Set `--stop-policy=max-iterations` with the desired `--max-iterations` |\n201: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n202: | Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n203: | Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n208: \n209: | Problem | Fix |\n210: |---------|-----|\n211: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05, or use `--stop-policy=max-iterations` when early convergence is unacceptable |\n212: | Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n213: | P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n214: | Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n215: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## 13. RELATED\n220: \n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 232. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.11.0.16\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review quick reference\"\n  - \"review loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"p0 p1 p2 severity ladder\"\n  - \"release readiness verdicts\"\n  - \"review loop troubleshooting\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.11.0.16\n---\n\n# Deep Review Quick Reference\n\nOne-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nUse this quick reference when you need the command shape, artifact names, convergence rules, and synthesis outputs for the autonomous deep-review loop without loading the full protocol references.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Looking up the canonical `/deep:review` invocation without re-reading the full SKILL.md.\n- Confirming default thresholds, verdicts, or release-readiness states at a glance.\n- Refreshing the artifact-name and packet-file checklist before a manual orchestration pass.\n- Triaging a stuck loop and need the fastest path to convergence semantics.\n\n### Commands\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:review:auto \"target\"` | Run autonomous review (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:review:confirm \"target\"` | Run review with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:review \"target\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 7 | Maximum review iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.10 | Base sensitivity for review convergence |\n| `--stop-policy` | convergence | Use `max-iterations` when convergence must not end the run before the iteration ceiling |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `--restart` | off | Archive the current review packet and start a fresh lineage |\n| `--severity-threshold` | P2 | Minimum severity to report |\n\n---\n\n## 2. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Multi-pass code quality audit | `/deep:review` |\n| Simple single-pass code review | `sk-code-review` |\n| Pre-release readiness check | `/deep:review:auto \"spec folder\"` |\n| Spec/implementation alignment check | `/deep:review:auto \"skill sk-name\"` |\n| Deep technical investigation | `/deep:research` (different skill) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```\n/deep:review  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-review agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Review (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings (P0/P1/P2)\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (review-report.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE FILES\n\nReview mode stores its packet under the resolved local review path rooted at `{spec_folder}/review/`:\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Review parameters (immutable) |\n| State | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned finding registry |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n| Dashboard | `review/deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated review dashboard |\n| Iterations | `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings (write-once) |\n| Report | `review/review-report.md` | Markdown | Final 9-section review report |\n| Pause | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Pause between iterations |\n\n### Lifecycle Modes\n\n| Mode | Effect |\n|------|--------|\n| `resume` | Continue the current review lineage without resetting generation |\n| `restart` | Archive current review state and start a new generation |\n| `fork` (deferred) | Reserved. Start a sibling lineage branch with explicit parent linkage. Not runtime-wired. |\n| `completed-continue` (deferred) | Reserved. Snapshot the completed review and reopen it for amendment-only review deltas. Not runtime-wired. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\n| ID | Dimension | Priority | Description |\n|----|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| D1 | Correctness | 1 | Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants |\n| D2 | Security | 2 | Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization |\n| D3 | Traceability | 3 | Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity |\n| D4 | Maintainability | 4 | Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, ease of safe follow-on changes |\n\n---\n\n## 6. REVIEW VERDICTS\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning | Next Command |\n|---------|-----------|---------|--------------|\n| FAIL | Active P0 findings remain OR any binary gate fails | Does not meet quality standards | `/speckit:plan` for remediation |\n| CONDITIONAL | No P0, but active P1 findings remain | Meets threshold but has required fixes | `/speckit:plan` for fixes |\n| PASS | No active P0/P1 findings | Shippable, set `hasAdvisories=true` when P2 findings remain | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Release Readiness\n\n`releaseReadinessState` is the canonical config/report field for review readiness tracking.\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `in-progress` | Review still running or required coverage incomplete |\n| `converged` | All 4 dimensions covered and the stabilization pass found no new P0/P1 findings |\n| `release-blocking` | At least one unresolved P0 remains active |\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW QUALITY GUARDS\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding has file:line evidence and is not inference-only |\n| Scope | Findings and reviewed files stay within declared review scope |\n| Coverage | Configured dimensions plus required traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REVIEW CONVERGENCE\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `0.08` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with `minStabilizationPasses >= 1` |\n\n**Key defaults:** `maxIterations=7`, `convergenceThreshold=0.10`, `rollingStopThreshold=0.08`, `noProgressThreshold=0.05`, `stuckThreshold=2`, `minStabilizationPasses=1`\n\n**P0 override:** Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence.\n\n---\n\n## 9. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-review iteration:\n1. Read `deep-review-state.jsonl`, `deep-review-findings-registry.json`, and `deep-review-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 review actions (Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query + Grep)\n4. Write `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with P0/P1/P2 findings\n5. Run adversarial self-check on any P0 findings (Hunter/Skeptic/Referee)\n6. Update `deep-review-strategy.md` (findings, coverage, next focus)\n7. Append iteration record to `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n\n---\n\n## 10. REVIEW REPORT SECTIONS\n\n| # | Section | Purpose |\n|---|---------|---------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why the verdict routes to planning or changelog follow-up |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence and final severity |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Grouped action lanes derived from active findings |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec delta derived from review results |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Action-ready plan starter for remediation |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol status and unresolved gaps |\n| 8 | Deferred Items | P2 advisories, blocked checks, and follow-up items |\n| 9 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, replay validation, and convergence evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 11. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper review | Lower convergence (0.05), raise max iterations (10) |\n| Forced iteration ceiling | Set `--stop-policy=max-iterations` with the desired `--max-iterations` |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.15), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Focus on security | Specify `--dimensions security,correctness` |\n| Broad coverage | Use all 4 default dimensions and allow the stabilization pass to run |\n\n---\n\n## 12. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.10 to 0.05, or use `--stop-policy=max-iterations` when early convergence is unacceptable |\n| Stuck on one dimension | Check strategy.md \"Next Focus\" rotation |\n| P0 findings blocking convergence | Expected behavior: P0 override prevents premature stop |\n| Review-report missing sections | Verify synthesis phase completed (check state.jsonl for synthesis event) |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n\n---\n\n## 13. RELATED\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":232,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1782998183077,"end":1782998183093}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02701d36d99158ea016a4664a4fef88191aac05a00ee830642"}},"id":"prt_f22f92ca4001rKJtv756QEMppL","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f89885001iInzGWJjhNp1H1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998184873,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers","callID":"call_LP05LaRAByWIxJ8JV1dFapFo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"prompt":"Execute detached deep-review fan-out lineage for spec folder .opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved, artifact_dir .opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/review/lineages/gpt, session_id fanout-gpt-1782998103426-5a2g5w, executor cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.5-fast, maxIterations 10, stopPolicy max-iterations. Write only lineage artifacts and final line FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:gpt.","specFolder":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved","tenantId":"","userId":"","agentId":"","limit":5,"session_id":"","turnNumber":1,"include_cognitive":false},"output":"{\n  \"summary\": \"No matching trigger phrases found\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"count\": 0,\n    \"results\": [],\n    \"matchType\": \"trigger-phrase\",\n    \"degradedMatching\": null,\n    \"triggerSignals\": [],\n    \"cognitive\": null\n  },\n  \"hints\": [\n    \"Ensure memories have trigger phrases defined\",\n    \"Try a different prompt or check memory content\",\n    \"Auto-surface hook: injected 10 constitutional and 5 triggered memories (1597ms)\"\n  ],\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"tool\": \"memory_match_triggers\",\n    \"tokenCount\": 2186,\n    \"latencyMs\": 235,\n    \"cacheHit\": false,\n    \"autoSurface\": {\n      \"constitutionalCount\": 10,\n      \"triggeredCount\": 5,\n      \"surfaced_at\": \"2026-07-02T13:16:24.632Z\",\n      \"latencyMs\": 1597\n    },\n    \"autoSurfacedContext\": {\n      \"constitutional\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": 38292,\n          \"specFolder\": \"system-spec-kit\",\n          \"filePath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/goal-prompting-runtime-specific.md\",\n          \"title\": \"GOAL PROMPTING — Runtime