{"type":"text","timestamp":1782998221456,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22f98d8b001fB0QCjONYrVMs0","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"text","text":"The workflow contract confirms this is the single-lineage path with the fan-out artifact override bound directly. I’m loading the YAML phase details and local protocol assets before creating any lineage files.","time":{"start":1782998207884,"end":1782998221452},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664bfbba481918345910064c84d6a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998221514,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9jWs4NBb27j0ucAkosWCkbSZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":241,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n241:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n242:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n243:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n244:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n245:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n246:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n247:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n248:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n249:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n250: \n251:       step_acquire_lock:\n252:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n253:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n254:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n255:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n256:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n257:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n258:         on_halt:\n259:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n260:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n261:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n262:         on_cancel:\n263:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n264:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n265:         on_workflow_exit:\n266:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n267:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n268: \n269:       step_classify_session:\n270:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n271:         inspect:\n272:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n273:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n274:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n275:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n276:         classify:\n277:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n278:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n279:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n280:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n281:         outputs:\n282:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n283:         lifecycle_routing:\n284:           - \"If lineage_mode == restart and session_state is resume or completed-session, execute on_restart before on_resume or on_completed_session.\"\n285:           - \"If lineage_mode == auto or lineage_mode == resume, preserve the existing resume/completed/fresh behavior.\"\n286:         on_resume:\n287:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n288:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n289:           skip_to: phase_loop\n290:         on_restart:\n291:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n292:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n293:           set:\n294:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n295:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n296:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n297:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n298:           skip_to: step_create_config\n299:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n300:         on_completed_session:\n301:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n302:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n303:         on_invalid_state:\n304:           halt: true\n305:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n306:         on_fresh:\n307:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n308: \n309:       step_scope_discovery:\n310:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n311:         resolve:\n312:           spec-folder: |\n313:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n314:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n315:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n316:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n317:           skill: |\n318:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n319:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n320:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n321:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n322:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n323:           agent: |\n324:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .agents/)\n325:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n326:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n327:           track: |\n328:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n329:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n330:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n331:           files: |\n332:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n333:             2. Validate all files exist\n334:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n335:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n336:         outputs:\n337:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n338:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n339: \n340:       step_order_dimensions:\n341:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n342:         algorithm: |\n343:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n344:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n345:              correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n346:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n347:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n348:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n349:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n350:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n351:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n352:         outputs:\n353:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n354:           - inventory_pass: true\n355: \n356:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n357:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n358:         outputs:\n359:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n360:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n361:         normalize: |\n362:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n363:             - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n364:             - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n365:             - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n366:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n367: \n368:       step_resolve_session_id:\n369:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve timestamp fallback\"\n370:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n371:         if_present:\n372:           bind:\n373:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n374:         if_absent:\n375:           bind:\n376:             session_id_init: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n377: \n378:       step_create_config:\n379:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n380:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n381:         populate:\n382:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n383:           mode: \"review\"\n384:           sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n385:           parentSessionId: null\n386:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n387:           generation: 1\n388:           continuedFromRun: null\n389:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n390:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n391:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n392:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n393:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n394:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n395:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n396:           crossReference:\n397:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n398:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n399:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n400:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n401:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n402:           stopPolicy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n403:           stuckThreshold: 2\n404:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n405:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n406:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n407:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n408:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n409:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n410:           status: \"initialized\"\n411:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n412:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n413:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n414: \n415:       step_create_state_log:\n416:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n417:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n418:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n419:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"stopPolicy\":\"{stop_policy}\",\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n420:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n421: \n422:       step_create_findings_registry:\n423:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n424:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n425:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n426: \n427:       step_create_strategy:\n428:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n429:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n430:         populate:\n431:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n432:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n433:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n434:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n435:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n436:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n437:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n438:           stop_policy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n439:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n440: \n441:       step_seed_coverage_graph:\n442:         action: \"Seed the review coverage graph before the first convergence check\"\n443:         transform: |\n444:           1. Convert review_scope_files into FILE nodes.\n445:           2. Convert review target groupings into coarse SLICE nodes only; do not expand SYMBOL\n446:              or DEPENDENCY nodes in review mode.\n447:           3. Emit COVERS edges from SLICE nodes to FILE nodes when the grouping is known.\n448:           4. Bind coverage_seed_source to \"scope_discovery\" and coverage_seed_confidence to 0.50.\n449:           5. When scope discovery yields no files, emit [] for both arrays; the upsert script\n450:              returns a warning and review continues with an empty graph.\n451:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n452:         outputs:\n453:           - coverage_seed_nodes_json: \"Seed nodes for review SLICE and FILE kinds only\"\n454:           - coverage_seed_edges_json: \"Seed COVERS edges where review target groupings resolved\"\n455:           - coverage_seed_warning: \"Warning emitted when the seed batch inserts zero nodes, else empty\"\n456:         on_warning:\n457:           log: \"Coverage graph seed inserted zero nodes; continuing with an empty graph.\"\n458:           proceed: true\n459: \n460:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n461:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n462:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n463:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n464:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n465: \n466:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n467:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n468:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n469:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n470: \n471:       step_init_complete:\n472:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n473:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n474: \n475:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n476:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n477:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n478:   phase_loop:\n479:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n480:     repeat: true\n481:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n482:     steps:\n483: \n484:       step_read_state:\n485:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n486:         read:\n487:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n488:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n489:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n490:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n491:         extract:\n492:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n493:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n494:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n495:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n496:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n497:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n498:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n499:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n500:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n501:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n502:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n503:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n504:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n505:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n506:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n507:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n508:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n509:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n510:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n511:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n512:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n513:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n514:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n515:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n516:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n517:           - stop_policy: \"Extract stopPolicy from deep-review-config.json, default 'convergence'. Valid values: convergence, max-iterations.\"\n518: \n519:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n520:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n521:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n522:         if_exists:\n523:           set:\n524:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n525:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n526:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n527:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n528:         if_not_exists:\n529:           proceed: true\n530: \n531:       step_graph_convergence:\n532:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n533:         inspect:\n534:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n535:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n536:         transform: |\n537:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n538:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n539:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n540:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n541:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n542:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n543:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n544:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n545:         outputs:\n546:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n547:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n548:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n549:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n550:           - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n551: \n552:       step_check_convergence:\n553:         action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n554:         algorithm: |\n555:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n556:              claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n557:              If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n558:                candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n559:                stop_blocked = true\n560:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n561:                blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n562:                recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n563:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n564:           1. HARD STOPS:\n565:              a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n566:              b) if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: do not allow all-dimensions-clean or composite convergence to stop; treat convergence signals as telemetry, set decision = \"CONTINUE\", and broaden the next review angle.\n567:              c) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n568:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n569:           2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n570:              if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n571:           3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n572:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n573:                Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n574:                If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n575:           4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n576:                signals = []\n577:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n578:                   avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n579:                   stop if avg <= 0.08\n580:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n581:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n582:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n583:                c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n584:                   coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n585:                   stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n586:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n587:                if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n588:                if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: convergence votes are telemetry only; set weighted_stop_score for diagnostics, keep decision = \"CONTINUE\", and choose a broader next focus.\n589:                else if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n590:           5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n591:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n592:                b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n593:                c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n594:                d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n595:                e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n596:                f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n597:                g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n598:                h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n599:                i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n600:              if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n601:                decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n602:                stop_blocked = true\n603:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n604:                blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n605:                blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n606:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n607:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n608:                dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n609:                dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n610:                dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n611:                p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n612:                active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n613:                evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n614:                avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n615:                hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n616:                claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n617:                claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n618:                fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n619:                security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n620:                fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n621:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n622:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n623:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n624:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n625:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n626:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n627:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n628:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n629:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n630:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n631:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n632:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n633:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n634:                     stop_blocked = true\n635:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n636:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n637:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n638:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n639:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n640:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n641:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n642:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n643:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n644:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n645:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n646:                     stop_blocked = false\n647:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n648:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n649:         outputs:\n650:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n651:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n652:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n653:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n654:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n655:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n656:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n657:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n658:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n659:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n660:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n\n(Showing lines 241-660 of 1603. Use offset=661 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        lifecycle_routing:\n          - \"If lineage_mode == restart and session_state is resume or completed-session, execute on_restart before on_resume or on_completed_session.\"\n          - \"If lineage_mode == auto or lineage_mode == resume, preserve the existing resume/completed/fresh behavior.\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve timestamp fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stopPolicy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"stopPolicy\":\"{stop_policy}\",\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{session_id_init}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stop_policy: \"{stop_policy}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_seed_coverage_graph:\n        action: \"Seed the review coverage graph before the first convergence check\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Convert review_scope_files into FILE nodes.\n          2. Convert review target groupings into coarse SLICE nodes only; do not expand SYMBOL\n             or DEPENDENCY nodes in review mode.\n          3. Emit COVERS edges from SLICE nodes to FILE nodes when the grouping is known.\n          4. Bind coverage_seed_source to \"scope_discovery\" and coverage_seed_confidence to 0.50.\n          5. When scope discovery yields no files, emit [] for both arrays; the upsert script\n             returns a warning and review continues with an empty graph.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n        outputs:\n          - coverage_seed_nodes_json: \"Seed nodes for review SLICE and FILE kinds only\"\n          - coverage_seed_edges_json: \"Seed COVERS edges where review target groupings resolved\"\n          - coverage_seed_warning: \"Warning emitted when the seed batch inserts zero nodes, else empty\"\n        on_warning:\n          log: \"Coverage graph seed inserted zero nodes; continuing with an empty graph.\"\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n          - stop_policy: \"Extract stopPolicy from deep-review-config.json, default 'convergence'. Valid values: convergence, max-iterations.\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n          - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n        algorithm: |\n          0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n             claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n             If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n               candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n               recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n               Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n          1. HARD STOPS:\n             a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n             b) if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: do not allow all-dimensions-clean or composite convergence to stop; treat convergence signals as telemetry, set decision = \"CONTINUE\", and broaden the next review angle.\n             c) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n             Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n          2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n             if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n               graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n               Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n               If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n          4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n               signals = []\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n                  stop if avg <= 0.08\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n                  coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n                  stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n               if stop_policy == \"max-iterations\" AND iteration_count < max_iterations: convergence votes are telemetry only; set weighted_stop_score for diagnostics, keep decision = \"CONTINUE\", and choose a broader next focus.\n               else if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n          5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n               a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n               b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n               c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n               d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n               e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n               f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n               g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n               h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n               i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n             if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n               decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n               blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n               convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n               convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n               dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n               dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n               p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n               active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n               evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n               avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n               hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n               fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n               security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n               fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"","lineStart":241,"lineEnd":660,"totalLines":1603,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998221502,"end":1782998221511}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664cd61f081919ae30570b7cf030b"}},"id":"prt_f22f9c28e00130BEu290LinP0W","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998221586,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OtZ2bvVHOtPbu4LFIV1QVPSY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1081,"limit":560},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1081:           | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n1082:           | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n1083: \n1084:           ## Dimension Coverage\n1085:           | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n1086:           |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n1087:           | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n1088: \n1089:           ## Traceability Coverage\n1090:           | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n1091:           |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n1092:           | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n1093: \n1094:           ## Progress\n1095:           | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n1096:           |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n1097:           | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n1098: \n1099:           ## Trend\n1100:           - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n1101:           - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1102:           - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n1103: \n1104:           ## Next Focus\n1105:           {next_dimension}\n1106:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1107:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1108: \n1109:       step_update_tracking:\n1110:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1111:         set:\n1112:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1113:           p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1114:           p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1115:           p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1116:           stuck_count: |\n1117:             if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n1118:             if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n1119:             if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n1120:             else: 0\n1121:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1122: \n1123:       step_loop_decision:\n1124:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1125:         goto: step_read_state\n1126: \n1127:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1128:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1129:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1130:   phase_synthesis:\n1131:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1132:     steps:\n1133: \n1134:       step_fanout_merge:\n1135:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1136:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1137:         command: |\n1138:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1139:             --loop-type review \\\n1140:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1141:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1142:         wait_for_completion: true\n1143:         bind_from_output:\n1144:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1145:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1146:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1147: \n1148:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1149:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1150:         read:\n1151:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1152:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1153:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1154:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1155:         extract:\n1156:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1157:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1158:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1159:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1160:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1161:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1162:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1163:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1164:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1165: \n1166:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1167:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1168:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1169:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1170:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1171:       step_derive_verdict:\n1172:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1173:         algorithm: |\n1174:           if p0_count > 0:\n1175:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1176:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1177:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1178:           else:\n1179:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1180:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1181:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1182:         outputs:\n1183:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1184:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1185:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1186:         contract: |\n1187:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1188:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n1189: \n1190:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1191:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1192:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1193:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1194: \n1195:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1196:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1197:         algorithm: |\n1198:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1199:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1200:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1201:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1202:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1203:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1204:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1205:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1206:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1207:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1208:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1209:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1210:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1211:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1212:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1213:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1214:              - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n1215:              - Determine final severity and status\n1216:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1217:         outputs:\n1218:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1219:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1220:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1221:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1222: \n1223:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1224:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1225:         algorithm: |\n1226:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1227:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1228:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1229:             3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1230:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1231: \n1232:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1233:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1234:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1235:         read:\n1236:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1237:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1238:         write:\n1239:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1240:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1241: \n1242:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1243:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1244:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1245: \n1246:       step_compile_review_report:\n1247:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1248:         instructions: |\n1249:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1250: \n1251:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1252:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1253:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1254:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1255:              - Review scope summary\n1256: \n1257:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1258:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1259:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1260:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1261:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1262: \n1263:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1264:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1265:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1266: \n1267:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1268:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1269: \n1270:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1271:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1272: \n1273:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1274:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1275: \n1276:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1277:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1278:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1279:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1280: \n1281:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1282:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1283:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1284:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1285: \n1286:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1287:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1288: \n1289:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1290:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1291:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1292:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1293:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1294: \n1295:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1296:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1297:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1298: \n1299:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1300:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1301: \n1302:       step_convergence_report:\n1303:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1304:         command: |\n1305:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1306:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1307: \n1308:           const paths = {\n1309:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1310:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n1311:             review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n1312:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1313:           };\n1314: \n1315:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1316:             try {\n1317:               return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n1318:             } catch {\n1319:               return false;\n1320:             }\n1321:           }\n1322: \n1323:           function readJson(filePath) {\n1324:             try {\n1325:               return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n1326:             } catch {\n1327:               return null;\n1328:             }\n1329:           }\n1330: \n1331:           function readJsonl(filePath) {\n1332:             if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n1333:             return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n1334:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1335:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1336:               .filter(Boolean)\n1337:               .flatMap((line) => {\n1338:                 try {\n1339:                   return [JSON.parse(line)];\n1340:                 } catch {\n1341:                   return [];\n1342:                 }\n1343:               });\n1344:           }\n1345: \n1346:           function countIterationFindings(record) {\n1347:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n1348:             const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n1349:             if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n1350:             if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n1351:             return 0;\n1352:           }\n1353: \n1354:           function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n1355:             return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n1356:           }\n1357: \n1358:           function findingKeys(candidate) {\n1359:             if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n1360:               const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n1361:               return key ? [key] : [];\n1362:             }\n1363:             if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n1364:             return [...new Set([\n1365:               candidate.id,\n1366:               candidate.findingId,\n1367:               candidate.title,\n1368:               candidate.summary,\n1369:               candidate.text,\n1370:               candidate.finding,\n1371:               candidate.description,\n1372:             ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n1373:           }\n1374: \n1375:           function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n1376:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n1377:             return record.findingDetails\n1378:               .map(findingKeys)\n1379:               .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n1380:           }\n1381: \n1382:           function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n1383:             return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n1384:               .filter(Array.isArray)\n1385:               .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n1386:               .flatMap(findingKeys);\n1387:           }\n1388: \n1389:           function appendEvent(event) {\n1390:             appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n1391:           }\n1392: \n1393:           const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n1394:           const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n1395:           const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n1396:           const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n1397:           const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n1398:           const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n1399:           const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n1400:           const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n1401:           const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n1402:           const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n1403:           const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n1404:           const missingArtifacts = [\n1405:             ['registry', paths.registry],\n1406:             ['review', paths.review],\n1407:             ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n1408:           ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n1409:           const invariantFailures = [];\n1410:           if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n1411:           if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n1412:           if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n1413:           if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n1414:           if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n1415: \n1416:           if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n1417:             appendEvent({\n1418:               type: 'event',\n1419:               event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n1420:               mode: 'review',\n1421:               severity: 'warning',\n1422:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1423:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1424:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1425:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1426:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1427:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1428:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1429:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1430:               reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n1431:               invariantFailures,\n1432:               missingArtifacts,\n1433:               registryFindingCount,\n1434:               iterationFindingCount,\n1435:               identifiableFindingCount,\n1436:               missingStructuredFindingCount,\n1437:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1438:             });\n1439:           } else {\n1440:             appendEvent({\n1441:               type: 'event',\n1442:               event: 'synthesis_complete',\n1443:               mode: 'review',\n1444:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1445:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1446:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1447:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1448:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1449:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1450:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1451:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1452:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1453:             });\n1454:           }\n1455:           EOF\n1456:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1457: \n1458:       step_update_config_status:\n1459:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1460:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1461:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1462: \n1463:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1464:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1465:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1466:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n1467:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1468: \n1469:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1470:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1471:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1472:   phase_save:\n1473:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1474:     steps:\n1475: \n1476:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1477:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1478:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1479:         requirements:\n1480:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1481:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n1482:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1483:         example_payload: |\n1484:           {\n1485:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1486:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n1487:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n1488:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n1489:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1490:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1491:           }\n1492: \n1493:       step_generate_context:\n1494:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1495:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1496:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1497: \n1498:       step_index_memory:\n1499:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1500:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1501:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1502:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1503: \n1504:       step_verify_save:\n1505:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1506:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1507:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1508: \n1509:       step_release_lock:\n1510:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1511:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1512:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1513: \n1514:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1515:   # COMPLETION\n1516:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1517:   completion:\n1518:     message: |\n1519:       Deep review complete.\n1520:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1521:       Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n1522:       Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n1523: \n1524:       Artifacts:\n1525:         - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1526:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n1527:         - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n1528:         - Memory context saved\n1529: \n1530:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1531:     next_steps:\n1532:       - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n1533:       - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n1534:       - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n1535:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1536: \n1537: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1538: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1539: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1540: error_recovery:\n1541:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1542:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1543:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1544:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n1545: \n1546: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1547: # RULES\n1548: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1549: rules:\n1550:   ALWAYS:\n1551:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1552:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n1553:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1554:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1555:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1556:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1557:     - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n1558:     - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n1559:     - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n1560:   NEVER:\n1561:     - skip_convergence_check\n1562:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1563:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1564:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1565:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1566:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1567:     - modify_files_under_review\n1568:     - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n1569: \n1570: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1571: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1572: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1573: reference_only_appendix:\n1574:   checkpoint_commit:\n1575:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1576:     commands:\n1577:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n1578:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1579:   severity_weights:\n1580:     note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n1581:     weights:\n1582:       P0: 10.0\n1583:       P1: 5.0\n1584:       P2: 1.0\n1585:     p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n1586:     clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n1587:   review_dimensions:\n1588:     note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n1589:     dimensions:\n1590:       - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n1591:       - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n1592:       - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n1593:       - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n1594:   cross_reference_protocols:\n1595:     note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n1596:     core_protocols:\n1597:       - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1598:       - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n1599:     overlay_protocols:\n1600:       - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n1601:       - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".opencode/.agents\" }\n1602:       - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1603:       - { check: \"Playbook vs Support\", source: \"Scenario preconditions\", target: \"actual support\" }\n\n(End of file - total 1603 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n          | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n\n          ## Dimension Coverage\n          | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n          |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n          | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n\n          ## Traceability Coverage\n          | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n          |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n          | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n\n          ## Progress\n          | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n          |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n          | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n          ## Trend\n          - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"          | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n          | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n\n          ## Dimension Coverage\n          | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n          |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n          | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n\n          ## Traceability Coverage\n          | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n          |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n          | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n\n          ## Progress\n          | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n          |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n          | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n          ## Trend\n          - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n          - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n\n          ## Next Focus\n          {next_dimension}\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          stuck_count: |\n            if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n            if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n            if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n            else: 0\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n            review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n            } catch {\n              return false;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJson(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n            } catch {\n              return null;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJsonl(filePath) {\n            if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .flatMap((line) => {\n                try {\n                  return [JSON.parse(line)];\n                } catch {\n                  return [];\n                }\n              });\n          }\n\n          function countIterationFindings(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n            const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n            if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n            if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n            return 0;\n          }\n\n          function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n            return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n          }\n\n          function findingKeys(candidate) {\n            if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n              const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n              return key ? [key] : [];\n            }\n            if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n            return [...new Set([\n              candidate.id,\n              candidate.findingId,\n              candidate.title,\n              candidate.summary,\n              candidate.text,\n              candidate.finding,\n              candidate.description,\n            ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n          }\n\n          function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n            return record.findingDetails\n              .map(findingKeys)\n              .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n          }\n\n          function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n            return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n              .filter(Array.isArray)\n              .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n              .flatMap(findingKeys);\n          }\n\n          function appendEvent(event) {\n            appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n          }\n\n          const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n          const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n          const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n          const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n          const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n          const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n          const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n          const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n          const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n          const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n          const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n          const missingArtifacts = [\n            ['registry', paths.registry],\n            ['review', paths.review],\n            ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n          ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,\n              registryFindingCount,\n              iterationFindingCount,\n              identifiableFindingCount,\n              missingStructuredFindingCount,\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          } else {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_complete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          }\n          EOF\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep review complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n      Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n        - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n      - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n      - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n    - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n    - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n    - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n    - modify_files_under_review\n    - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  severity_weights:\n    note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n    weights:\n      P0: 10.0\n      P1: 5.0\n      P2: 1.0\n    p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n    clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n  review_dimensions:\n    note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n    dimensions:\n      - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n      - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n      - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n      - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n  cross_reference_protocols:\n    note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n    core_protocols:\n      - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n    overlay_protocols:\n      - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n      - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".opencode/.agents\" }\n      - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Playbook vs Support\", source: \"Scenario preconditions\", target: \"actual support\" }","lineStart":1081,"lineEnd":1603,"totalLines":1603,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998221550,"end":1782998221581}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664cd62148191bcd741db3cbe4c4c"}},"id":"prt_f22f9c2ea001etsLGMHBLqqFkP","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998221587,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wXXw8CaGQcW7GxSD6tAnA2EH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":661,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n661:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n662:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n663:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n664:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n665:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n666:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n667:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n668:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n669:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n670:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n671:           - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n672:           - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n673:           - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n674:           - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n675:           - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n676:           - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n677:           - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n678:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n679:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n680:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n681:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n682:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n683: \n684:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n685:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n686:         if_blocked:\n687:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n688:           log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n689:         if_not_blocked:\n690:           proceed: true\n691: \n692:       step_handle_convergence:\n693:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n694:         if_stop:\n695:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n696:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n697:         if_blocked:\n698:           log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n699:         if_stuck_recovery:\n700:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n701:           recovery_strategies:\n702:             - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n703:             - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n704:             - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n705:           pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n706:           set:\n707:             next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n708:             pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n709:             pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n710:             pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n711:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n712:         if_continue:\n713:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n714: \n715:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n716:         action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n717:         if_pending_pause_event:\n718:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n719:           message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n720:           reset:\n721:             pending_stop_event: null\n722:             pending_stop_reason: null\n723:             pending_stop_detail: null\n724:           halt: true\n725:         if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n726:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n727:           reset:\n728:             pending_stop_event: null\n729:             pending_stop_reason: null\n730:             pending_stop_detail: null\n731:         if_no_pending_event:\n732:           proceed: true\n733: \n734:       step_generate_state_summary:\n735:         action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n736:         generate: |\n737:           STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n738:           Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n739:           Dimension: {next_dimension}\n740:           Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n741:           Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n742:           Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n743:           {resource_map_prompt_line}\n744:           Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n745:           Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n746:           Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n747:           Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n748: \n749:       step_marker_scan:\n750:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n751:         algorithm: |\n752:           if current_iteration > 1:\n753:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n754:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n755:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n756:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n757:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n758:                 halt with exit code 2\n759:         note: |\n760:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n761:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n762:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n763:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n764: \n765:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n766:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n767:         resolve_executor:\n768:           source: \"config.executor\"\n769:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n770:         pre_dispatch:\n771:           generate_summary: |\n772:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n773:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n774:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n775:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n776:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n777:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n778:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n779:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n780:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n781:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n782:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n783:           render_prompt_pack:\n784:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n785:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n786:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n787:             variables:\n788:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n789:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n790:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n791:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n792:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n793:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n794:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n795:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n796:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n797:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n798:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n799:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n800:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n801:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n802:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n803:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n804:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n805:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n806:           args:\n807:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n808:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n809:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n810:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n811:         if_native:\n812:           dispatch:\n813:             agent: deep-review\n814:             model: opus\n815:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n816:           wait_for_completion: true\n817:         if_cli_copilot:\n818:           command: |\n819:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n820:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n821:             import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n822: \n823:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n824: \n825:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n826:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n827: \n828:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n829:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n830:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n831:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n832:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n833:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n834:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n835:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n836:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n837: \n838:             const baseArgs = [\n839:               '-p',\n840:               prompt,\n841:               '--model',\n842:               '{config.executor.model}',\n843:               '--allow-all-tools',\n844:               '--no-ask-user',\n845:             ];\n846: \n847:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n848:               promptPath,\n849:               prompt,\n850:               targetAuthority,\n851:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n852:             });\n853: \n854:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n855:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n856:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n857:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n858:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n859:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n860:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n861:             }\n862: \n863:             const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n864:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n865:               stdio: 'inherit',\n866:               timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n867:             });\n868:             process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n869:             EOF\n870:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n871:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n872:           wait_for_completion: true\n873:           notes:\n874:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n875:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n876:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n877:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n878:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n879:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n880:         if_cli_claude_code:\n881:           command: |\n882:             if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n883:             claude \\\n884:               -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n885:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n886:               --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n887:               --output-format text \\\n888:               {optional_effort_flag}\n889:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n890:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n891:           wait_for_completion: true\n892:           render_hint:\n893:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n894:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n895:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n896:             optional_effort_flag: |\n897:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n898:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n899:           notes:\n900:             - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n901:             - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n902:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n903:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n904:         if_cli_opencode:\n905:           command: |\n906:             opencode run \\\n907:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n908:               --format json \\\n909:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n910:               --pure \\\n911:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n912:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n913:               \"$(printf '%s\\n\\n' 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'; cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n914:               </dev/null\n915:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n916:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n917:           wait_for_completion: true\n918:           render_hint:\n919:             optional_variant_flag: |\n920:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n921:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n922:           notes:\n923:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n924:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n925:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n926:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n927:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n928:         post_dispatch_validate:\n929:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n930:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n931:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n932:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n933:           route_proof:\n934:             mode: review\n935:             target_agent: deep-review\n936:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n937:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n938:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n939:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n940:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n941:           failure_reasons:\n942:             - iteration_file_missing\n943:             - iteration_file_empty\n944:             - jsonl_not_appended\n945:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n946:             - jsonl_parse_error\n947:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n948:             - delta_file_missing\n949:             - delta_file_empty\n950:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n951:             - executor_missing\n952:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n953:             - v2_missing_ledger\n954:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n955:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n956:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n957:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n958:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n959:             - route_proof_missing\n960:             - route_proof_mismatch\n961:           warning_surface:\n962:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n963:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n964:             severity: \"advisory\"\n965:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n966:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n967:           on_failure:\n968:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n969:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n970:         record_executor_audit:\n971:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n972:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n973:           field: \"executor\"\n974:           value:\n975:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n976:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n977:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n978:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n979: \n980:       step_evaluate_results:\n981:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n982:         verify:\n983:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n984:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n985:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n986:         extract:\n987:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n988:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n989:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n990:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n991:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n992:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n993:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n994:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n995:         on_missing_outputs:\n996:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n997:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n998:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n999:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n1000: \n1001:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n1002:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n1003:         verify:\n1004:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n1005:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n1006:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n1007:         on_pass:\n1008:           set:\n1009:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n1010:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1011:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1012:         on_fail:\n1013:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1014:           set:\n1015:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1016:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1017:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1018: \n1019:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1020:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1021:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1022:         read:\n1023:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1024:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1025:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1026:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1027:         write:\n1028:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1029:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1030:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1031:         failure_modes:\n1032:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1033:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1034:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1035:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1036:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1037: \n1038:       step_graph_upsert:\n1039:         action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n1040:         read:\n1041:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1042:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1043:         transform: |\n1044:           1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n1045:           2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n1046:           3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n1047:           4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n1048:           5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n1049:           6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n1050:           7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n1051:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n1052:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n1053:         outputs:\n1054:           - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n1055:           - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n1056:         skip_conditions:\n1057:           - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n1058: \n1059:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1060:         action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n1061:         read:\n1062:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1063:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1064:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1065:         content: |\n1066:           # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n1067: \n1068:           Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n1069: \n1070:           ## Status\n1071:           - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n1072:           - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n1073:           - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1074:           - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n1075:           - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n1076: \n1077:           ## Findings Summary\n1078:           | Severity | Count | Trend |\n1079:           |----------|------:|-------|\n1080:           | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n\n(Showing lines 661-1080 of 1603. Use offset=1081 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n          pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n          set:\n            next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n            pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n        if_pending_pause_event:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n          halt: true\n        if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n        if_no_pending_event:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_generate_state_summary:\n        action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n        generate: |\n          STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n          Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          Dimension: {next_dimension}\n          Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n          Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n          Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n          {resource_map_prompt_line}\n          Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n          Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n          Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              stdio: 'inherit',\n              timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n            });\n            process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n            claude \\\n              -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n              --output-format text \\\n              {optional_effort_flag}\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n            optional_effort_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n            - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(printf '%s\\n\\n' 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'; cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded, resolved_route]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: review\n            target_agent: deep-review\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n            - route_proof_missing\n            - route_proof_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n          3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n          5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n        skip_conditions:\n          - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        content: |\n          # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n          Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n\n          ## Status\n          - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n          - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n          - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n          - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n\n          ## Findings Summary\n          | Severity | Count | Trend |\n          |----------|------:|-------|\n          | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |","lineStart":661,"lineEnd":1080,"totalLines":1603,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998221544,"end":1782998221584}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664cd62088191bb4e762351fd2cfc"}},"id":"prt_f22f9c2c10013FfgEfrBwHBber","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998221592,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vCvUdp7XOXAw7Gy7KTwgF3ar","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review State Format\n3: description: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state format\"\n6:   - \"deep review config schema\"\n7:   - \"review severity weights\"\n8:   - \"file protection levels\"\n9:   - \"review iteration file structure\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.28\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review State Format\n16: \n17: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: The deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n24: \n25: | File | Format | Mutability |\n26: |------|--------|------------|\n27: | `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n28: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n29: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n30: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n31: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n32: | `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n33: | `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n35: \n36: ```text\n37: {artifact_dir}/\n38:   deep-review-config.json\n39:   deep-review-state.jsonl\n40:   deep-review-findings-registry.json\n41:   deep-review-strategy.md\n42:   deep-review-dashboard.md\n43:   .deep-review-pause\n44:   review-report.md\n45:   iterations/\n46:     iteration-001.md\n47:     iteration-002.md\n48:     ...\n49: ```\n50: \n51: `{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n52: \n53: ### When to Use\n54: \n55: - Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n56: - Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n57: - Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n58: - Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n63: \n64: Created during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n65: \n66: ```json\n67: {\n68:   \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n69:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n70:   \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n71:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n72:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n73:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n74:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n75:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n76:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n77:   \"generation\": 1,\n78:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n79:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n80:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n81:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n82:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n83:   \"crossReference\": {\n84:     \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n85:     \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n86:   },\n87:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n88:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n89:   \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n90:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n91:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n92:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n93:   \"fileProtection\": {\n94:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n95:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n96:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n97:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n98:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n99:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n100:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n101:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n102:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n103:   },\n104:   \"reducer\": {\n105:     \"enabled\": true,\n106:     \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n107:     \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n108:     \"metrics\": [\n109:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n110:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n111:       \"openFindings\",\n112:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n113:       \"convergenceScore\"\n114:     ]\n115:   }\n116: }\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### Field Reference\n120: \n121: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n122: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n123: | mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n124: | reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n125: | reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n126: | reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n127: | resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n128: | sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n129: | parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n130: | lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n131: | generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n132: | continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n133: | maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n134: | convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n135: | stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n136: | severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n137: | crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n138: | qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n139: | specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n140: | status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n141: | releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n142: | fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n143: | reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n144: \n145: ### File Protection Levels\n146: \n147: | Level | Meaning |\n148: |-------|---------|\n149: | immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n150: | append-only | New content added at end only |\n151: | mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n152: | write-once | Created once, never modified |\n153: | auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n154: | operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n155: \n156: ### Review Dimensions\n157: \n158: | Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n159: |-----------|----------|---------------------|\n160: | correctness | 1 | Yes |\n161: | security | 2 | Yes |\n162: | traceability | 3 | Yes |\n163: | maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n164: \n165: ### Severity Weights\n166: \n167: | Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n168: |----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n169: | P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n170: | P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n171: | P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## 3. STATE LOG\n176: \n177: The `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n182: \n183: Updated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n184: \n185: ### Required Sections\n186: \n187: | Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n188: |---------|-----------|---------|\n189: | topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n190: | review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n191: | completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n192: | running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n193: | what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n194: | what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n195: | exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n196: | ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n197: | next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n198: | known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n199: | cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n200: | files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n201: | review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n202: \n203: ### Mapping from Research Mode\n204: \n205: | Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n206: |---------------|-------------------|\n207: | review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n208: | completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n209: | running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n210: | cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n211: | files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n212: | review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n213: \n214: Sections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n215: \n216: ### Update Protocol\n217: \n218: 1. Read current strategy file\n219: 2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n220: 3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n221: 4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n222: 5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n223: 6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n228: \n229: Reducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n230: \n231: ```json\n232: {\n233:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n234:   \"generation\": 1,\n235:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n236:   \"openFindings\": [],\n237:   \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n238:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n239:   \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n240:   \"severityChanged\": [],\n241:   \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n242:   \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n243:     \"correctness\": true,\n244:     \"security\": true,\n245:     \"traceability\": false,\n246:     \"maintainability\": false\n247:   },\n248:   \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n249:     \"P0\": 0,\n250:     \"P1\": 1,\n251:     \"P2\": 2\n252:   },\n253:   \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n254:   \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n255:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n256:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n257:   \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n258:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n259:   \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n260: }\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 544. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.28\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review State Format\ndescription: State file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop, config, JSONL log, strategy, iteration files, and review report.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state format\"\n  - \"deep review config schema\"\n  - \"review severity weights\"\n  - \"file protection levels\"\n  - \"review iteration file structure\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.28\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Format\n\nState file schemas for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep review loop uses 8 state files under the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` owned by the target spec:\n\n| File | Format | Mutability |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | JSON | Immutable after init |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | JSON Lines | Append-only |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | JSON | Auto-generated reducer state |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Markdown | Updated each iteration |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Auto-generated (read-only) |\n| `.deep-review-pause` | Sentinel | Created/deleted by user |\n| `review-report.md` | Markdown | Updated at synthesis |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Write-once |\n\n```text\n{artifact_dir}/\n  deep-review-config.json\n  deep-review-state.jsonl\n  deep-review-findings-registry.json\n  deep-review-strategy.md\n  deep-review-dashboard.md\n  .deep-review-pause\n  review-report.md\n  iterations/\n    iteration-001.md\n    iteration-002.md\n    ...\n```\n\n`{artifact_dir}` comes from `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review')`. Root-spec runs resolve directly to `{spec_folder}/review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase runs use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `review/` resolves directly to `{spec_folder}/review/` (no `pt-NN` wrapper). A `pt-NN` packet is allocated only when prior content for a non-matching target already exists. Continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact (or matching `pt-NN` packet).\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Validating deep-review state files emitted by an iteration or by the reducer.\n- Implementing a state consumer (e.g. dashboard, advisor probe, downstream packet).\n- Debugging JSONL reducer output or auditing schema-version transitions.\n- Authoring fixtures that need to round-trip through the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG FILE (deep-review-config.json)\n\nCreated during initialization. Not modified after creation.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"topic\": \"Review of deep-review skill package\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"specs/030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\", \"maintainability\"],\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"],\n    \"overlay\": [\"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"specFolder\": \"030-deep-review-review-mode\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\"latestJSONLDelta\", \"newIterationFile\", \"priorReducedState\"],\n    \"outputs\": [\"findingsRegistry\", \"dashboardMetrics\", \"strategyUpdates\"],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Field Reference\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| mode | `\"review\"` | -- | Session mode discriminator (required) |\n| reviewTarget | string | -- | Path or identifier of the review target |\n| reviewTargetType | string | `\"spec-folder\"` | `spec-folder`, `skill`, `agent`, `track`, `files` |\n| reviewDimensions | string[] | all 4 | Dimensions to evaluate |\n| resource_map_present | boolean | false | True only when `{specFolder}/resource-map.md` existed during init, enables the Resource Map Coverage audit pass and conditional report section |\n| sessionId | string | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\n| parentSessionId | string \\| null | `null` | Parent lineage reference for restart flows |\n| lineageMode | string | `\"new\"` | `new`, `resume`, `restart`. `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not emitted by the current runtime |\n| generation | number | 1 | Lineage generation number, incremented on `restart`, unchanged on `resume` |\n| continuedFromRun | number \\| null | `null` | Count of completed iteration records at the lifecycle boundary (set on `resume` and `restart`) |\n| maxIterations | number | 7 | Hard cap on loop iterations |\n| convergenceThreshold | number | 0.10 | Stop when severity-weighted new findings ratio below this |\n| stuckThreshold | number | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| severityThreshold | string | `\"P2\"` | Minimum severity to report: `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| crossReference | object | -- | Core (hard-gated) and overlay (advisory) protocol sets |\n| qualityGateThreshold | boolean | true | Whether binary quality gates are enforced |\n| specFolder | string | -- | Spec folder path (relative to specs/) |\n| status | string | `\"initialized\"` | `initialized`, `running`, `converged`, `stuck`, `complete`, `error` |\n| releaseReadinessState | string | `\"in-progress\"` | `in-progress`, `converged`, `release-blocking` |\n| fileProtection | object | -- | Mutability declarations (see protection levels below) |\n| reducer | object | -- | Canonical reducer inputs, outputs, and metrics names |\n\n### File Protection Levels\n\n| Level | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| immutable | Cannot be modified after creation |\n| append-only | New content added at end only |\n| mutable | Can be read, edited, overwritten |\n| write-once | Created once, never modified |\n| auto-generated | System-managed, overwritten each refresh |\n| operator-controlled | Created or deleted only by the human/operator to control loop state |\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Priority | Required for Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|---------------------|\n| correctness | 1 | Yes |\n| security | 2 | Yes |\n| traceability | 3 | Yes |\n| maintainability | 4 | Yes |\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Label | Requires file:line |\n|----------|--------|-------|--------------------|\n| P0 | 10.0 | Blocker | Yes |\n| P1 | 5.0 | Required | Yes |\n| P2 | 1.0 | Suggestion | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## 3. STATE LOG\n\nThe `deep-review-state.jsonl` record schemas (config, iteration, event, lineage) and the Review Depth Schema (v2) live in `state_jsonl.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRATEGY FILE (deep-review-strategy.md)\n\nUpdated at the end of each iteration. Serves as the persistent brain across fresh-context iterations.\n\n### Required Sections\n\n| Section | Updated By | Purpose |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| topic | Init only | Review topic from config |\n| review-dimensions | Each iteration | Unchecked dimensions drive next focus |\n| completed-dimensions | Each iteration | Checked dimensions with verdict summary |\n| running-findings | Each iteration | P0/P1/P2 active counts + deltas |\n| what-worked | Each iteration | Successful approaches for reuse |\n| what-failed | Each iteration | Failed approaches to avoid |\n| exhausted-approaches | When fully tried | \"Do not retry\" registry |\n| ruled-out-directions | Each iteration | Eliminated directions with reasons |\n| next-focus | Each iteration | Recommended direction for next iteration |\n| known-context | Init only | Prior work from memory context |\n| cross-reference-status | Each iteration | Core vs overlay protocol status |\n| files-under-review | Each iteration | Per-file coverage state table |\n| review-boundaries | Init only | Max iterations, thresholds, config |\n\n### Mapping from Research Mode\n\n| Review Section | Research Equivalent |\n|---------------|-------------------|\n| review-dimensions | Key Questions (remaining) |\n| completed-dimensions | Answered Questions |\n| running-findings | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| cross-reference-status | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| files-under-review | _(none, review-specific)_ |\n| review-boundaries | Research Boundaries |\n\nSections unchanged from research: topic, what-worked, what-failed, exhausted-approaches, ruled-out-directions, next-focus, known-context.\n\n### Update Protocol\n\n1. Read current strategy file\n2. Move completed dimensions from \"remaining\" to \"completed\" with `[x]` and verdict\n3. Update running-findings with P0/P1/P2 counts and deltas\n4. Add to what-worked / what-failed with iteration number\n5. Move exhausted approaches. Update cross-reference-status and files-under-review\n6. Set next-focus based on remaining dimensions and open findings\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINDINGS REGISTRY (deep-review-findings-registry.json)\n\nReducer-owned JSON document regenerated after every iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-04-03T12-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"openFindings\": [],\n  \"resolvedFindings\": [],\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"persistentSameSeverity\": [],\n  \"severityChanged\": [],\n  \"repeatedFindings\": [],\n  \"dimensionCoverage\": {\n    \"correctness\": true,\n    \"security\": true,\n    \"traceability\": false,\n    \"maintainability\": false\n  },\n  \"findingsBySeverity\": {\n    \"P0\": 0,\n    \"P1\": 1,\n    \"P2\": 2\n  },\n  \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n  \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n  \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":544,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1782998221561,"end":1782998221589}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664cd6228819193d752ae40159df8"}},"id":"prt_f22f9c2f60010Cz9YsmGxEzueX","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998221592,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_nygHN4zd5s9CX05aqxX1tWb7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.11.0.3\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Outputs\n15: \n16: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n27: \n28: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n29: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n30: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n31: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n32: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n33: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n34: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n35: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n36: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n37: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n42: \n43: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n44: \n45: ```text\n46: Review verdict: PASS\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ```text\n50: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ```text\n54: Review verdict: FAIL\n55: ```\n56: \n57: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n62: \n63: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n64: \n65: - Current iteration and next focus.\n66: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n67: - Dimension coverage.\n68: - Convergence trend.\n69: - Gate blockers.\n70: - Provisional verdict.\n71: \n72: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n77: \n78: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n79: \n80: - Executive summary.\n81: - Planning trigger.\n82: - Active finding registry.\n83: - Remediation workstreams.\n84: - Spec seed.\n85: - Plan seed.\n86: - Traceability status.\n87: - Deferred items.\n88: - Audit appendix.\n89: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n94: \n95: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n96: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n97: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1782998221565,"end":1782998221591}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664cd623081919cf1e76b662b5eb0"}},"id":"prt_f22f9c2fa001y9k7p0jDsQGqHj","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998221600,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FVNilRndPY9rMKX36tndSAuQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Loop Protocol\n3: description: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"review loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"review auto resume\"\n9:   - \"review synthesis phase\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.11.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Review Loop Protocol\n16: \n17: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: The deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n30: - Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n31: - Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n32: - Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n36: │  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n37: │              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n38: │ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n39: │ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n40: │ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n41: │ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n42: │ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n43: │ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n44: │ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n45: │              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n46: │              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n47: │              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n48: │              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n49: │              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n50: │              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n51: └──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### Core Innovation\n55: \n56: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n57: \n58: ### Key References\n59: \n60: | Resource | Path | Purpose |\n61: |----------|------|---------|\n62: | Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n63: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n64: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n65: | Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n66: | Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n71: \n72: ### Purpose\n73: \n74: Set up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n75: \n76: ### Steps\n77: \n78: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n79:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n80:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n81:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n82:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n83: \n84: 2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n85: \n86: 3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n87: \n88:    | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n89:    |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n90:    | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n91:    | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n92:    | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n93:    | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n94:    | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n95: \n96:    Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n97: \n98: 4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n99: \n100:    | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n101:    |----------|-----------|-----------|\n102:    | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n103:    | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n104:    | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n105:    | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n106: \n107:    Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n108: \n109: 5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n110: \n111:    | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n112:    |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n113:    | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n114:    | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n115:    | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n116:    | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n117:    | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n118:    | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n119: \n120:    Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n121: \n122: 6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n123: \n124: 7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n125: \n126: 8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n127: \n128: 9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n129:    - Topic (review target description)\n130:    - Review Dimensions checklist\n131:    - Files Under Review table\n132:    - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n133:    - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n134:    - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n135:    - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n136:    - Review Boundaries from config\n137: 9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n138:    - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n139:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n140: \n141: 10. **Validate review charter**:\n142:    - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n143:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n144:    - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n145: \n146: 11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n147: \n148: ### Outputs\n149: \n150: | File | Location | Purpose |\n151: |------|----------|---------|\n152: | Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n153: | State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n154: | Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n155: | Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n160: \n161: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n162: \n163: #### Step 1: Read State\n164: \n165: - Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n166: - Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n167: - Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n168: \n169: Reducer contract for every loop refresh:\n170: \n171: | Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n172: |--------------|-----------------|-------|\n173: | Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n174: | Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n175: | Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n176: \n177: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n178: \n179: Run `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n180: \n181: - Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n182: - Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n183: - Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n184:   - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n185:   - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n186:   - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n187:   - Required traceability protocols are covered\n188:   - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n189: - Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n190: \n191: If convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n192: \n193: - `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n194: - `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n195: - `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n196: \n197: The blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n198: \n199: Convergence signals and weights:\n200: \n201: | Signal | Weight | Description |\n202: |--------|--------|-------------|\n203: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n204: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n205: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n206: \n207: **P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n208: \n209: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n210: \n211: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n212: \n213: 1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n214: 2. If present:\n215:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n216:    - Halt the loop with message:\n217:      ```\n218:      Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n219:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n220:      ```\n221:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n222: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n223:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n224:    - Continue from step_read_state\n225: \n226: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n227: \n228: Normalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n229: \n230: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n231: \n232: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n233: \n234: ```\n235: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\n236: Iteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\n237: Target: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\n238: Dimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\n239: Findings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\n240: Traceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\n241: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n242: Provisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\n243: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n244: ```\n245: \n246: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n247: \n248: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n249: \n250: Dispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n251: \n252: ```\n253: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n254: \n255: Review Target: {config.reviewTarget}\n256: Review Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\n257: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n258: Focus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\n259: Focus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\n260: Remaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 765. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.29\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Loop Protocol\ndescription: Complete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop, initialization, iteration, convergence, synthesis, and save phases.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review loop protocol\"\n  - \"review iteration lifecycle\"\n  - \"review loop initialization\"\n  - \"review auto resume\"\n  - \"review synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.29\n---\n\n# Deep Review Loop Protocol\n\nComplete lifecycle specification for the autonomous deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe deep review loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save. The YAML workflow manages the lifecycle. The `@deep-review` agent (LEAF-only, no WebFetch) executes individual review iterations with fresh context each time.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Initiating a deep-review loop on a spec folder, skill, agent, or track.\n- Resuming a paused or interrupted review session from prior state.\n- Validating the 4-phase lifecycle and lineage protocol against current behavior.\n- Auditing iteration-dispatch, convergence, or save-phase contracts before changes.\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT        │────>│  LOOP                         │────>│  SYNTHESIS    │────>│  SAVE    │\n│              │     │  ┌─────────────────────────┐  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Scope        │     │  │ Read State              │  │     │ Finding       │     │ Memory   │\n│ Discovery    │     │  │ Check Convergence       │  │     │ Registry      │     │ Context  │\n│ Dimension    │     │  │ Check Pause Sentinel    │  │     │ Dedup         │     │ Save     │\n│ Ordering     │     │  │ Generate State Summary  │  │     │               │     │          │\n│ Traceability │     │  │ Dispatch @deep-review   │  │     │ Severity      │     │          │\n│ Planning     │     │  │ Evaluate Results        │  │     │ Reconcile     │     │          │\n│ State Files  │     │  │ Claim Adjudication      │  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Dashboard Generation    │  │     │ Replay        │     │          │\n│              │     │  │ Loop Decision           │  │     │ Validation    │     │          │\n│              │     │  └────────┬────────────────┘  │     │               │     │          │\n│              │     │           │ repeat            │     │ review-report │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │ (9 core +     │     │          │\n│              │     │           │                   │     │  resource-map)│     │          │\n└──────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Innovation\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files on disk, not in-context memory. This eliminates context degradation in long review sessions where accumulated findings would otherwise bias subsequent dimensions.\n\n### Key References\n\n| Resource | Path | Purpose |\n|----------|------|---------|\n| Review contract | `assets/review_mode_contract.yaml` | Dimensions, verdicts, gates, protocols |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Unattended review loop |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Step-by-step review with approval gates |\n| Agent | `@deep-review` (LEAF) | Single iteration executor, no sub-agents, no WebFetch |\n| Memory save | `generate-context.js` | Context preservation script |\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\n\nSet up all state files for a new review session. Discover the scope, order dimensions by risk priority, establish the traceability protocol plan, and create the review state packet.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n\n2. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'review').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n\n3. **Scope discovery**: Resolve the review target into a concrete file list using one of 5 target types:\n\n   | Target Type | CLI Value | Resolution Strategy |\n   |-------------|-----------|---------------------|\n   | **Spec Folder** | `spec-folder` | Read `spec.md`, `plan.md`, implementation files listed in `tasks.md` |\n   | **Skill** | `skill` | Read `SKILL.md`, `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, find agent definitions and command entry points |\n   | **Agent** | `agent` | Find agent definitions across all runtimes, compare for consistency |\n   | **Track** | `track` | List all child spec folders under the track, read `spec.md` + `checklist.md` for each |\n   | **Files** | `files` | Expand glob patterns, validate existence, discover cross-references |\n\n   Store the resolved file list in strategy.md \"Files Under Review\".\n\n4. **Dimension ordering**: Order the 4 review dimensions for iteration based on risk priority:\n\n   | Priority | Dimension | Rationale |\n   |----------|-----------|-----------|\n   | 1 | Correctness | Logic errors have the highest blast radius |\n   | 2 | Security | Vulnerabilities require immediate attention |\n   | 3 | Traceability | Spec/code alignment ensures completeness |\n   | 4 | Maintainability | Patterns and documentation quality (lowest immediate risk) |\n\n   Default order: D1 Correctness, D2 Security, D3 Traceability, D4 Maintainability. This order is configurable but the default prioritizes highest-impact dimensions first.\n\n5. **Traceability protocol planning**: Partition the 6 cross-reference protocols into core vs overlay, and schedule only applicable overlays for the target type:\n\n   | Level | Protocol | Applies To | Gate Class | Purpose |\n   |-------|----------|------------|------------|---------|\n   | Core | `spec_code` | all targets | hard | Verify normative claims resolve to shipped behavior |\n   | Core | `checklist_evidence` | all targets | hard | Verify checked completion claims have evidence |\n   | Overlay | `skill_agent` | skill | advisory | Verify SKILL.md and runtime agents agree |\n   | Overlay | `agent_cross_runtime` | agent | advisory | Verify runtime agent parity |\n   | Overlay | `feature_catalog_code` | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory | Verify catalog claims match capability |\n   | Overlay | `playbook_capability` | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory | Verify playbook scenarios match executable reality |\n\n   Only schedule overlay protocols that apply to the resolved target type.\n\n6. **Write config**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` with `mode: \"review\"`, lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`), and review-specific fields including target, target type, dimensions, protocol plan, and release-readiness state.\n\n7. **Initialize state log**: First line of `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` with config record including `mode: \"review\"` and the lineage fields.\n\n8. **Initialize reducer state**: Create `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` with empty `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `repeatedFindings`, `dimensionCoverage`, `findingsBySeverity`, and `convergenceScore`.\n\n9. **Initialize strategy**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` from review template with:\n   - Topic (review target description)\n   - Review Dimensions checklist\n   - Files Under Review table\n   - Cross-Reference Status table grouped by core vs overlay\n   - Known Context from `memory_context()` results (if any)\n   - Resource-map snapshot when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init\n   - `resource-map.md not present. Skipping coverage gate` when it does not\n   - Review Boundaries from config\n9a. **Initialize resource-map coverage state**:\n   - If `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init: set `resource_map_present = true`, add `Resource Map Coverage` to the Review Charter, and persist a concise map summary in `Known Context`\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false`, record the skip note in `Known Context`, and continue without failing\n\n10. **Validate review charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains Non-Goals and Stop Conditions sections (may be empty but must exist)\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (target, dimensions, scope, non-goals) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept automatically and continue\n\n11. **Resume only if config, JSONL, strategy, and findings registry agree**. Otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing.\n\n### Outputs\n\n| File | Location | Purpose |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| Config | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json` | Review parameters (immutable after init) |\n| State | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Iteration log (1 initial line) |\n| Registry | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer-owned findings state |\n| Strategy | `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` | Dimensions, findings, next focus |\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n\n- Read `deep-review-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, extract `newFindingsRatio`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `traceabilityChecks`, and lineage data\n- Read `deep-review-findings-registry.json` -- extract `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, and `convergenceScore`\n- Read `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` -- get next focus dimension/files, remaining dimensions, and protocol gaps\n\nReducer contract for every loop refresh:\n\n| Reducer Part | Canonical Value | Notes |\n|--------------|-----------------|-------|\n| Inputs | `fullJSONLHistory`, `iterationFiles`, `priorReducedState` | Normal loop refresh is full-history: replay the persisted JSONL state and current iteration corpus each refresh so reducer output stays deterministic across restart, compaction, and synthesis audit paths. |\n| Outputs | `findingsRegistry`, `dashboardMetrics`, `strategyUpdates` | The same refresh pass updates the canonical registry, refreshes dashboard metrics, and applies strategy updates. |\n| Metrics | `dimensionsCovered`, `findingsBySeverity`, `openFindings`, `resolvedFindings`, `convergenceScore` | These metrics drive convergence decisions, dashboard summaries, and synthesis readiness. |\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\n\nRun `shouldContinue_review()` (see `../deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md` Section 10.3):\n\n- Max iterations reached? `STOP`\n- Stuck count `>= 2` using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`? `STUCK_RECOVERY`\n- Composite convergence votes `STOP` only after:\n  - Rolling average uses `rollingStopThreshold = 0.08`\n  - Dimension coverage reaches 100% across the 4-dimension model\n  - Coverage has aged through `minStabilizationPasses >= 1`\n  - Required traceability protocols are covered\n  - Evidence, scope, and coverage gates pass\n- Otherwise: `CONTINUE`\n\nIf convergence math or a hard-stop candidate points to STOP, the workflow must run the review legal-stop decision tree before actually stopping. That decision tree records nine review-specific gates: `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate` (see `../convergence/convergence.md` §Section-1 blocked_stop event example for the authoritative shape). The Step 4a claim-adjudication path treats `claimAdjudicationGate` as a hard STOP gate, so the count covers both the convergence decision tree and the adjudication enforcement path. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. If any gate fails, the loop does **not** stop. Instead it emits a first-class `blocked_stop` JSONL event with:\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of the failed review gate names\n- `gateResults`: per-gate pass/fail payloads using the review gate names above\n- `recoveryStrategy`: one-line hint describing the next review action\n\nThe blocked-stop event is append-only evidence that legal-stop blocked the run. The loop then continues with the recovery or next-focus path rather than synthesizing.\n\nConvergence signals and weights:\n\n| Signal | Weight | Description |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | Last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values average below `rollingStopThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | Latest ratio within noise floor derived from historical ratios |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | All 4 dimensions plus required traceability protocols covered, with stabilization |\n\n**P0 override**: Any new P0 finding sets `newFindingsRatio >= 0.50`, blocking convergence regardless of composite score.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `review/.deep-review-pause` exists (note: the file name uses the shared `-pause` suffix)\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"sentinel file detected\"}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```\n     Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {reviewed}/{total} dimensions complete, {P0}/{P1}/{P2} findings.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause review between iterations.\n\nNormalization rule: if the runtime first observes a raw `paused` condition or a raw `stuck_recovery` condition, it MUST rewrite the emitted JSONL event names to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` before appending them. Persisted review JSONL should never contain raw `paused` or raw `stuck_recovery` rows after emission.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated, review mode):\nIteration: {N} of {max} | Mode: review\nTarget: {config.reviewTarget} ({config.reviewTargetType})\nDimensions: {reviewed}/{total} complete | Next: {nextDimension}\nFindings: P0:{count} P1:{count} P2:{count} active\nTraceability: core={core_status} overlay={overlay_status}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nProvisional verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} | hasAdvisories={hasAdvisories}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n\nDispatch `@deep-review` with review-specific context:\n\n```\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nReview Target: {config.reviewTarget}\nReview Mode: {config.reviewTargetType}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Dimension: {strategy.nextFocus.dimension}\nFocus Files: {strategy.nextFocus.files}\nRemaining Dimensions: {strategy.remainingDimensions}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":765,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1782998221556,"end":1782998221598}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_022f8fc67e7e4354016a4664cd621c8191a9733dd6e015e044"}},"id":"prt_f22f9c2f0001b6AXn10WFIk21Q","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782998222337,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22f9c5fb001H3K5YUE1x2CqEk","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","messageID":"msg_f22f936c4001kCg30jhOZzms7V","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":56597,"input":16264,"output":393,"reasoning":516,"cache":{"write":0,"read":39424}},"cost":0}}
