{"type":"text","timestamp":1782998439880,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22fccbd6001ohaHBGaBtprJSm","messageID":"msg_f22fcbbf600107damhzSZvpul5","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"text","text":"I found one concrete review target already: child 007 is still in-progress and unimplemented while the parent/top-level summaries claim the follow-up phase has six of seven complete and only 007 open. I’m checking whether the live runtime actually has the sliding-window work; if absent, that becomes a traceability finding rather than an implementation defect in shipped code.","time":{"start":1782998420438,"end":1782998439879},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_074d2f22a48a93e6016a4665946a18819186873041826acac7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998439949,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bZrq40E5zqJVGuqtQXMlfJuT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/orchestrator.ts","offset":620,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/orchestrator.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n620:   entries.push(...runRegistryShellRules(folder, level, new Set(entries.map((item) => item.rule)), opts));\n621: \n622:   const summary = {\n623:     errors: entries.filter((item) => item.status === 'error').length,\n624:     warnings: entries.filter((item) => item.status === 'warn').length,\n625:     info: entries.filter((item) => item.status === 'info').length,\n626:   };\n627:   return {\n628:     folder,\n629:     level,\n630:     entries,\n631:     summary,\n632:     passed: summary.errors === 0 && !(opts.strict && summary.warnings > 0),\n633:   };\n634: }\n635: \n636: function parseCliArgs(argv: string[]): { folder: string; opts: ValidateOpts } {\n637:   let folder = '';\n638:   const opts: ValidateOpts = {};\n639:   for (let index = 0; index < argv.length; index += 1) {\n640:     const arg = argv[index];\n641:     switch (arg) {\n642:       case '--folder':\n643:         folder = argv[index + 1] ?? '';\n644:         index += 1;\n645:         break;\n646:       case '--strict':\n647:         opts.strict = true;\n648:         break;\n649:       case '--json':\n650:         opts.json = true;\n651:         break;\n652:       case '--quiet':\n653:       case '-q':\n654:         opts.quiet = true;\n655:         break;\n656:       case '--verbose':\n657:         opts.verbose = true;\n658:         break;\n659:       default:\n660:         if (!arg.startsWith('--') && !folder) folder = arg;\n66