ence-bearing graph rows since the latest snapshot', () => {\n\n  Line 207:     expect(signalsModule.computeGraphNoveltyDelta(nodes, edges, [snapshot])).toBeCloseTo(2 / 3, 5);\n\n  Line 210:   it('computeGraphNoveltyDelta fails open when no prior snapshot exists', () => {\n\n  Line 213:     expect(signalsModule.computeGraphNoveltyDelta(nodes, [], [])).toBe(0);\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts:\n  Line 381:     /step_resolve_session_id:[\\s\\S]*session_id_init: \"\\{session_id\\}\"[\\s\\S]*session_id_init: \"\\{ISO_8601_NOW\\}\"/,\n\n  Line 402:   const renderTemplate = (template: string) => template.replaceAll('{session_id_init}', sessionIdInit);\n\n  Line 555:         `You are orchestrating the ${agentName} workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage.`,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 424: Prompt summary: Validate the deep-research minIterations floor and convergenceMode behavior against config, YAML, and tests.\n\n  Line 426: Expected signals: `minIterations` defaults to 3, `convergenceMode` defaults to `default`, early STOP uses `minIterationsNotReached`, and `min_iterations_guard_pass` is emitted when the floor clears.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/manual_testing_playbook/04--convergence-and-recovery/anti-convergence-floor.md:\n  Line 29: - Prompt: `Validate the deep-research minIterations floor and convergenceMode behavior against config, YAML, and tests.`\n\n  Line 32: - Expected signals: `minIterations` defaults to 3, `convergenceMode` defaults to `default`, early STOP uses `minIterationsNotReached`, and `min_iterations_guard_pass` is emitted when the floor clears.\n\n  Line 46: Validate the deep-research minIterations floor and convergenceMode behavior against config, YAML, and tests.\n\n  Line 48: 1. `bash: rg -n 'minIterations|convergenceMode|antiConvergence' .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json`\n\n  Line 49: 2. `bash: rg -n 'min_iterations|minIterationsNotReached|min_iterations_guard_pass|convergenceMode' .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`\n\n  Line 52: `minIterations` defaults to 3, early convergence STOP is overridden until the floor clears, `convergenceMode` is accepted, and older configs without the field keep prior behavior with a warning.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/feature_catalog/03--convergence/anti-convergence-floor.md:\n  Line 7:   - \"convergenceMode off\"\n\n  Line 21: The anti-convergence floor keeps deep-research from ending after a shallow early signal. Operators get a declarative `minIterations` default and a `convergenceMode` escape hatch without weakening max-iteration, pause, or halt boundaries.\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"slidingWindow|sliding-window|convergenceMode|computeGraphNoveltyDelta|reportedNovelty|graphNoveltyDelta|session_id_init|sessionId_init|You are orchestrating|You are a .*agent running a fan-out|workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage","time":{"start":1782998439947,"end":1782998440034}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074d2f22a48a93e6016a4665a7d29c8191948e945e34abf8bc"}},"id":"prt_f22fd1808001oqLXjNLO29DsVj","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22fcbbf600107damhzSZvpul5"}}
