2`, all `title contains [template:`) — a genuine, real-world confirmation the detector works, not a synthetic-only pass.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-002-fanout-leaf-identity-conflation.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Changelog: Fanout LEAF-Identity Conflation [011-followup-remediation/002-fanout-leaf-identity-conflation]\"\n\n  Line 17: > Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/002-fanout-leaf-identity-conflation` (Level 1)\n\n  Line 18: > Parent packet: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/008-convergence-threshold-and-forced-depth-flag/spec.md:\n  Line 26:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 74: - Any change to the actual convergence ALGORITHM (that's child 009's sliding-window design work).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/006-ux-observability-automation/spec.md:\n  Line 60: | **Phase** | 6 of 7 |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/008-convergence-threshold-and-forced-depth-flag/plan.md:\n  Line 21:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/008-convergence-threshold-and-forced-depth-flag/tasks.md:\n  Line 21:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/decision-record.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Decision record for whether to build a sliding-window convergence mode now, defer it, or reject it.\"\n\n  Line 15:     recent_action: \"Recorded sliding-window convergence decision\"\n\n  Line 16:     next_safe_action: \"Implement sliding-window convergence in a follow-up phase if approved\"\n\n  Line 28:       - \"Recommendation: defer sliding-window implementation to a follow-up phase, but build it next because generation-2 evidence validated denominator drag.\"\n\n  Line 62: - This phase must not implement the sliding-window convergence mode; it is decision-record only for REQ-001.\n\n  Line 64: - Any future mode must be explicit, opt-in, and telemetry-visible so operators can compare full-history and sliding-window signals.\n\n  Line 73: **We chose**: Defer implementation from this phase, but build a sliding-window convergence mode in a follow-up phase.\n\n  Line 75: **How it works**: The follow-up should add an explicit `convergenceMode` value such as `sliding-window`, with a bounded `slidingWindowSize` such as 5 iterations. In that mode, convergence should evaluate recent `newInfoRatio` over the last N iterations rather than over the full accumulated denominator. The existing `default` full-history mode and `off` mode should remain available for backward-compatible operator intent.\n\n  Line 88: | Reject sliding-window mode | No new runtime complexity | Ignores generation-2 evidence that convergence would have stopped before late findings surfaced | 2/10 |\n\n  Line 100: - The follow-up has a concrete target: explicit `convergenceMode=sliding-window`, bounded window size, and telemetry that compares recent-window and full-history novelty.\n\n  Line 112: | Operators confuse `max-iterations` with adaptive convergence | L | Document `max-iterations` as fixed-depth intent and `sliding-window` as adaptive late-novelty intent |\n\n  Line 123: | 2 | **Beyond Local Maxima?** | PASS | Alternatives include default convergence, `off`, fixed-depth `max-iterations`, and a new sliding-window mode. |\n\n  Line 137: - No sliding-window convergence code is implemented.\n\n  Line 143: - Add `convergenceMode: \"sliding-window\"` alongside the current default and `off` modes.\n\n  Line 145: - Record both full-history and sliding-window `newInfoRatio` in telemetry for at least one rollout cycle.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/changelog-156-root.md:\n  Line 21: Packet 156 mined two reference loop codebases into a ranked improvement backlog, shipped that backlog as seven subsystem and remediation phases, then ran a deep-research fan-out against the packet itself and shipped the resulting 11-child remediation phase, then dispatched a 10-iteration deep-review against its own public documentation, and is now closing the follow-ups phase 009 itself deferred. Phases 001 through 010 are complete. Phase 011 has 6 of 7 children complete; the sliding-window convergence mode (child 007) has not started.\n\n  Line 51: | `011-followup-remediation` | In Progress (6/7) | Closes the 4 items phase 009's changelog deferred: fan-out session-id and LEAF-identity fixes, scaffold-content authoring for ~40 leaves, the validate.sh registry bridge (which also surfaced and closed a repo-wide dist-freshness gap, shipped separately as `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`). Sliding-window convergence (child 007) not started. |\n\n  Line 76: - Phase 009 identified several deliberately deferred items: 2 review findings remain genuinely active, a sliding-window convergence mode is a documented follow-up, the default validate.sh path does not read the shell rule registry, and dozens of leaf children across phases 002 through 007 still carry scaffold markers in their own plan.md or tasks.md. See `009-research-backlog-remediation/changelog-009-root.md` for detail.\n\n  Line 78: - Phase 011 has closed 3 of phase 009's 4 deferred items (both review findings, scaffold-content authoring, the validate.sh registry bridge). Child 007 (sliding-window convergence mode) remains open. See `011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md` for detail.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/spec.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Design (decision-record) a sliding-window convergence mode for forced-depth loops, and implement 4 concrete hardening recommendations: stall alerting, merge-time dedup, per-lineage cost cap, lag-ceiling observability mapping.\"\n\n  Line 25:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 27:       - \"Is a sliding-window convergence mode worth implementing now, or should this phase deliver only the decision-record/proposal and defer implementation to a follow-up, given research.md itself marks it needs-design and not directly observed as a live problem in the actual runs so far?\"\n\n  Line 48: | **Handoff Criteria** | A decision-record exists proposing (not necessarily shipping) a sliding-window convergence mode; all 4 named hardening items are implemented and tested |\n\n  Line 62: Produce a decision-record evaluating whether/how a sliding-window convergence mode should work (design only — implementation is a follow-up unless the design turns out to be trivial), and implement the 4 concrete hardening items, which don't require new algorithm design.\n\n  Line 71: - Write `decision-record.md` proposing a sliding-window convergence mode (e.g. average newInfoRatio over the last N iterations rather than full history) as an alternative `convergenceMode` value, alongside the existing `default`/`off` modes — cite the actual generation-2 forced-depth run's data (once available) as supporting/refuting evidence for whether denominator-drag is real.\n\n  Line 78: - Actually implementing the sliding-window convergence mode itself (design/decision-record only, per the Level-2 scope split above) — flag as a clear follow-up item if the decision-record concludes it should be built.\n\n  Line 98: | REQ-001 | A decision-record exists evaluating the sliding-window proposal | File exists, cites real evidence (including generation-2 data if available by the time this is implemented), and reaches an explicit recommendation (build now / defer / not needed) |\n\n  Line 116: - **SC-002**: Decision-record reaches an explicit, evidence-based recommendation on the sliding-window design.\n\n  Line 134: - Whether the sliding-window mode should actually be implemented in this phase or deferred — see frontmatter open_questions; resolve based on what the decision-record concludes.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/plan.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Plan for the sliding-window decision-record and 4 hardening implementations.\"\n\n  Line 21:     completion_pct: 0\n\n  Line 37: Two independent workstreams: (A) a design-only decision-record for sliding-window convergence — read `convergence.md`'s current rolling-average implementation, model the denominator-drag hypothesis mathematically, check the generation-2 forced-depth run's actual data (if it has completed by the time this phase is implemented) for real evidence either way, and write a recommendation. (B) four concrete hardening items in `fanout-run.cjs`/`fanout-merge.cjs`, each independently testable — check `fanout-merge.cjs`'s existing `enableNearDuplicateDedup` option first, since it may already solve item 2 of F-016.\n\n  Line 54: - **Design, don't build, the sliding-window mode this phase** — the research itself marked this needs-design and unobserved; premature implementation without checking real generation-2 data first would be exactly the kind of over-engineering this project's own quality principles warn against.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/tasks.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Task list for the sliding-window decision-record and 4 hardening items.\"\n\n  Line 21:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation/spec.md:\n  Line 11:     packet_pointer: \"deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation\"\n\n  Line 23:       session_id: \"sonnet-011-followup-remediation\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Summary of the sliding-window decision-record (defer) and the 4 hardening item dispositions (2 built, 2 already-existing and newly tested/documented).\"\n\n  Line 51: Wrote an evidence-cited `decision-record.md` recommending **defer** on a sliding-window convergence mode (build in a follow-up phase, not this one) — grounded in generation-2 forced-depth research's \"mathematically-proven\" denominator-drag finding, with citations down to the raw glm iteration files. Implemented the 2 hardening items that genuinely didn't exist yet (stall-watchdog alerting, per-lineage cost/budget cap), and confirmed + tested + explicitly dispositioned the 2 that turned out to already exist in the codebase (lag-ceiling status mapping, near-duplicate finding dedup).\n\n  Line 86: - **Defer the sliding-window convergence mode**, per the decision-record's own 5-checks evaluation and alternatives comparison — the packet's own scope explicitly banned implementing it in this phase regardless of how strong the evidence became.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation/plan.md:\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation\"\n\n  Line 20:       session_id: \"sonnet-011-followup-remediation\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation/tasks.md:\n  Line 10:     packet_pointer: \"deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation\"\n\n  Line 19:       session_id: \"sonnet-011-followup-remediation\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/007-parent-scaffold-and-governance-docs/spec.md:\n  Line 27:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 11:     packet_pointer: \"deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation\"\n\n  Line 42: | **Spec Folder** | `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation` |\n\n  Line 103: | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh .opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation/001-fanout-session-id-propagation --strict` | PASS: 0 errors, 0 warnings, RESULT PASSED. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/009-research-backlog-remediation/007-parent-scaffold-and-governance-docs/plan.md:\n  Line 21:     completion_pct: 0\n\n\n/Users/miche