{"type":"text","timestamp":1782998469513,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f22fd4638001QaPrjImK32HnN4","messageID":"msg_f22fd1c310019eIBNL8Ls4brlt","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"text","text":"The session-id fix is complete for deep-review, but the child summary itself records context/research as a follow-up candidate. I’m checking the shared context/research workflows now because the parent narrative appears to claim all three loop types were covered.","time":{"start":1782998451768,"end":1782998469510},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0088aca6b493ec06016a4665b3b3fc819486a50a0e8bb9f301","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998469572,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_eahOHOhAY7ZyAn1KDiNEcL7n","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/changelog-156-root.md","offset":1,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/changelog-156-root.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Changelog: Agent Loops Improved [030-agent-loops-improved/root]\"\n3: description: \"Packet-level rollup changelog for spec 156, agent-loops-improved, covering eleven phases from reference research through research-backlog remediation, a documentation truth audit, and an in-progress follow-up remediation phase.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"156 root changelog\"\n6:   - \"packet rollup changelog\"\n7:   - \"agent loops improved packet changelog\"\n8: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: ---\n11: # Changelog\n12: \n13: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: changelog/root.md | v1.0 -->\n14: \n15: ## 2026-07-01\n16: \n17: > Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved` (Level 2, phase parent)\n18: \n19: ### Summary\n20: \n21: Packet 156 mined two reference loop codebases into a ranked improvement backlog, shipped that backlog as seven subsystem and remediation phases, then ran a deep-research fan-out against the packet itself and shipped the resulting 11-child remediation phase, then dispatched a 10-iteration deep-review against its own public documentation, and is now closing the follow-ups phase 009 itself deferred. Phases 001 through 010 are complete. Phase 011 has 6 of 7 children complete; the sliding-window convergence mode (child 007) has not started.\n22: \n23: ### Before vs After\n24: \n25: **Before**\n26: \n27: The loop-based systems, deep-loop-runtime, deep-loop-workflows and the system-spec-kit commands and agents that drive them, carried known gaps in resilience, convergence quality, observability, safety and interconnection, with no ranked, evidence-backed program to close them.\n28: \n29: **After**\n30: \n31: The packet shipped a dependency-ordered program: reference research produced the backlog, deep-loop-runtime and deep-loop-workflows hardening landed first, then speckit autopilot, advisor interconnection, UX and observability, hermetic testing and a safety-remediation track followed. A phase then mined the packet's own remaining gaps and closed every tooling bug, every claimed-versus-actual drift and every infrastructure hardening item the research found, ending by fixing the two most severe bugs the research runtime surfaced in its own completion and hang-handling logic. A final phase dispatched an independent deep-review against the public README and confirmed it now matches what actually shipped.\n32: \n33: **Impact**\n34: \n35: The loop stack is now more durable under interruption, more explicit about convergence, more observable during long runs and safer around state mutation, the packet's own research-and-remediation tooling is now trustworthy enough to keep using on future work, and the public documentation a reader sees first now matches the shipped reality.\n36: \n37: ### Included Phases\n38: \n39: | Phase | Status | Summary |\n40: |---|---|---|\n41: | `001-reference-research` | Complete | 50-iteration mining of loop-cli-main and kasper into 40 ranked recommendations. |\n42: | `002-deep-loop-runtime` | Complete | 18 runtime recommendations: atomic-state, loop-lock, sleep, jsonl, executor and fallback, coverage-graph, fanout and lifecycle. |\n43: | `003-deep-loop-workflows` | Complete | 12 workflow recommendations: anti-convergence and ADRs, injection-inbox, ideas and rejected caches, benchmark, push-wave. |\n44: | `004-system-spec-kit` | Complete | Speckit autopilot lifecycle. |\n45: | `005-skill-interconnection` | Complete | Advisor routing projection. |\n46: | `006-ux-observability-automation` | Complete | Dashboards, telemetry heartbeat, run-now, dry-run, observability envelope, memory-upsert. |\n47: | `007-testing` | Complete | Hermetic test isolation, record-replay cassette harness. |\n48: | `008-loop-systems-remediation` | Complete | Deep-review deferred findings and MiMo-campaign recommendations across 7 children, rollback hash-guard through detached CLI fan-out hardening. |\n49: | `009-research-backlog-remediation` | Complete | 11 children implementing a deep-research fan-out's own backlog against the packet, tooling bug fixes, drift closure, convergence and observability hardening, synthesis integrity and orchestrator watchdog. |\n50: | `010-documentation-truth-audit` | Complete | Dispatched 10-iteration GPT-5.5-fast deep-review of the public README against everything shipped; fixed a stale section label, an under-promoted Goal plugin, a missing safety-posture disclosure and a stale metadata entity. |\n51: | `011-followup-remediation` | In Progress (6/7) | Closes the 4 items phase 009's changelog deferred: fan-out session-id and LEAF-identity fixes, scaffold-content authoring for ~40 leaves, the validate.sh registry bridge (which also surfaced and closed a repo-wide dist-freshness gap, shipped separately as `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`). Sliding-window convergence (child 007) not started. |\n52: \n53: ### Added\n54: \n55: - See each phase's own root changelog in this directory for phase-level detail.\n56: \n57: ### Changed\n58: \n59: - See each phase's own root changelog in this directory for phase-level detail.\n60: \n61: ### Fixed\n62: \n63: - See each phase's own root changelog in this directory for phase-level detail.\n64: \n65: ### Verification\n66: \n67: - `validate.sh --strict --recursive` on the packet root, PASSED with 0 errors across all 12 top-level folders as of phase 011 child 006's completion (2026-07-02) -- re-verified after a repo-wide dist-freshness fix and metadata regen, not just at phase 010.\n68: - Every phase independently validated and, where applicable, independently test-verified before being marked Complete.\n69: \n70: ### Files Changed\n71: \n72: _No packet-level file-level detail recorded. See each phase's own root changelog and leaf changelogs for full file-level detail._\n73: \n74: ### Follow-Ups\n75: \n76: - Phase 009 identified several deliberately deferred items: 2 review findings remain genuinely active, a sliding-window convergence mode is a documented follow-up, the default validate.sh path does not read the shell rule registry, and dozens of leaf children across phases 002 through 007 still carry scaffold markers in their own plan.md or tasks.md. See `009-research-backlog-remediation/changelog-009-root.md` for detail.\n77: - Phase 010 found no follow-ups of its own. See `010-documentation-truth-audit/changelog-010-root.md` for detail.\n78: - Phase 011 has closed 3 of phase 009's 4 deferred items (both review findings, scaffold-content authoring, the validate.sh registry bridge). Child 007 (sliding-window convergence mode) remains open. See `011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md` for detail.\n\n(End of file - total 78 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Changelog: Agent Loops Improved [030-agent-loops-improved/root]\"\ndescription: \"Packet-level rollup changelog for spec 156, agent-loops-improved, covering eleven phases from reference research through research-backlog remediation, a documentation truth audit, and an in-progress follow-up remediation phase.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"156 root changelog\"\n  - \"packet rollup changelog\"\n  - \"agent loops improved packet changelog\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n# Changelog\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: changelog/root.md | v1.0 -->\n\n## 2026-07-01\n\n> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved` (Level 2, phase parent)\n\n### Summary\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/changelog-156-root.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Changelog: Agent Loops Improved [030-agent-loops-improved/root]\"\ndescription: \"Packet-level rollup changelog for spec 156, agent-loops-improved, covering eleven phases from reference research through research-backlog remediation, a documentation truth audit, and an in-progress follow-up remediation phase.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"156 root changelog\"\n  - \"packet rollup changelog\"\n  - \"agent loops improved packet changelog\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n# Changelog\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: changelog/root.md | v1.0 -->\n\n## 2026-07-01\n\n> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved` (Level 2, phase parent)\n\n### Summary\n\nPacket 156 mined two reference loop codebases into a ranked improvement backlog, shipped that backlog as seven subsystem and remediation phases, then ran a deep-research fan-out against the packet itself and shipped the resulting 11-child remediation phase, then dispatched a 10-iteration deep-review against its own public documentation, and is now closing the follow-ups phase 009 itself deferred. Phases 001 through 010 are complete. Phase 011 has 6 of 7 children complete; the sliding-window convergence mode (child 007) has not started.\n\n### Before vs After\n\n**Before**\n\nThe loop-based systems, deep-loop-runtime, deep-loop-workflows and the system-spec-kit commands and agents that drive them, carried known gaps in resilience, convergence quality, observability, safety and interconnection, with no ranked, evidence-backed program to close them.\n\n**After**\n\nThe packet shipped a dependency-ordered program: reference research produced the backlog, deep-loop-runtime and deep-loop-workflows hardening landed first, then speckit autopilot, advisor interconnection, UX and observability, hermetic testing and a safety-remediation track followed. A phase then mined the packet's own remaining gaps and closed every tooling bug, every claimed-versus-actual drift and every infrastructure hardening item the research found, ending by fixing the two most severe bugs the research runtime surfaced in its own completion and hang-handling logic. A final phase dispatched an independent deep-review against the public README and confirmed it now matches what actually shipped.\n\n**Impact**\n\nThe loop stack is now more durable under interruption, more explicit about convergence, more observable during long runs and safer around state mutation, the packet's own research-and-remediation tooling is now trustworthy enough to keep using on future work, and the public documentation a reader sees first now matches the shipped reality.\n\n### Included Phases\n\n| Phase | Status | Summary |\n|---|---|---|\n| `001-reference-research` | Complete | 50-iteration mining of loop-cli-main and kasper into 40 ranked recommendations. |\n| `002-deep-loop-runtime` | Complete | 18 runtime recommendations: atomic-state, loop-lock, sleep, jsonl, executor and fallback, coverage-graph, fanout and lifecycle. |\n| `003-deep-loop-workflows` | Complete | 12 workflow recommendations: anti-convergence and ADRs, injection-inbox, ideas and rejected caches, benchmark, push-wave. |\n| `004-system-spec-kit` | Complete | Speckit autopilot lifecycle. |\n| `005-skill-interconnection` | Complete | Advisor routing projection. |\n| `006-ux-observability-automation` | Complete | Dashboards, telemetry heartbeat, run-now, dry-run, observability envelope, memory-upsert. |\n| `007-testing` | Complete | Hermetic test isolation, record-replay cassette harness. |\n| `008-loop-systems-remediation` | Complete | Deep-review deferred findings and MiMo-campaign recommendations across 7 children, rollback hash-guard through detached CLI fan-out hardening. |\n| `009-research-backlog-remediation` | Complete | 11 children implementing a deep-research fan-out's own backlog against the packet, tooling bug fixes, drift closure, convergence and observability hardening, synthesis integrity and orchestrator watchdog. |\n| `010-documentation-truth-audit` | Complete | Dispatched 10-iteration GPT-5.5-fast deep-review of the public README against everything shipped; fixed a stale section label, an under-promoted Goal plugin, a missing safety-posture disclosure and a stale metadata entity. |\n| `011-followup-remediation` | In Progress (6/7) | Closes the 4 items phase 009's changelog deferred: fan-out session-id and LEAF-identity fixes, scaffold-content authoring for ~40 leaves, the validate.sh registry bridge (which also surfaced and closed a repo-wide dist-freshness gap, shipped separately as `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`). Sliding-window convergence (child 007) not started. |\n\n### Added\n\n- See each phase's own root changelog in this directory for phase-level detail.\n\n### Changed\n\n- See each phase's own root changelog in this directory for phase-level detail.\n\n### Fixed\n\n- See each phase's own root changelog in this directory for phase-level detail.\n\n### Verification\n\n- `validate.sh --strict --recursive` on the packet root, PASSED with 0 errors across all 12 top-level folders as of phase 011 child 006's completion (2026-07-02) -- re-verified after a repo-wide dist-freshness fix and metadata regen, not just at phase 010.\n- Every phase independently validated and, where applicable, independently test-verified before being marked Complete.\n\n### Files Changed\n\n_No packet-level file-level detail recorded. See each phase's own root changelog and leaf changelogs for full file-level detail._\n\n### Follow-Ups\n\n- Phase 009 identified several deliberately deferred items: 2 review findings remain genuinely active, a sliding-window convergence mode is a documented follow-up, the default validate.sh path does not read the shell rule registry, and dozens of leaf children across phases 002 through 007 still carry scaffold markers in their own plan.md or tasks.md. See `009-research-backlog-remediation/changelog-009-root.md` for detail.\n- Phase 010 found no follow-ups of its own. See `010-documentation-truth-audit/changelog-010-root.md` for detail.\n- Phase 011 has closed 3 of phase 009's 4 deferred items (both review findings, scaffold-content authoring, the validate.sh registry bridge). Child 007 (sliding-window convergence mode) remains open. See `011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md` for detail.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":78,"totalLines":78,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/changelog-156-root.md","time":{"start":1782998469559,"end":1782998469570}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0088aca6b493ec06016a4665c56c748194bd7a108accd980a8"}},"id":"prt_f22fd8bb6001jG2Gr35onyuEDd","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22fd1c310019eIBNL8Ls4brlt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998469584,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8wC7i5DsqEpPehWthLmjSk4q","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md","offset":1,"limit":130},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Changelog: Follow-Up Remediation [011-followup-remediation/root]\"\n3: description: \"Chronological changelog for the Follow-Up Remediation spec root.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"root changelog\"\n6:   - \"packet changelog\"\n7:   - \"nested changelog\"\n8: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n9: contextType: \"implementation\"\n10: ---\n11: # Changelog\n12: \n13: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: changelog/root.md | v1.0 -->\n14: \n15: ## 2026-07-02\n16: \n17: > Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation` (Level 2)\n18: \n19: ### Summary\n20: \n21: Phase 011 closes the 4 deferred follow-ups phase 009's own changelog named: 2 active review findings from a prior codex deep-review lineage, scaffold-content authoring debt across phases 002-007, the `validate.sh` dual-path registry-bridge gap, and (not yet started) the sliding-window convergence mode. Children 001-006 are Complete; child 007 (sliding-window convergence) remains pending. Closing child 006 required tracing a stale-dist bug in `validate.sh` itself back to its root cause and, once fixed, discovering the fix's true blast radius was repo-wide rather than packet-scoped — that work was spun out into its own packet (`system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`) rather than absorbed into this phase, to keep this phase's own scope from ballooning past \"close packet 030's follow-ups.\"\n22: \n23: ### Before vs After\n24: \n25: **Before**\n26: \n27: `deep_review_auto.yaml`'s \"new lineage\" init path wrote `sessionId` as a raw timestamp instead of binding the real session id the fan-out runner generates, so every downstream consumer (state log, findings registry, convergence events, claim adjudication) inherited the wrong id. The shared fan-out prompt builder told dispatched subprocesses \"you are a {agentName} agent\" and instructed them to run the full multi-iteration loop, contradicting the LEAF-agent contract that requires exactly one iteration. 18 leaves under `002-deep-loop-runtime`, 12 under `003-deep-loop-workflows`, and 10 more across `004-007` had genuinely-authored `spec.md` files but scaffold-template placeholder `plan.md`/`tasks.md` bodies. The default `validate.sh` invocation never ran registry-backed shell rules (`COMMENT_HYGIENE_MARKER`, `SCAFFOLD_NEVER_TOUCHED`, and ~18 others), only the 2 originally believed to be the whole gap — because the compiled validation orchestrator `validate.sh` depends on had been silently stale for roughly two weeks, with no freshness check anywhere in the repo to catch it.\n28: \n29: **After**\n30: \n31: Both fan-out review findings are fixed: session ids propagate correctly through the native-executor path too, and the shared prompt builder frames dispatched subprocesses as orchestrating the workflow YAML rather than claiming LEAF-agent identity, covering all 3 loop types (context/research/review) from one shared-function fix. All ~40 originally-scoped leaf children (plus `001-reference-research`, a standalone phase outside that original count) now carry real, spec.md-grounded `plan.md`/`tasks.md` content. `validate.sh`'s default path now bridges every eligible registry rule automatically, proven by a fixture that previously would have silently passed and now correctly fails. A permanent, repo-wide dist-freshness enforcement layer now exists — a shared checker, a hard `validate.sh` backstop, a Claude Code hook, and an OpenCode plugin — so this exact failure mode (a stale compiled artifact silently masking shipped validator logic for weeks) cannot recur unnoticed again.\n32: \n33: **Impact**\n34: \n35: Packet 030 itself passes `validate.sh --strict --recursive` with 0 errors across all 12 folders. The registry-bridge fix, once its true scope was understood, also exposed and is now closing a repo-wide validation debt spanning all 43 packet roots in the monorepo (257 folders) — most of it pre-existing and never previously visible to any caller, not something this phase's own changes created.\n36: \n37: **Why**\n38: \n39: Phase 009's changelog explicitly deferred these 4 items rather than declaring them silently out of scope; leaving them open after packet 030 was otherwise \"done\" would have meant the packet's own documented follow-up list stayed permanently stale. Sequencing children 003-005 (scaffold-content authoring) strictly before child 006 (the registry bridge) was a hard dependency: enabling `SCAFFOLD_NEVER_TOUCHED` by default before those ~40 leaves had real content would have immediately broken them.\n40: \n41: ### Added\n42: \n43: - `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/dist-freshness.cjs` — shared source-vs-dist staleness checker, 7 watched packages.\n44: - `.opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js` — OpenCode plugin warning before risky Bash dispatches and once per session.\n45: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh` — Claude Code PostToolUse warn-only checker.\n46: - A hard fail-closed backstop in `validate.sh`'s `run_node_orchestrator()` (exit 3 on stale compiled orchestrator).\n47: - `runRegistryShellRules()` and 3 supporting functions in `orchestrator.ts`, bridging the default validate.sh path to registry-backed shell rules.\n48: - Real `plan.md`/`tasks.md`/`implementation-summary.md` content for `001-reference-research` and all ~40 leaf children across phases 002-007.\n49: - New top-level packet `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation` (2 children: dist-freshness enforcement, repo-wide remediation sweep).\n50: \n51: ### Changed\n52: \n53: - `deep_review_auto.yaml` / `deep_review_confirm.yaml`: `session_id` now resolved and bound into config/state-log/findings-registry writes instead of a raw timestamp.\n54: - `fanout-run.cjs`'s `buildLoopPrompt` identity line reworded across all 3 loop types; `buildNativeCommandInput` now threads a session id.\n55: - `.opencode/bin/{spec-memory,code-index,skill-advisor}.cjs` migrated from inline per-shim freshness logic onto the shared `dist-freshness.cjs` module.\n56: - `finalize-dist.mjs` had a now-dead build-time hash write removed (orphaned when the CLI shims migrated to the shared cache scheme) and a stale, sourceless `hooks/opencode/session-start.js` artifact requirement removed.\n57: \n58: ### Fixed\n59: \n60: - Fan-out session-id propagation (F002) and LEAF-identity conflation (F003), both prior codex deep-review findings.\n61: - ~40 leaf children's scaffold-template content debt across phases 002-007, plus `001-reference-research`'s own 9 scaffold markers (outside the original leaf-only scope).\n62: - A `Spec Folder` metadata literal-string-compare bug in `008-loop-systems-remediation` and `010-documentation-truth-audit`'s own `implementation-summary.md` files, discovered while investigating the same gate failure.\n63: - 3 P2 findings from a formal `sk-code-review` pass on the new dist-freshness code (silent fail-open on an unexpected checker error, a symlink-cycle gap in the source-file walk, a non-atomic cache write).\n64: \n65: ### Verification\n66: \n67: - `validate.sh --strict --recursive` on the whole `030-agent-loops-improved` packet: 0 errors, 12/12 folders.\n68: - `test-validation-extended.sh`: 113/113, independently re-run multiple times across this phase's work.\n69: - `072-scaffold-never-touched-violation` fixture: fails via the default invocation (previously would have silently passed); `073-scaffold-never-touched-clean` still passes; explicit `SPECKIT_RULES=` path confirmed unchanged.\n70: - A `git checkout` incident mid-session discarded child 006's uncommitted work; recovered from a local Time Machine snapshot and independently re-verified (diff-stat, full function-level read, two full test-suite re-runs) — recorded in `006-validate-sh-registry-bridge/implementation-summary.md`.\n71: - Formal `sk-code-review` pass on the dist-freshness code: APPROVED after fixing all 3 P2 findings it raised.\n72: \n73: ### Files Changed\n74: \n75: | File | Change |\n76: |------|--------|\n77: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`, `deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Session-id resolution and binding |\n78: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Identity-line rewording, native-executor session-id threading |\n79: | `002-deep-loop-runtime/{001-018}-*`, `003-deep-loop-workflows/{001-012}-*`, `004-007`'s 10 leaves, `001-reference-research` | Real `plan.md`/`tasks.md`/`implementation-summary.md` content |\n80: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/orchestrator.ts` | Registry-bridge functions, wired into `validateFolder()` |\n81: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/test-validation-extended.sh` | New default-path scaffold regression test |\n82: | `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation/**` (new packet) | Shared dist-freshness infra + repo-wide remediation sweep |\n83: | `.opencode/bin/{spec-memory,code-index,skill-advisor}.cjs`, `finalize-dist.mjs` | Migrated onto shared freshness module, dead-code removed |\n84: | `008-loop-systems-remediation`, `010-documentation-truth-audit` `implementation-summary.md` | Spec Folder metadata fix |\n85: \n86: ### Follow-Ups\n87: \n88: - Child 007 (sliding-window convergence mode, per ADR-001 in `009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/decision-record.md`) has not started.\n89: - `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`'s bucket-3 report (54 folders across 17 packets, mostly `ai-systems/*`, that predate the current template-compliance contract) recommends extending `SPECKIT_GENERATED_METADATA_GRANDFATHER` into a general template-compliance grandfather mechanism — a policy decision still open, not implemented.\n\n(End of file - total 89 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Changelog: Follow-Up Remediation [011-followup-remediation/root]\"\ndescription: \"Chronological changelog for the Follow-Up Remediation spec root.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"root changelog\"\n  - \"packet changelog\"\n  - \"nested changelog\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n# Changelog\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: changelog/root.md | v1.0 -->\n\n## 2026-07-02\n\n> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation` (Level 2)\n\n### Summary\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Changelog: Follow-Up Remediation [011-followup-remediation/root]\"\ndescription: \"Chronological changelog for the Follow-Up Remediation spec root.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"root changelog\"\n  - \"packet changelog\"\n  - \"nested changelog\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n# Changelog\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: changelog/root.md | v1.0 -->\n\n## 2026-07-02\n\n> Spec folder: `.opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/011-followup-remediation` (Level 2)\n\n### Summary\n\nPhase 011 closes the 4 deferred follow-ups phase 009's own changelog named: 2 active review findings from a prior codex deep-review lineage, scaffold-content authoring debt across phases 002-007, the `validate.sh` dual-path registry-bridge gap, and (not yet started) the sliding-window convergence mode. Children 001-006 are Complete; child 007 (sliding-window convergence) remains pending. Closing child 006 required tracing a stale-dist bug in `validate.sh` itself back to its root cause and, once fixed, discovering the fix's true blast radius was repo-wide rather than packet-scoped — that work was spun out into its own packet (`system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`) rather than absorbed into this phase, to keep this phase's own scope from ballooning past \"close packet 030's follow-ups.\"\n\n### Before vs After\n\n**Before**\n\n`deep_review_auto.yaml`'s \"new lineage\" init path wrote `sessionId` as a raw timestamp instead of binding the real session id the fan-out runner generates, so every downstream consumer (state log, findings registry, convergence events, claim adjudication) inherited the wrong id. The shared fan-out prompt builder told dispatched subprocesses \"you are a {agentName} agent\" and instructed them to run the full multi-iteration loop, contradicting the LEAF-agent contract that requires exactly one iteration. 18 leaves under `002-deep-loop-runtime`, 12 under `003-deep-loop-workflows`, and 10 more across `004-007` had genuinely-authored `spec.md` files but scaffold-template placeholder `plan.md`/`tasks.md` bodies. The default `validate.sh` invocation never ran registry-backed shell rules (`COMMENT_HYGIENE_MARKER`, `SCAFFOLD_NEVER_TOUCHED`, and ~18 others), only the 2 originally believed to be the whole gap — because the compiled validation orchestrator `validate.sh` depends on had been silently stale for roughly two weeks, with no freshness check anywhere in the repo to catch it.\n\n**After**\n\nBoth fan-out review findings are fixed: session ids propagate correctly through the native-executor path too, and the shared prompt builder frames dispatched subprocesses as orchestrating the workflow YAML rather than claiming LEAF-agent identity, covering all 3 loop types (context/research/review) from one shared-function fix. All ~40 originally-scoped leaf children (plus `001-reference-research`, a standalone phase outside that original count) now carry real, spec.md-grounded `plan.md`/`tasks.md` content. `validate.sh`'s default path now bridges every eligible registry rule automatically, proven by a fixture that previously would have silently passed and now correctly fails. A permanent, repo-wide dist-freshness enforcement layer now exists — a shared checker, a hard `validate.sh` backstop, a Claude Code hook, and an OpenCode plugin — so this exact failure mode (a stale compiled artifact silently masking shipped validator logic for weeks) cannot recur unnoticed again.\n\n**Impact**\n\nPacket 030 itself passes `validate.sh --strict --recursive` with 0 errors across all 12 folders. The registry-bridge fix, once its true scope was understood, also exposed and is now closing a repo-wide validation debt spanning all 43 packet roots in the monorepo (257 folders) — most of it pre-existing and never previously visible to any caller, not something this phase's own changes created.\n\n**Why**\n\nPhase 009's changelog explicitly deferred these 4 items rather than declaring them silently out of scope; leaving them open after packet 030 was otherwise \"done\" would have meant the packet's own documented follow-up list stayed permanently stale. Sequencing children 003-005 (scaffold-content authoring) strictly before child 006 (the registry bridge) was a hard dependency: enabling `SCAFFOLD_NEVER_TOUCHED` by default before those ~40 leaves had real content would have immediately broken them.\n\n### Added\n\n- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/dist-freshness.cjs` — shared source-vs-dist staleness checker, 7 watched packages.\n- `.opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js` — OpenCode plugin warning before risky Bash dispatches and once per session.\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-code/scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh` — Claude Code PostToolUse warn-only checker.\n- A hard fail-closed backstop in `validate.sh`'s `run_node_orchestrator()` (exit 3 on stale compiled orchestrator).\n- `runRegistryShellRules()` and 3 supporting functions in `orchestrator.ts`, bridging the default validate.sh path to registry-backed shell rules.\n- Real `plan.md`/`tasks.md`/`implementation-summary.md` content for `001-reference-research` and all ~40 leaf children across phases 002-007.\n- New top-level packet `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation` (2 children: dist-freshness enforcement, repo-wide remediation sweep).\n\n### Changed\n\n- `deep_review_auto.yaml` / `deep_review_confirm.yaml`: `session_id` now resolved and bound into config/state-log/findings-registry writes instead of a raw timestamp.\n- `fanout-run.cjs`'s `buildLoopPrompt` identity line reworded across all 3 loop types; `buildNativeCommandInput` now threads a session id.\n- `.opencode/bin/{spec-memory,code-index,skill-advisor}.cjs` migrated from inline per-shim freshness logic onto the shared `dist-freshness.cjs` module.\n- `finalize-dist.mjs` had a now-dead build-time hash write removed (orphaned when the CLI shims migrated to the shared cache scheme) and a stale, sourceless `hooks/opencode/session-start.js` artifact requirement removed.\n\n### Fixed\n\n- Fan-out session-id propagation (F002) and LEAF-identity conflation (F003), both prior codex deep-review findings.\n- ~40 leaf children's scaffold-template content debt across phases 002-007, plus `001-reference-research`'s own 9 scaffold markers (outside the original leaf-only scope).\n- A `Spec Folder` metadata literal-string-compare bug in `008-loop-systems-remediation` and `010-documentation-truth-audit`'s own `implementation-summary.md` files, discovered while investigating the same gate failure.\n- 3 P2 findings from a formal `sk-code-review` pass on the new dist-freshness code (silent fail-open on an unexpected checker error, a symlink-cycle gap in the source-file walk, a non-atomic cache write).\n\n### Verification\n\n- `validate.sh --strict --recursive` on the whole `030-agent-loops-improved` packet: 0 errors, 12/12 folders.\n- `test-validation-extended.sh`: 113/113, independently re-run multiple times across this phase's work.\n- `072-scaffold-never-touched-violation` fixture: fails via the default invocation (previously would have silently passed); `073-scaffold-never-touched-clean` still passes; explicit `SPECKIT_RULES=` path confirmed unchanged.\n- A `git checkout` incident mid-session discarded child 006's uncommitted work; recovered from a local Time Machine snapshot and independently re-verified (diff-stat, full function-level read, two full test-suite re-runs) — recorded in `006-validate-sh-registry-bridge/implementation-summary.md`.\n- Formal `sk-code-review` pass on the dist-freshness code: APPROVED after fixing all 3 P2 findings it raised.\n\n### Files Changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml`, `deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Session-id resolution and binding |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Identity-line rewording, native-executor session-id threading |\n| `002-deep-loop-runtime/{001-018}-*`, `003-deep-loop-workflows/{001-012}-*`, `004-007`'s 10 leaves, `001-reference-research` | Real `plan.md`/`tasks.md`/`implementation-summary.md` content |\n| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/orchestrator.ts` | Registry-bridge functions, wired into `validateFolder()` |\n| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/test-validation-extended.sh` | New default-path scaffold regression test |\n| `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation/**` (new packet) | Shared dist-freshness infra + repo-wide remediation sweep |\n| `.opencode/bin/{spec-memory,code-index,skill-advisor}.cjs`, `finalize-dist.mjs` | Migrated onto shared freshness module, dead-code removed |\n| `008-loop-systems-remediation`, `010-documentation-truth-audit` `implementation-summary.md` | Spec Folder metadata fix |\n\n### Follow-Ups\n\n- Child 007 (sliding-window convergence mode, per ADR-001 in `009-research-backlog-remediation/009-convergence-design-and-hardening/decision-record.md`) has not started.\n- `system-speckit/030-validate-sh-dist-freshness-and-repo-remediation`'s bucket-3 report (54 folders across 17 packets, mostly `ai-systems/*`, that predate the current template-compliance contract) recommends extending `SPECKIT_GENERATED_METADATA_GRANDFATHER` into a general template-compliance grandfather mechanism — a policy decision still open, not implemented.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":89,"totalLines":89,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/changelog/011-followup-remediation/changelog-011-root.md","time":{"start":1782998469562,"end":1782998469573}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0088aca6b493ec06016a4665c56c7c8194b184a4319e10f064"}},"id":"prt_f22fd8bb8001o1zWKNEzY3aU2l","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22fd1c310019eIBNL8Ls4brlt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998469585,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_GhZ8ax8rzWOCI61F7bGnXrNp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":380},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\n5: # - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\n6: #   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\n9: #   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\n10: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n11: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n12: #\n13: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\n14: # - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\n15: #   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\n16: #   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\n17: #   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n18: #\n19: # HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\n20: # - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a\n21: #   READ-ONLY analyzer that returns structured findings. The HOST (this\n22: #   workflow) is the ONLY writer of merged state: iteration files,\n23: #   coverage-graph, dashboard, and the Context Report. This keeps the loop\n24: #   Gate-3-safe even when CLI seats run with permissive sandboxes.\n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: role: Deep Context Loop Manager\n27: purpose: Iterative codebase-context gathering via parallel heterogeneous sweeps with convergence detection\n28: action: Run deep-context loop from initialization through synthesis\n29: operating_mode:\n30:   workflow: iterative_loop\n31:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n32:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n33:   approvals: none\n34:   tracking: progressive_context_state\n35:   validation: convergence_detection\n36: \n37: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n38: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: operating_principles:\n41:   core: \"Fresh per-iteration sweep + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n42:   approach: \"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over ONE shared focus in parallel, merge by agreement, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n43:   mandate: \"Seats are read-only analyzers; the host writes ALL merged state. Never hold findings in memory only.\"\n44:   by_model_shared_scope: \"Every seat sweeps the SAME current focus each iteration. Cross-executor AGREEMENT is the confidence signal — NOT disjoint-slice fan-out.\"\n45: \n46: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n47: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: user_inputs:\n50:   scope: \"[SCOPE] - Target feature/area to gather codebase context for. REQUIRED.\"\n51:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path (or standalone run dir). REQUIRED.\"\n52:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 8.\"\n53:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Per-iteration new-agreement-eligible-findings floor. Default: 0.10.\"\n54:   executor_pool: \"[EXECUTOR_POOL] - Shared-scope pool (config.fanout.executors). Default: 2 native (native-only); CLI/combined via --executor/--executors.\"\n55:   relevance_gate: \"[RELEVANCE_GATE] - Min relevance to keep a finding (else lowConfidence). Default: 0.55 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n56:   agreement_min: \"[AGREEMENT_MIN] - Min distinct executors for a finding to be agreement-eligible. Default: 2 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n57:   concurrency: \"[CONCURRENCY] - Max parallel seats in the by-model sweep. Default: 4 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n58: \n59: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n60: # CONTEXT LOADING\n61: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n62: context_loading:\n63:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n64:   purpose: \"Load prior context for the scope and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n65:   mcp_integration:\n66:     tool: memory_context\n67:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n68:     parameters: { input: \"{scope}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n69:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n70:   behavior:\n71:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n72:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n73: \n74: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n75: # SKILL REFERENCE\n76: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n77: skill_reference:\n78:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n79:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md\n80:   references:\n81:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n82:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/convergence/convergence.md\n83:   templates:\n84:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json\n85:     report: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/context_report_template.md\n86:   runtime:\n87:     coverage_graph_db: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\n88:     convergence_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs\n89:     upsert_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs\n90:     fanout_run_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\n91:     fanout_merge_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs\n92:     council_dispatch: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs\n93:   prompt_framing: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md\n94: \n95: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n96: # AGENT CONFIGURATION (native seat)\n97: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n98: agent_config:\n99:   agent: deep-context\n100:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-context.md\"\n101:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n102:   model: opus\n103:   leaf_only: true\n104:   read_only_analyzer: true\n105:   tools: [Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query, code_graph_context]\n106:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n107:   note: \"Native seats are READ-ONLY. They return structured findings to the host; they never write merged state.\"\n108: \n109: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n110: # STATE FILE PATHS\n111: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n112: state_paths:\n113:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n114:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-config.json\"\n115:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-state.jsonl\"\n116:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-strategy.md\"\n117:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n118:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-dashboard.md\"\n119:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context-pause\"\n120:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context.lock\"\n121:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n122:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n123:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n124:   # Per-seat raw findings for an iteration (one file per seat, host-collected before merge).\n125:   seat_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/seats\"\n126:   seat_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/seats/iter-{NNN}/{label}.json\"\n127:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n128:   # canonical state_log append. Must contain at least one record whose type === \"iteration\".\n129:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n130:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n131:   report_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.md\"\n132:   report_json_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.json\"\n133:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n134: \n135: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n136: # WORKFLOW\n137: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n138: workflow:\n139: \n140:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n141:     description: \"Resolve the context artifact directory from spec_folder (or standalone run dir)\"\n142:     note: \"Root specs keep context artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/context/. Child phases keep local packet dirs in {spec_folder}/context/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/context_archive/{packet}/. When no spec folder exists, use a standalone run dir and hand context-report.md to /speckit:plan.\"\n143:     command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'context')));\\\"\"\n144:     outputs:\n145:       - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local context owner directory\"\n146:       - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n147:       - artifact_dir: \"Resolved context packet directory for this target\"\n148:       - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local context archive directory for this target\"\n149: \n150:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n151:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n152:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n153:   phase_init:\n154:     purpose: Create all state files and seed the frontier for the context session\n155:     steps:\n156: \n157:       step_preflight_contract:\n158:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n159:         verify:\n160:           - required_values_present: [scope, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, executor_pool]\n161:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation). A standalone run dir is allowed ONLY when no spec folder was named in the scope or derivable from it; FAIL closed if a standalone target is bound while the scope named or derived a spec folder (auto_mode_contract §1 fallback guard)\"\n162:           - pool_non_empty: \"config.fanout.executors has at least one seat (warn when exactly one — no agreement signal)\"\n163:           - pool_mode: \"config.fanout.mode == 'by-model-shared-scope'\"\n164:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n165:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n166:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n167: \n168:       step_create_directories:\n169:         action: \"Create spec folder and context packet directories if they don't exist\"\n170:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir} {state_paths.seat_dir}\"\n171: \n172:       step_acquire_lock:\n173:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n174:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --packet {spec_folder}\"\n175:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-context run already holds this packet.\"\n176:         note: \"Uses the deep-loop-runtime loop-lock helper (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n177:         on_halt:\n178:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n179:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n180:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n181:         on_cancel:\n182:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n183:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n184:         on_workflow_exit:\n185:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n186:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n187: \n188:       step_classify_session:\n189:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n190:         inspect:\n191:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n192:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n193:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n194:         classify:\n195:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n196:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on scope/spec folder\"\n197:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n198:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n199:         outputs:\n200:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n201:         on_resume:\n202:           gate3_classification: write-path\n203:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n204:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n205:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n206:           skip_to: phase_loop\n207:         on_restart:\n208:           action: \"Archive the current context packet under the local context_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n209:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n210:           set:\n211:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n212:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n213:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n214:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n215:           skip_to: step_create_config\n216:         on_completed_session:\n217:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed context/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n218:           halt: true\n219:           message: \"Completed deep-context packet detected. Archive or replace the existing context/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n220:         on_invalid_state:\n221:           halt: true\n222:           message: \"Existing deep-context state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid context packet before continuing.\"\n223:         on_fresh:\n224:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n225: \n226:       step_seed_frontier:\n227:         action: \"Seed the SLICE frontier from the scope BEFORE the first sweep (never a whole-repo sweep)\"\n228:         instructions: |\n229:           1. Extract anchors from {scope}: paths, symbols, error strings, domain terms.\n230:           2. Expand via the System Code Graph: code_graph_query on 2-5 word concept descriptions →\n231:              blast-radius / calls → ranked SLICE nodes.\n232:           3. If the code graph is stale or unavailable, fall back to Glob+Grep over the anchors.\n233:           4. Rank slices by anchor proximity; cap the initial frontier so each iteration's focus\n234:              is a tractable slice set, not the whole repo.\n235:         outputs:\n236:           - frontier_slices_json: \"Ranked SLICE node list (path, symbol, kind, rank), else [] when nothing resolved\"\n237:           - frontier_source: \"code_graph | glob_grep_fallback\"\n238:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"frontier_seeded\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"source\":\"{frontier_source}\",\"sliceCount\":\"{frontier_slice_count}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n239: \n240:       step_create_config:\n241:         action: \"Create deep-context-config.json from template (carry the resolved pool + thresholds)\"\n242:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json\n243:         populate:\n244:           scope: \"{scope}\"\n245:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n246:           loopType: \"context\"\n247:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n248:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n249:           # Semantic: per-iteration new-agreement-eligible-findings floor. See convergence.md.\n250:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n251:           stuckThreshold: 2\n252:           maxToolCallsPerIteration: 12\n253:           relevanceGate: \"{relevance_gate}\"\n254:           agreementMin: \"{agreement_min}\"\n255:           fanout.mode: \"by-model-shared-scope\"\n256:           fanout.concurrency: \"{concurrency}\"\n257:           fanout.executors: \"{executor_pool}\"\n258:           report.path: \"context/context-report.md\"\n259:           report.jsonPath: \"context/context-report.json\"\n260:           reducer.enabled: true\n261:           reducer.registryFile: \"context/findings-registry.json\"\n262:           reducer.dashboardFile: \"context/deep-context-dashboard.md\"\n263:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n264:           status: \"initialized\"\n265:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n266:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n267:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n268:           lineage.generation: 1\n269:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n270:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n271: \n272:       step_create_state_log:\n273:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n274:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"scope\":\"{scope}\",\"loopType\":\"context\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"relevanceGate\":{relevance_gate},\"agreementMin\":{agreement_min},\"fanout\":{\"mode\":\"by-model-shared-scope\",\"concurrency\":{concurrency}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n275:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n276: \n277:       step_create_strategy:\n278:         action: \"Create strategy file with the seeded frontier and the executor pool roster\"\n279:         populate:\n280:           scope: \"{scope}\"\n281:           frontier: \"Render frontier_slices_json as the initial focus candidates (ranked SLICE list)\"\n282:           executor_pool: \"Render the pool roster: one row per seat (label, kind, model, promptFramework)\"\n283:           known_context: \"None\"\n284:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n285:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n286:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n287:           relevance_gate: \"{relevance_gate}\"\n288:           agreement_min: \"{agreement_min}\"\n289:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n290: \n291:       step_create_registry:\n292:         action: \"Initialize host-owned findings registry (merged, deduped, agreement-scored)\"\n293:         content: '{\"reuseCandidates\":[],\"integrationPoints\":[],\"conventions\":[],\"dependencies\":[],\"gaps\":[],\"contradictions\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"findings\":0,\"agreementEligible\":0,\"sliceCoverage\":0,\"reuseCatalogCoverage\":0,\"agreementRate\":0,\"relevanceFloor\":0,\"dependencyCompleteness\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0}}'\n294:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n295: \n296:       step_seed_coverage_graph:\n297:         action: \"Seed the coverage graph from the resolved frontier before the first convergence check\"\n298:         transform: |\n299:           1. Convert frontier_slices_json into a deduplicated node batch:\n300:              - SLICE nodes from each ranked frontier slice\n301:              - FILE nodes from every slice path\n302:              - SYMBOL nodes from slice symbol entries when present\n303:              - DEPENDENCY nodes from import/dependency expansion when available\n304:           2. Emit best-effort edges only when both endpoints exist: FILE CONTAINS SYMBOL,\n305:              SYMBOL DEPENDS_ON DEPENDENCY, and FILE IMPORTS FILE.\n306:           3. Bind coverage_seed_source to frontier_source and coverage_seed_confidence to 0.55\n307:              for code_graph, else 0.35 for fallback-derived seeds.\n308:           4. When the frontier is empty, emit [] for both arrays; the upsert script returns\n309:              a warning and the loop continues with an empty graph.\n310:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"context\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n311:         outputs:\n312:           - coverage_seed_nodes_json: \"Seed nodes for SLICE, FILE, SYMBOL, and DEPENDENCY kinds\"\n313:           - coverage_seed_edges_json: \"Seed edges for import/dependency containment where endpoints resolved\"\n314:           - coverage_seed_warning: \"Warning emitted when the seed batch inserts zero nodes, else empty\"\n315:         on_warning:\n316:           log: \"Coverage graph seed inserted zero nodes; continuing with an empty graph.\"\n317:           proceed: true\n318: \n319:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n320:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n321:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n322:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n323:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n324: \n325:       step_init_complete:\n326:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, strategy, registry created; frontier seeded ({frontier_slice_count} slices via {frontier_source}); pool = {pool_summary}.\"\n327:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, prev_agreement_eligible_count: 0, low_progress_streak: 0 }\n328: \n329:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n330:   # PHASE 2: PARALLEL-SWEEP ITERATION LOOP\n331:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n332:   phase_loop:\n333:     purpose: Per iteration, sweep the shared focus with the WHOLE pool in parallel, then merge + converge\n334:     repeat: true\n335:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n336:     steps:\n337: \n338:       step_read_state:\n339:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and registry\"\n340:         read:\n341:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n342:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n344:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n345:         extract:\n346:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n347:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n348:           - current_focus: \"Frontier slice set for this iteration from strategy.md 'Next Focus', else the seeded frontier\"\n349:           - prev_agreement_eligible_count: \"agreementEligible from the previous iteration record, else 0\"\n350:           - new_agreement_eligible_last: \"newAgreementEligible from the latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n351:           - slice_coverage_latest: \"sliceCoverage from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n352:           - reuse_catalog_coverage_latest: \"reuseCatalogCoverage from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n353:           - agreement_rate_latest: \"agreementRate from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n354:           - relevance_floor_latest: \"relevanceFloor from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n355:           - uncovered_slices: \"SLICE nodes without an outgoing COVERED_BY edge (recovery focus candidates)\"\n356:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'iter N: focus (newAgr, agreementRate)'\"\n357:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n358: \n359:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n360:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n361:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n362:         if_exists:\n363:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n364:           message: \"Context loop paused. Delete context/.deep-context-pause to resume.\"\n365:           halt: true\n366:         if_not_exists:\n367:           proceed: true\n368: \n369:       # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n370:       # THE PARALLEL HETEROGENEOUS SWEEP\n371:       # All seats analyze the SAME current_focus. native batch ‖ CLI pool\n372:       # start TOGETHER and barrier-join. Seats are READ-ONLY; they write\n373:       # only their own seats/iter-NNN/{label}.json. The host merges after.\n374:       # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n375:       step_render_seat_prompts:\n376:         action: \"Render ONE prompt per seat for the SHARED current focus, carrying the full lineage contract\"\n377:         ensure_dirs: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration} {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\"\n378:         for_each: \"seat in config.fanout.executors\"\n379:         contract_per_seat: |\n380:           Resolved route: mode=context; target_agent=@deep-context; execution=parallel_read_only_sweep; seat_label={seat.label}; do_not_run_full_loop=true\n\n(Showing lines 1-380 of 840. Use offset=381 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\n# - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\n#   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\n#   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\n# - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\n#   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\n#   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\n#   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n#\n# HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\n# - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\n# - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\n#   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\n#   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\n# - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\n#   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\n#   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\n#   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n#\n# HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\n# - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a\n#   READ-ONLY analyzer that returns structured findings. The HOST (this\n#   workflow) is the ONLY writer of merged state: iteration files,\n#   coverage-graph, dashboard, and the Context Report. This keeps the loop\n#   Gate-3-safe even when CLI seats run with permissive sandboxes.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Context Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative codebase-context gathering via parallel heterogeneous sweeps with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-context loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_context_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh per-iteration sweep + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over ONE shared focus in parallel, merge by agreement, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Seats are read-only analyzers; the host writes ALL merged state. Never hold findings in memory only.\"\n  by_model_shared_scope: \"Every seat sweeps the SAME current focus each iteration. Cross-executor AGREEMENT is the confidence signal — NOT disjoint-slice fan-out.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  scope: \"[SCOPE] - Target feature/area to gather codebase context for. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path (or standalone run dir). REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 8.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Per-iteration new-agreement-eligible-findings floor. Default: 0.10.\"\n  executor_pool: \"[EXECUTOR_POOL] - Shared-scope pool (config.fanout.executors). Default: 2 native (native-only); CLI/combined via --executor/--executors.\"\n  relevance_gate: \"[RELEVANCE_GATE] - Min relevance to keep a finding (else lowConfidence). Default: 0.55 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n  agreement_min: \"[AGREEMENT_MIN] - Min distinct executors for a finding to be agreement-eligible. Default: 2 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n  concurrency: \"[CONCURRENCY] - Max parallel seats in the by-model sweep. Default: 4 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior context for the scope and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{scope}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json\n    report: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/context_report_template.md\n  runtime:\n    coverage_graph_db: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\n    convergence_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs\n    upsert_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs\n    fanout_run_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\n    fanout_merge_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs\n    council_dispatch: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs\n  prompt_framing: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION (native seat)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-context\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-context.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  read_only_analyzer: true\n  tools: [Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query, code_graph_context]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n  note: \"Native seats are READ-ONLY. They return structured findings to the host; they never write merged state.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-state.jsonl\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-seat raw findings for an iteration (one file per seat, host-collected before merge).\n  seat_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/seats\"\n  seat_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/seats/iter-{NNN}/{label}.json\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. Must contain at least one record whose type === \"iteration\".\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  report_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.md\"\n  report_json_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.json\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve the context artifact directory from spec_folder (or standalone run dir)\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep context artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/context/. Child phases keep local packet dirs in {spec_folder}/context/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/context_archive/{packet}/. When no spec folder exists, use a standalone run dir and hand context-report.md to /speckit:plan.\"\n    command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'context')));\\\"\"\n    outputs:\n      - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local context owner directory\"\n      - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n      - artifact_dir: \"Resolved context packet directory for this target\"\n      - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local context archive directory for this target\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files and seed the frontier for the context session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [scope, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, executor_pool]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation). A standalone run dir is allowed ONLY when no spec folder was named in the scope or derivable from it; FAIL closed if a standalone target is bound while the scope named or derived a spec folder (auto_mode_contract §1 fallback guard)\"\n          - pool_non_empty: \"config.fanout.executors has at least one seat (warn when exactly one — no agreement signal)\"\n          - pool_mode: \"config.fanout.mode == 'by-model-shared-scope'\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and context packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir} {state_paths.seat_dir}\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --packet {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-context run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the deep-loop-runtime loop-lock helper (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on scope/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current context packet under the local context_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed context/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-context packet detected. Archive or replace the existing context/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-context state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid context packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_seed_frontier:\n        action: \"Seed the SLICE frontier from the scope BEFORE the first sweep (never a whole-repo sweep)\"\n        instructions: |\n          1. Extract anchors from {scope}: paths, symbols, error strings, domain terms.\n          2. Expand via the System Code Graph: code_graph_query on 2-5 word concept descriptions →\n             blast-radius / calls → ranked SLICE nodes.\n          3. If the code graph is stale or unavailable, fall back to Glob+Grep over the anchors.\n          4. Rank slices by anchor proximity; cap the initial frontier so each iteration's focus\n             is a tractable slice set, not the whole repo.\n        outputs:\n          - frontier_slices_json: \"Ranked SLICE node list (path, symbol, kind, rank), else [] when nothing resolved\"\n          - frontier_source: \"code_graph | glob_grep_fallback\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"frontier_seeded\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"source\":\"{frontier_source}\",\"sliceCount\":\"{frontier_slice_count}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-context-config.json from template (carry the resolved pool + thresholds)\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json\n        populate:\n          scope: \"{scope}\"\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          loopType: \"context\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: per-iteration new-agreement-eligible-findings floor. See convergence.md.\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxToolCallsPerIteration: 12\n          relevanceGate: \"{relevance_gate}\"\n          agreementMin: \"{agreement_min}\"\n          fanout.mode: \"by-model-shared-scope\"\n          fanout.concurrency: \"{concurrency}\"\n          fanout.executors: \"{executor_pool}\"\n          report.path: \"context/context-report.md\"\n          report.jsonPath: \"context/context-report.json\"\n          reducer.enabled: true\n          reducer.registryFile: \"context/findings-registry.json\"\n          reducer.dashboardFile: \"context/deep-context-dashboard.md\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"scope\":\"{scope}\",\"loopType\":\"context\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"relevanceGate\":{relevance_gate},\"agreementMin\":{agreement_min},\"fanout\":{\"mode\":\"by-model-shared-scope\",\"concurrency\":{concurrency}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file with the seeded frontier and the executor pool roster\"\n        populate:\n          scope: \"{scope}\"\n          frontier: \"Render frontier_slices_json as the initial focus candidates (ranked SLICE list)\"\n          executor_pool: \"Render the pool roster: one row per seat (label, kind, model, promptFramework)\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          relevance_gate: \"{relevance_gate}\"\n          agreement_min: \"{agreement_min}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize host-owned findings registry (merged, deduped, agreement-scored)\"\n        content: '{\"reuseCandidates\":[],\"integrationPoints\":[],\"conventions\":[],\"dependencies\":[],\"gaps\":[],\"contradictions\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"findings\":0,\"agreementEligible\":0,\"sliceCoverage\":0,\"reuseCatalogCoverage\":0,\"agreementRate\":0,\"relevanceFloor\":0,\"dependencyCompleteness\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_seed_coverage_graph:\n        action: \"Seed the coverage graph from the resolved frontier before the first convergence check\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Convert frontier_slices_json into a deduplicated node batch:\n             - SLICE nodes from each ranked frontier slice\n             - FILE nodes from every slice path\n             - SYMBOL nodes from slice symbol entries when present\n             - DEPENDENCY nodes from import/dependency expansion when available\n          2. Emit best-effort edges only when both endpoints exist: FILE CONTAINS SYMBOL,\n             SYMBOL DEPENDS_ON DEPENDENCY, and FILE IMPORTS FILE.\n          3. Bind coverage_seed_source to frontier_source and coverage_seed_confidence to 0.55\n             for code_graph, else 0.35 for fallback-derived seeds.\n          4. When the frontier is empty, emit [] for both arrays; the upsert script returns\n             a warning and the loop continues with an empty graph.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"context\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n        outputs:\n          - coverage_seed_nodes_json: \"Seed nodes for SLICE, FILE, SYMBOL, and DEPENDENCY kinds\"\n          - coverage_seed_edges_json: \"Seed edges for import/dependency containment where endpoints resolved\"\n          - coverage_seed_warning: \"Warning emitted when the seed batch inserts zero nodes, else empty\"\n        on_warning:\n          log: \"Coverage graph seed inserted zero nodes; continuing with an empty graph.\"\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, strategy, registry created; frontier seeded ({frontier_slice_count} slices via {frontier_source}); pool = {pool_summary}.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, prev_agreement_eligible_count: 0, low_progress_streak: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: PARALLEL-SWEEP ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Per iteration, sweep the shared focus with the WHOLE pool in parallel, then merge + converge\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and registry\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_focus: \"Frontier slice set for this iteration from strategy.md 'Next Focus', else the seeded frontier\"\n          - prev_agreement_eligible_count: \"agreementEligible from the previous iteration record, else 0\"\n          - new_agreement_eligible_last: \"newAgreementEligible from the latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - slice_coverage_latest: \"sliceCoverage from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n          - reuse_catalog_coverage_latest: \"reuseCatalogCoverage from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n          - agreement_rate_latest: \"agreementRate from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n          - relevance_floor_latest: \"relevanceFloor from latest iteration record, else 0\"\n          - uncovered_slices: \"SLICE nodes without an outgoing COVERED_BY edge (recovery focus candidates)\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'iter N: focus (newAgr, agreementRate)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Context loop paused. Delete context/.deep-context-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n      # THE PARALLEL HETEROGENEOUS SWEEP\n      # All seats analyze the SAME current_focus. native batch ‖ CLI pool\n      # start TOGETHER and barrier-join. Seats are READ-ONLY; they write\n      # only their own seats/iter-NNN/{label}.json. The host merges after.\n      # ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n      step_render_seat_prompts:\n        action: \"Render ONE prompt per seat for the SHARED current focus, carrying the full lineage contract\"\n        ensure_dirs: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir}/iter-{current_iteration} {state_paths.seat_dir}/iter-{current_iteration}\"\n        for_each: \"seat in config.fanout.executors\"\n        contract_per_seat: |\n          Resolved route: mode=context; target_agent=@deep-context; execution=parallel_read_only_sweep; seat_label={seat.label}; do_not_run_full_loop=true","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":380,"totalLines":840,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998469553,"end":1782998469575}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0088aca6b493ec06016a4665c56c608194901ea1fdda71afc9"}},"id":"prt_f22fd8b88001BgCgWkdxP3C0zn","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22fd1c310019eIBNL8Ls4brlt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998469593,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_M1nR81PaiHkGq2Eabz1etaIf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":380},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n102:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n103:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n104:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n105:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n106:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n107:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n108:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n109:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n110:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n111:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n112:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n113:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n114:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n115:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n116:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n117:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n118:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n119:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n120:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n121:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n122: \n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: # WORKFLOW\n125: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n126: workflow:\n127: \n128:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n129:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n130:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n131:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n132:     if_present:\n133:       bind:\n134:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n135:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_subfolder: null\n137:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n138:     if_absent:\n139:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n140:       outputs:\n141:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n142:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n143:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n144:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n145: \n146:   step_fanout_spawn:\n147:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n148:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n149:     instructions: |\n150:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n151:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n152:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n153:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n154:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n155:     sub_steps:\n156:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n157:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n158:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n159:         command: |\n160:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n161:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n162:             --loop-type research \\\n163:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n164:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n165:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n166:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n167:         wait_for_completion: true\n168:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n169:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n170:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n171:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n172:         dispatch:\n173:           agent: deep-research\n174:           model: opus\n175:           context: |\n176:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n177:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n178:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n179:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n180:               executor: native\n181:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n182:         wait_for_completion: true\n183: \n184:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n185:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n186:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n187:   phase_init:\n188:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n189:     steps:\n190: \n191:       step_preflight_contract:\n192:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n193:         verify:\n194:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n195:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n196:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n197:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n198:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n199: \n200:       step_create_directories:\n201:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n202:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n203: \n204:       step_detect_resource_map:\n205:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n206:         inspect:\n207:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n208:         classify:\n209:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n210:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n211:         outputs:\n212:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n213:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n214: \n215:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n216:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n217:         inspect_legacy:\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n221:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n222:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n223:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n224:         on_legacy_read:\n225:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n226: \n227:       step_acquire_lock:\n228:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n229:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n230:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n231:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n232:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n233:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n234:         on_halt:\n235:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n236:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n237:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n238:         on_cancel:\n239:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n240:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n241:         on_workflow_exit:\n242:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n243:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n244: \n245:       step_classify_session:\n246:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n247:         inspect:\n248:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n249:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n250:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n251:         classify:\n252:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n253:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n254:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n255:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n256:         outputs:\n257:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n258:         on_resume:\n259:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n260:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n261:           gate3_classification: write-path\n262:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n263:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: phase_loop\n266:         on_restart:\n267:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n268:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n269:           set:\n270:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n271:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n272:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n273:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n274:           skip_to: step_create_config\n275:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n276:         on_completed_session:\n277:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n278:           halt: true\n279:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n280:         on_invalid_state:\n281:           halt: true\n282:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n283:         on_fresh:\n284:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n285: \n286:       step_create_config:\n287:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n288:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n289:         populate:\n290:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n291:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n292:           minIterations: 3\n293:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n294:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n295:           convergenceMode: \"default\"\n296:           stuckThreshold: 3\n297:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n298:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n299:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n300:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n301:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n302:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n303:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n304:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n305:           status: \"initialized\"\n306:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n307:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n308:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n309:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n310:           lineage.generation: 1\n311:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n312:           nextRunAt: null\n313:           remainingDelayMs: null\n314:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n315: \n316:       step_create_state_log:\n317:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n318:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n319:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n320:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n321: \n322:       step_create_strategy:\n323:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n324:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n325:         populate:\n326:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n327:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n328:           known_context: \"None\"\n329:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n330:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n331:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n332:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n333: \n334:       step_create_registry:\n335:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n336:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n337:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n338: \n339:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n340:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n341:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n342:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n344: \n345:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n346:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n347:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n348:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n349: \n350:       step_detect_spec_present:\n351:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n352:         inspect:\n353:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n354:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n355:         classify:\n356:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n357:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n358:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n359:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n360:         outputs:\n361:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n362:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n363:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n364: \n365:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n366:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n367:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n368:         branches:\n369:           no-spec:\n370:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n371:             seed_markers:\n372:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n373:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n374:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n375:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n376:             set:\n377:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n378:               validate_spec_doc: true\n379:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n380:           spec-present:\n\n(Showing lines 1-380 of 1655. Use offset=381 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          convergenceMode: \"default\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":380,"totalLines":1655,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998469557,"end":1782998469591}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0088aca6b493ec06016a4665c56c7081949970562abb7c06c5"}},"id":"prt_f22fd8bb2001C2oUqQjueWudzL","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f22fd1c310019eIBNL8Ls4brlt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998469596,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_AJ8NVPOoAFwS08OZ1lbJr4kt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"AUTO_SESSION_ID|session_id|sessionId|lineage.sessionId|config.lineage.sessionId","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets","include":"deep_{context,research}_auto.yaml"},"output":"Found 53 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml:\n  Line 204:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n\n  Line 205:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  Line 208:           action: \"Archive the current context packet under the local context_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n\n  Line 212:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n\n  Line 214:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  Line 265:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n  Line 310:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"context\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{coverage_seed_nodes_json}' --edges '{coverage_seed_edges_json}' --seed-source \\\"{coverage_seed_source}\\\" --seed-confidence \\\"{coverage_seed_confidence}\\\"\"\n\n  Line 363:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n  Line 494:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"sweep_settled\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"focusSliceCount\":\"{current_focus_slice_count}\",\"seatsSucceeded\":{seats_succeeded_json},\"seatsFailed\":{seats_failed_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n  Line 533:           record: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"context\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-context\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=context target_agent=deep-context\",\"status\":\"evidence\",\"focus\":\"{current_focus_label}\",\"findingsCount\":{merged_findings_count},\"newAgreementEligible\":{new_agreement_eligible_count},\"agreementEligible\":{cumulative_agreement_eligible_count},\"sliceCoverage\":{slice_coverage},\"reuseCatalogCoverage\":{reuse_catalog_coverage},\"agreementRate\":{agreement_rate},\"relevanceFloor\":{relevance_floor},\"dependencyCompleteness\":{dependency_completeness},\"contradictions\":{contradictions_count},\"seatsSucceeded\":{seats_succeeded_count},\"durationMs\":{sweep_duration_ms},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n  Line 566:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"context\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_js