mmand/action evidence and exit status, (4) confirm scope and residue checks, (5) document confidence level, and only then send the RETURN.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:\n  Line 34: **Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n\n  Line 51: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n  Line 57: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n  Line 189: **Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n\n  Line 543: | Inflate newInfoRatio | Delays convergence, wastes iterations | Calculate honestly from actual findings |\n\n  Line 548: | Hide contradictions | Makes convergence look cleaner than evidence supports | Cite both sides and mark unresolved conflicts honestly |\n\n  Line 565: │  ├─► Append exactly one iteration record for convergence detection      │\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/.goal-state/736d6f6b652d73657373696f6e2d31373832383939303735373237.json:\n  Line 2:   \"sessionId\": \"smoke-session-1782899075727\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/.goal-state/7365735f30646538303366626566666559744b56357057565a367a714e31.json:\n  Line 2:   \"sessionId\": \"ses_0de803fbeffeYtKV5pWVZ6zqN1\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/ai-council.md:\n  Line 49: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n  Line 91: 6. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Score each seat using the 5-dimension planning rubric (see §6 Synthesis Protocol), identify agreements, isolate disagreements, and detect convergence bias.\n\n  Line 151: | Research | 0.2 | Evidence gathering, source validation, unknown reduction | Ambiguous requirements, external facts |\n\n  Line 170: 4. **Output diversity**: if two seats return essentially the same plan, run cross-critique to decide whether convergence is real or artificial.\n\n  Line 218: Never increase N above 3 to simulate consensus. If more than three vantage points matter, stage them in the plan as follow-up validation instead of dispatching an oversized council.\n\n  Line 346: 6. **Compose the unified plan** with attribution, prerequisites, validation steps, and risk mitigations.\n\n  Line 350: **Purpose:** Counter convergence bias and shallow consensus. The council should seek genuine disagreement before concluding that a plan is strong.\n\n  Line 368: - If all seats score within 5 points and propose essentially the same plan, flag potential convergence sycophancy.\n\n  Line 370: - If convergence is genuine, note the shared evidence. If artificial, re-run the weakest seat with stronger contrarian framing or report insufficient diversity.\n\n  Line 614: | **Strategy Overload** | >3 seats creates noise, not signal | Max 3. More seats are staged as follow-up validation |\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"fanout|fan-out|sessionId|session_id|artifact_dir|resolveArtifactRoot|convergence|sliding|maxIterations|stopPolicy|validation","time":{"start":1782998760587,"end":1782998760633}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e438a055f929dd2016a4666e86cec819190000115d30d46bd"}},"id":"prt_f2301fc88001nSA3r3wmvQ5wYu","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f2301c6e0001PTPVGcU53VUqMi"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998760664,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"call_NcLxd0VimPcY1IuwuEu6QGYJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":".opencode/specs/deep-loops/030-agent-loops-improved/review/lineages/gpt/**","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"No files found","metadata":{"count":0,"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1782998760544,"end":1782998760663}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e438a055f929dd2016a4666e86cd08191a4e3025f2abe0364"}},"id":"prt_f2301fc2c001tre0qSGkzFKJLC","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f2301c6e0001PTPVGcU53VUqMi"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782998761033,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f2301fe47001Cp7yD0DLL71FpU","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","messageID":"msg_f2301c6e0001PTPVGcU53VUqMi","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":35588,"input":960,"output":324,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":34304}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782998762686,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"id":"prt_f230204bd001gg17QdIYSCE0p7","messageID":"msg_f2301ffd8001NrRk2YQyRqu0ox","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","snapshot":"6d9a7e5dacbf04e2a0140385843ff24f912f6687","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998776384,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BFDA2TNywEmNOP0hwY62ZQVt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   session_id: \"[SESSION_ID] - Optional caller-supplied session id for fan-out lineages. Default: timestamp.\"\n34:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n35:   max_iterations: 7\n36:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n37:   stop_policy: \"[convergence|max-iterations] - Stop behavior. Default: convergence. max-iterations treats convergence as telemetry until the hard iteration ceiling.\"\n38:   config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: \"[optional internal path] - Fan-out lineage artifact override for command-owned single-lineage execution.\"\n39: \n40: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n41: # CONTEXT LOADING\n42: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n43: context_loading:\n44:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n45:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n46:   mcp_integration:\n47:     tool: memory_context\n48:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n49:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n50:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n51:   behavior:\n52:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n53:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n54: \n55: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n56: # SKILL REFERENCE\n57: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n58: skill_reference:\n59:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n60:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n61:   references:\n62:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n63:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n64:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n65:   templates:\n66:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n67:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n68: \n69: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n70: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n71: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n72: agent_config:\n73:   agent: deep-review\n74:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n75:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n76:   mode: subagent\n77:   model: opus\n78:   leaf_only: true\n79:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n80:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n81:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n82: \n83: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n84: # STATE FILE PATHS\n85: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n86: state_paths:\n87:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n88:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n89:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n90:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n91:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n92:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n93:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n94:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n95:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n96:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n97:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n98:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n99:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n100:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n101:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n102:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n103:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n104:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n105:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n106:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n107:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n108:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n109:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n110:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n111:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n112:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n113: \n114: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n115: # WORKFLOW\n116: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n117: workflow:\n118: \n119:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n120:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n121:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n122:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n123:     if_present:\n124:       bind:\n125:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n126:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n127:         artifact_subfolder: null\n128:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n129:     if_absent:\n130:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n131:       outputs:\n132:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n133:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n134:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n135:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n136: \n137:   step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n138:     description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n139:     skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n140:     instructions: |\n141:       This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n142:       immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n143:       cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n144:       fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n145:       authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n146:       second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n147:       the packet directory.\n148:     command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n149:     outputs:\n150:       - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n151:       - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n152:     on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n153: \n154:   step_fanout_spawn:\n155:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n156:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n157:     instructions: |\n158:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n159:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n160:       A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n161:       session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n162:       self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n163:       first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n164:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n165:       deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n166:       deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n167:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n168:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n169:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n170:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n171:     sub_steps:\n172:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n173:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n174:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n175:         command: |\n176:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n177:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n178:             --loop-type review \\\n179:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n180:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n181:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n182:             --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n183:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n184:         wait_for_completion: true\n185: \n186:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n187:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n188:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n189:   phase_init:\n190:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n191:     steps:\n192: \n193:       step_preflight_contract:\n194:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n195:         verify:\n196:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, stop_policy]\n197:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n198:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n199:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n200:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n201: \n202:       step_create_directories:\n203:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n204:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n205: \n206:       step_detect_resource_map:\n207:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n208:         inspect:\n209:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n210:         classify:\n211:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n212:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n213:         outputs:\n214:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n215:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n216: \n217:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n218:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n219:         detect:\n220:           canonical_review_state:\n221:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n222:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n223:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n224:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n225:           legacy_review_state:\n226:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n227:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n228:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n229:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n230:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n231:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n232:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n233:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n234:           legacy_review_markers:\n235:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n236:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n237:         migrate_only:\n238:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n239:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n240:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n241:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n242:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n243:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n244:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n245:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n246:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n247:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n248:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n249:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n250: \n251:       step_acquire_lock:\n252:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n253:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n254:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n255:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n256:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n257:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n258:         on_halt:\n259:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n260:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 1603. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the dispatch-context check before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (dispatch-context check) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: DISPATCH-CONTEXT CHECK\n\n**STATUS: ☐ CHECKED**\n\n```\nThis gate checks actual dispatch context, not self-reported capability -- the prior\nself-assessment version of this check produced a confirmed false-positive block (a\ncapable agent judged itself \"uncertain\" on an abstract question and hard-stopped).\n\nCHECK: was this file invoked directly as /deep:context (typed by the user, or an\nexplicit Task delegation naming this exact command) -- as opposed to another agent\npasting this file's raw content into a Task-dispatch prompt as inline ad hoc\ninstructions for a worker to follow (that worker should follow its own dispatch\nprompt, not re-run this command's full setup contract)?\n\n├─ YES, or no concrete evidence of the pasted-inline case:\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ NO, with concrete evidence this file's content was pasted inline rather than\n   invoked as the command itself:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ DIRECT INVOCATION REQUIRED                              │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:context [arguments]                                │\n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Must be invoked directly, not pasted as inline sub-agent instructions\"\n\nDefault on ambiguity: PROCEED. Do not block on an inability to introspect abstract\ncapability (e.g. \"can I orchestrate a workflow\") -- that question is unanswerable\nfrom the inside and is what caused the original false-positive block. Block only on\nconcrete evidence of the pasted-inline case above.\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  session_id: \"[SESSION_ID] - Optional caller-supplied session id for fan-out lineages. Default: timestamp.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n  stop_policy: \"[convergence|max-iterations] - Stop behavior. Default: convergence. max-iterations treats convergence as telemetry until the hard iteration ceiling.\"\n  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: \"[optional internal path] - Fan-out lineage artifact override for command-owned single-lineage execution.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n    description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n    skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n    instructions: |\n      This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n      immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n      cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n      fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n      authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n      second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n      the packet directory.\n    command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n    outputs:\n      - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n      - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n    on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n      session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n      self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n      first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n            --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, stop_policy]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":1603,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998776379,"end":1782998776383}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_006743334b9993a8016a4666f855ec8191ab11a3df6a088784"}},"id":"prt_f23023a2c001WvKv1SNgX4fJAe","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f2301ffd8001NrRk2YQyRqu0ox"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998776468,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_zp1NSxhF6KcsU3CdbtIPtxQ4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\n5: # - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\n6: #   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\n9: #   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\n10: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n11: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n12: #\n13: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\n14: # - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\n15: #   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\n16: #   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\n17: #   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n18: #\n19: # HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\n20: # - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a\n21: #   READ-ONLY analyzer that returns structured findings. The HOST (this\n22: #   workflow) is the ONLY writer of merged state: iteration files,\n23: #   coverage-graph, dashboard, and the Context Report. This keeps the loop\n24: #   Gate-3-safe even when CLI seats run with permissive sandboxes.\n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: role: Deep Context Loop Manager\n27: purpose: Iterative codebase-context gathering via parallel heterogeneous sweeps with convergence detection\n28: action: Run deep-context loop from initialization through synthesis\n29: operating_mode:\n30:   workflow: iterative_loop\n31:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n32:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n33:   approvals: none\n34:   tracking: progressive_context_state\n35:   validation: convergence_detection\n36: \n37: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n38: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: operating_principles:\n41:   core: \"Fresh per-iteration sweep + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n42:   approach: \"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over ONE shared focus in parallel, merge by agreement, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n43:   mandate: \"Seats are read-only analyzers; the host writes ALL merged state. Never hold findings in memory only.\"\n44:   by_model_shared_scope: \"Every seat sweeps the SAME current focus each iteration. Cross-executor AGREEMENT is the confidence signal — NOT disjoint-slice fan-out.\"\n45: \n46: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n47: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: user_inputs:\n50:   scope: \"[SCOPE] - Target feature/area to gather codebase context for. REQUIRED.\"\n51:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path (or standalone run dir). REQUIRED.\"\n52:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 8.\"\n53:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Per-iteration new-agreement-eligible-findings floor. Default: 0.10.\"\n54:   executor_pool: \"[EXECUTOR_POOL] - Shared-scope pool (config.fanout.executors). Default: 2 native (native-only); CLI/combined via --executor/--executors.\"\n55:   relevance_gate: \"[RELEVANCE_GATE] - Min relevance to keep a finding (else lowConfidence). Default: 0.55 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n56:   agreement_min: \"[AGREEMENT_MIN] - Min distinct executors for a finding to be agreement-eligible. Default: 2 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n57:   concurrency: \"[CONCURRENCY] - Max parallel seats in the by-model sweep. Default: 4 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n58: \n59: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n60: # CONTEXT LOADING\n61: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n62: context_loading:\n63:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n64:   purpose: \"Load prior context for the scope and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n65:   mcp_integration:\n66:     tool: memory_context\n67:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n68:     parameters: { input: \"{scope}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n69:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n70:   behavior:\n71:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n72:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n73: \n74: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n75: # SKILL REFERENCE\n76: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n77: skill_reference:\n78:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n79:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md\n80:   references:\n81:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n82:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/convergence/convergence.md\n83:   templates:\n84:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json\n85:     report: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/context_report_template.md\n86:   runtime:\n87:     coverage_graph_db: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\n88:     convergence_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs\n89:     upsert_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs\n90:     fanout_run_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\n91:     fanout_merge_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs\n92:     council_dispatch: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs\n93:   prompt_framing: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md\n94: \n95: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n96: # AGENT CONFIGURATION (native seat)\n97: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n98: agent_config:\n99:   agent: deep-context\n100:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-context.md\"\n101:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n102:   model: opus\n103:   leaf_only: true\n104:   read_only_analyzer: true\n105:   tools: [Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query, code_graph_context]\n106:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n107:   note: \"Native seats are READ-ONLY. They return structured findings to the host; they never write merged state.\"\n108: \n109: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n110: # STATE FILE PATHS\n111: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n112: state_paths:\n113:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n114:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-config.json\"\n115:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-state.jsonl\"\n116:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-strategy.md\"\n117:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n118:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-dashboard.md\"\n119:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context-pause\"\n120:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context.lock\"\n121:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n122:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n123:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n124:   # Per-seat raw findings for an iteration (one file per seat, host-collected before merge).\n125:   seat_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/seats\"\n126:   seat_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/seats/iter-{NNN}/{label}.json\"\n127:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n128:   # canonical state_log append. Must contain at least one record whose type === \"iteration\".\n129:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n130:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n131:   report_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.md\"\n132:   report_json_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.json\"\n133:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n134: \n135: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n136: # WORKFLOW\n137: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n138: workflow:\n139: \n140:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n141:     description: \"Resolve the context artifact directory from spec_folder (or standalone run dir)\"\n142:     note: \"Root specs keep context artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/context/. Child phases keep local packet dirs in {spec_folder}/context/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/context_archive/{packet}/. When no spec folder exists, use a standalone run dir and hand context-report.md to /speckit:plan.\"\n143:     command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'context')));\\\"\"\n144:     outputs:\n145:       - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local context owner directory\"\n146:       - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n147:       - artifact_dir: \"Resolved context packet directory for this target\"\n148:       - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local context archive directory for this target\"\n149: \n150:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n151:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n152:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n153:   phase_init:\n154:     purpose: Create all state files and seed the frontier for the context session\n155:     steps:\n156: \n157:       step_preflight_contract:\n158:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n159:         verify:\n160:           - required_values_present: [scope, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, executor_pool]\n161:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation). A standalone run dir is allowed ONLY when no spec folder was named in the scope or derivable from it; FAIL closed if a standalone target is bound while the scope named or derived a spec folder (auto_mode_contract §1 fallback guard)\"\n162:           - pool_non_empty: \"config.fanout.executors has at least one seat (warn when exactly one — no agreement signal)\"\n163:           - pool_mode: \"config.fanout.mode == 'by-model-shared-scope'\"\n164:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n165:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n166:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n167: \n168:       step_create_directories:\n169:         action: \"Create spec folder and context packet directories if they don't exist\"\n170:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir} {state_paths.seat_dir}\"\n171: \n172:       step_acquire_lock:\n173:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n174:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --packet {spec_folder}\"\n175:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-context run already holds this packet.\"\n176:         note: \"Uses the deep-loop-runtime loop-lock helper (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n177:         on_halt:\n178:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n179:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n180:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n181:         on_cancel:\n182:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n183:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n184:         on_workflow_exit:\n185:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n186:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n187: \n188:       step_classify_session:\n189:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n190:         inspect:\n191:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n192:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n193:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n194:         classify:\n195:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n196:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on scope/spec folder\"\n197:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n198:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n199:         outputs:\n200:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n201:         on_resume:\n202:           gate3_classification: write-path\n203:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n204:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n205:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n206:           skip_to: phase_loop\n207:         on_restart:\n208:           action: \"Archive the current context packet under the local context_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n209:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n210:           set:\n211:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n212:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n213:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n214:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n215:           skip_to: step_create_config\n216:         on_completed_session:\n217:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed context/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n218:           halt: true\n219:           message: \"Completed deep-context packet detected. Archive or replace the existing context/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n220:         on_invalid_state:\n\n(Showing lines 1-220 of 840. Use offset=221 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\n# - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\n#   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\n#   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\n# - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\n#   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\n#   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\n#   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n#\n# HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\n# - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\n# - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\n#   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\n#   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\n# - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\n#   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\n#   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\n#   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n#\n# HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\n# - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a\n#   READ-ONLY analyzer that returns structured findings. The HOST (this\n#   workflow) is the ONLY writer of merged state: iteration files,\n#   coverage-graph, dashboard, and the Context Report. This keeps the loop\n#   Gate-3-safe even when CLI seats run with permissive sandboxes.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Context Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative codebase-context gathering via parallel heterogeneous sweeps with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-context loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_context_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh per-iteration sweep + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over ONE shared focus in parallel, merge by agreement, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Seats are read-only analyzers; the host writes ALL merged state. Never hold findings in memory only.\"\n  by_model_shared_scope: \"Every seat sweeps the SAME current focus each iteration. Cross-executor AGREEMENT is the confidence signal — NOT disjoint-slice fan-out.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  scope: \"[SCOPE] - Target feature/area to gather codebase context for. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path (or standalone run dir). REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 8.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Per-iteration new-agreement-eligible-findings floor. Default: 0.10.\"\n  executor_pool: \"[EXECUTOR_POOL] - Shared-scope pool (config.fanout.executors). Default: 2 native (native-only); CLI/combined via --executor/--executors.\"\n  relevance_gate: \"[RELEVANCE_GATE] - Min relevance to keep a finding (else lowConfidence). Default: 0.55 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n  agreement_min: \"[AGREEMENT_MIN] - Min distinct executors for a finding to be agreement-eligible. Default: 2 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n  concurrency: \"[CONCURRENCY] - Max parallel seats in the by-model sweep. Default: 4 (deep_context_config.json).\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior context for the scope and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{scope}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json\n    report: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/assets/context_report_template.md\n  runtime:\n    coverage_graph_db: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts\n    convergence_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs\n    upsert_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs\n    fanout_run_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs\n    fanout_merge_script: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs\n    council_dispatch: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs\n  prompt_framing: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION (native seat)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-context\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-context.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  read_only_analyzer: true\n  tools: [Read, Grep, Glob, code_graph_query, code_graph_context]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n  note: \"Native seats are READ-ONLY. They return structured findings to the host; they never write merged state.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-state.jsonl\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-context-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-context.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-seat raw findings for an iteration (one file per seat, host-collected before merge).\n  seat_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/seats\"\n  seat_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/seats/iter-{NNN}/{label}.json\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. Must contain at least one record whose type === \"iteration\".\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  report_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.md\"\n  report_json_output: \"{artifact_dir}/context-report.json\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve the context artifact directory from spec_folder (or standalone run dir)\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep context artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/context/. Child phases keep local packet dirs in {spec_folder}/context/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/context_archive/{packet}/. When no spec folder exists, use a standalone run dir and hand context-report.md to /speckit:plan.\"\n    command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'context')));\\\"\"\n    outputs:\n      - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local context owner directory\"\n      - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n      - artifact_dir: \"Resolved context packet directory for this target\"\n      - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local context archive directory for this target\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files and seed the frontier for the context session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [scope, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, executor_pool]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation). A standalone run dir is allowed ONLY when no spec folder was named in the scope or derivable from it; FAIL closed if a standalone target is bound while the scope named or derived a spec folder (auto_mode_contract §1 fallback guard)\"\n          - pool_non_empty: \"config.fanout.executors has at least one seat (warn when exactly one — no agreement signal)\"\n          - pool_mode: \"config.fanout.mode == 'by-model-shared-scope'\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and context packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir} {state_paths.seat_dir}\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --packet {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-context run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the deep-loop-runtime loop-lock helper (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock {state_paths.lock_file} --owner {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on scope/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current context packet under the local context_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"context\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed context/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-context packet detected. Archive or replace the existing context/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":220,"totalLines":840,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998776459,"end":1782998776467}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_006743334b9993a8016a4666f856008191946ef4ce9551bb01"}},"id":"prt_f23023a550012XgZaINygEyAbs","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f2301ffd8001NrRk2YQyRqu0ox"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998776476,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0FquTvM3HtNK7VDPXCgVQhwc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n102:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n103:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n104:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n105:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n106:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n107:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n108:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n109:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n110:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n111:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n112:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n113:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n114:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n115:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n116:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n117:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n118:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n119:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n120:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n121:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n122: \n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: # WORKFLOW\n125: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n126: workflow:\n127: \n128:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n129:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n130:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n131:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n132:     if_present:\n133:       bind:\n134:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n135:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_subfolder: null\n137:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n138:     if_absent:\n139:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n140:       outputs:\n141:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n142:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n143:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n144:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n145: \n146:   step_fanout_spawn:\n147:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n148:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n149:     instructions: |\n150:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n151:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n152:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n153:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n154:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n155:     sub_steps:\n156:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n157:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n158:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n159:         command: |\n160:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n161:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n162:             --loop-type research \\\n163:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n164:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n165:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n166:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n167:         wait_for_completion: true\n168:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n169:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n170:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n171:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n172:         dispatch:\n173:           agent: deep-research\n174:           model: opus\n175:           context: |\n176:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n177:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n178:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n179:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n180:               executor: native\n181:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n182:         wait_for_completion: true\n183: \n184:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n185:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n186:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n187:   phase_init:\n188:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n189:     steps:\n190: \n191:       step_preflight_contract:\n192:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n193:         verify:\n194:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n195:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n196:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n197:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n198:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n199: \n200:       step_create_directories:\n201:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n202:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n203: \n204:       step_detect_resource_map:\n205:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n206:         inspect:\n207:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n208:         classify:\n209:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n210:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n211:         outputs:\n212:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n213:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n214: \n215:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n216:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n217:         inspect_legacy:\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n221:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n222:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n223:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n224:         on_legacy_read:\n225:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n226: \n227:       step_acquire_lock:\n228:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n229:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n230:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n231:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n232:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n233:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n234:         on_halt:\n235:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n236:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n237:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n238:         on_cancel:\n239:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n240:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 1655. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":1655,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1782998776471,"end":1782998776474}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_006743334b9993a8016a4666f85608819198012f4066023b82"}},"id":"prt_f23023a8d001df12gd8fJUIesQ","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f2301ffd8001NrRk2YQyRqu0ox"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782998776491,"sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fj0uGCPnG3GyfqUQSYYhTper","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: \n3: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n4: // ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n5: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n6: // ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n7: // ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n8: // ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n9: // ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n10: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n11: \n12: 'use strict';\n13: \n14: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n15: // 1. IMPORTS\n16: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n17: \n18: const fs = require('node:fs');\n19: const os = require('node:os');\n20: const path = require('node:path');\n21: const { spawn } = require('node:child_process');\n22: \n23: const {\n24:   classifyExitCode,\n25:   maybeThrowTestFault,\n26:   validateNamespaceValue,\n27: } = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n28: \n29: const {\n30:   runCappedPool,\n31:   appendStatusLedger,\n32:   markOrphanedLineages,\n33:   readRetryCountsFromLedger,\n34:   createWavePlannerInterface,\n35:   writeOrchestrationSummary,\n36: } = require('./fanout-pool.cjs');\n37: \n38: const {\n39:   runSalvageSweep,\n40:   extractTextFromOpencodeJson,\n41: } = require('./fanout-salvage.cjs');\n42: \n43: const {\n44:   appendObservabilityEvent,\n45: } = require('../lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs');\n46: \n47: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n48: // 2. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n49: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n50: \n51: const TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\n52: const isTsxLoaded = process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED === '1';\n53: \n54: function runTsxBootstrap() {\n55:   const child = spawn(\n56:     process.execPath,\n57:     ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n58:     {\n59:       cwd: process.cwd(),\n60:       env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n61:       stdio: [process.stdin.isTTY ? 'ignore' : 'pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n62:     },\n63:   );\n64: \n65:   if (!process.stdin.isTTY && child.stdin) {\n66:     child.stdin.on('error', () => {});\n67:     process.stdin.pipe(child.stdin);\n68:   }\n69: \n70:   child.stdout?.pipe(process.stdout);\n71:   child.stderr?.pipe(process.stderr);\n72: \n73:   for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n74:     process.once(signal, () => {\n75:       child.kill(signal);\n76:     });\n77:   }\n78: \n79:   child.on('close', (status, signal) => {\n80:     if (status !== null) {\n81:       process.exit(status);\n82:     }\n83:     process.exit(signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : signal === 'SIGTERM' ? 143 : 1);\n84:   });\n85: }\n86: \n87: if (require.main === module && !isTsxLoaded) {\n88:   runTsxBootstrap();\n89: }\n90: \n91: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: // 3. HELPERS\n93: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: \n95: function parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n96:   const args = {};\n97:   for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n98:     const token = argv[i];\n99:     if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n100:       throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n101:     }\n102:     const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n103:     const next = argv[i + 1];\n104:     if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n105:       args[key] = true;\n106:     } else {\n107:       args[key] = next;\n108:       i += 1;\n109:     }\n110:   }\n111:   return args;\n112: }\n113: \n114: function inputError(message) {\n115:   const err = new Error(message);\n116:   err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n117:   return err;\n118: }\n119: \n120: function ensureString(args, key) {\n121:   if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n122:     throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n123:   }\n124:   return args[key];\n125: }\n126: \n127: function parseOptionalNumber(args, key) {\n128:   const raw = args[key];\n129:   if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n130:     return null;\n131:   }\n132:   if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n133:     throw inputError(`${key} must be a number`);\n134:   }\n135:   const value = Number(raw);\n136:   if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n137:     throw inputError(`${key} must be a non-negative number`);\n138:   }\n139:   return value;\n140: }\n141: \n142: function readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName) {\n143:   if (!isRecord(rawConfig)) return null;\n144:   for (const name of names) {\n145:     if (!Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(rawConfig, name)) continue;\n146:     const raw = rawConfig[name];\n147:     if (raw === undefined || raw === null || raw === '') return null;\n148:     if (raw === true || raw === false) {\n149:       throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n150:     }\n151:     const value = Number(raw);\n152:     if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n153:       throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n154:     }\n155:     return Math.floor(value);\n156:   }\n157:   return null;\n158: }\n159: \n160: function readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName, fallback) {\n161:   const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName);\n162:   if (value === null) return fallback;\n163:   if (value <= 0) {\n164:     throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be greater than 0`);\n165:   }\n166:   return value;\n167: }\n168: \n169: function rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args) {\n170:   const merged = { ...(isRecord(rawConfig) ? rawConfig : {}) };\n171:   const mappings = [\n172:     ['stallWatchdogMs', 'stallWatchdogMs'],\n173:     ['maxCostUnitsPerLineage', 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage'],\n174:     ['maxTokensPerLineage', 'maxTokensPerLineage'],\n175:     ['maxTokenBudget', 'maxTokenBudget'],\n176:     ['maxTokenBudgetPerLineage', 'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage'],\n177:     ['costUnitsPerIteration', 'costUnitsPerIteration'],\n178:     ['estimatedTokensPerIteration', 'estimatedTokensPerIteration'],\n179:   ];\n180:   for (const [targetKey, argKey] of mappings) {\n181:     if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(args, argKey)) {\n182:       merged[targetKey] = args[argKey];\n183:     }\n184:   }\n185:   return merged;\n186: }\n187: \n188: function normalizeStopPolicy(raw) {\n189:   if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n190:     return 'convergence';\n191:   }\n192:   if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n193:     throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n194:   }\n195:   if (raw !== 'convergence' && raw !== 'max-iterations') {\n196:     throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n197:   }\n198:   return raw;\n199: }\n200: \n201: function jsonOut(payload) {\n202:   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n203: }\n204: \n205: function signalExitCode(signal) {\n206:   return signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : 143;\n207: }\n208: \n209: let fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = false;\n210: \n211: function installFanoutSignalHandlers(onStop) {\n212:   if (fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled) return;\n213:   fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = true;\n214: \n215:   for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n216:     process.once(signal, () => {\n217:       try {\n218:         onStop(signal);\n219:       } finally {\n220:         process.exit(signalExitCode(signal));\n221:       }\n222:     });\n223:   }\n224: }\n225: \n226: function updateLineageSnapshot(snapshots, event) {\n227:   if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return;\n228:   const existing = snapshots.get(event.label) || { label: event.label };\n229: \n230:   if (event.event === 'started') {\n231:     snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'running', started_at_iso: event.at });\n232:     return;\n233:   }\n234:   if (event.event === 'completed') {\n235:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n236:       ...existing,\n237:       status: 'fulfilled',\n238:       completed_at_iso: event.at,\n239:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n240:     });\n241:     return;\n242:   }\n243:   if (event.event === 'failed') {\n244:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n245:       ...existing,\n246:       status: event.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'rejected',\n247:       completed_at_iso: event.at,\n248:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n249:       error: event.error,\n250:     });\n251:     return;\n252:   }\n253:   if (event.event === 'retry_scheduled' || event.event === 'orphan_requeued') {\n254:     snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'requeued', updated_at_iso: event.at });\n255:     return;\n256:   }\n257:   if (event.event === 'progress') {\n258:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n259:       ...existing,\n260:       status: 'running',\n261:       updated_at_iso: event.at,\n262:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n263:     });\n264:   }\n265: }\n266: \n267: function buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n268:   return lineages.map((lineage) => snapshots.get(lineage.label) || { label: lineage.label, status: 'pending' });\n269: }\n270: \n271: function summarizeSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n272:   const results = buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots);\n273:   const succeeded = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'fulfilled').length;\n274:   const failed = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'rejected').length;\n275:   return {\n276:     results,\n277:     summary: {\n278:       total: lineages.length,\n279:       succeeded,\n280:       failed,\n281:       all_failed: lineages.length > 0 && failed === lineages.length,\n282:     },\n283:   };\n284: }\n285: \n286: function observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath) {\n287:   return path.join(path.dirname(ledgerPath), OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME);\n288: }\n289: \n290: function statusForLedgerEvent(entry) {\n291:   if (entry && typeof entry.status === 'string' && entry.status.trim() !== '') {\n292:     return entry.status;\n293:   }\n294:   if (!entry || typeof entry.event !== 'string') return 'unknown';\n295:   if (entry.event === 'started' || entry.event === 'progress' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting') return 'running';\n296:   if (entry.event === 'completed' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting_complete') return 'completed';\n297:   if (entry.event === 'failed') return entry.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'failed';\n298:   if (entry.event === 'stopped') return 'stopped';\n299:   if (entry.event === 'retry_scheduled' || entry.event === 'orphan_requeued') return 'retrying';\n300:   // Lag-ceiling signals from the pool: a stall warning while work remains pending, or a\n301:   // forced abort of the stalled attempt. Map both to typed statuses instead of 'unknown'.\n302:   if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_exceeded') return entry.action === 'abort' ? 'failed' : 'warning';\n303:   if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_abort') return 'failed';\n304:   if (entry.event === 'stall_detected') return 'warning';\n305:   if (entry.event === 'budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n306:   return 'unknown';\n307: }\n308: \n309: function appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry) {\n310:   appendStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry);\n311:   try {\n312:     appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath), entry, {\n313:       producer: 'fanout-run',\n314:       stream: 'orchestration-status',\n315:       subject: {\n316:         run_id: entry.run_id ?? null,\n317:         label: entry.label ?? null,\n318:         loop_type: entry.loop_type ?? null,\n319:         spec_folder: entry.spec_folder ?? null,\n320:       },\n\n(Showing lines 1-320 of 1747. Use offset=321 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n// ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst os = require('node:os');\nconst path = require('node:path');","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n// ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst os = require('node:os');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { spawn } = require('node:child_process');\n\nconst {\n  classifyExitCode,\n  maybeThrowTestFault,\n  validateNamespaceValue,\n} = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  runCappedPool,\n  appendStatusLedger,\n  markOrphanedLineages,\n  readRetryCountsFromLedger,\n  createWavePlannerInterface,\n  writeOrchestrationSummary,\n} = require('./fanout-pool.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  runSalvageSweep,\n  extractTextFromOpencodeJson,\n} = require('./fanout-salvage.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  appendObservabilityEvent,\n} = require('../lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\nconst isTsxLoaded = process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED === '1';\n\nfunction runTsxBootstrap() {\n  const child = spawn(\n    process.execPath,\n    ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n    {\n      cwd: process.cwd(),\n      env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n      stdio: [process.stdin.isTTY ? 'ignore' : 'pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n    },\n  );\n\n  if (!process.stdin.isTTY && child.stdin) {\n    child.stdin.on('error', () => {});\n    process.stdin.pipe(child.stdin);\n  }\n\n  child.stdout?.pipe(process.stdout);\n  child.stderr?.pipe(process.stderr);\n\n  for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n    process.once(signal, () => {\n      child.kill(signal);\n    });\n  }\n\n  child.on('close', (status, signal) => {\n    if (status !== null) {\n      process.exit(status);\n    }\n    process.exit(signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : signal === 'SIGTERM' ? 143 : 1);\n  });\n}\n\nif (require.main === module && !isTsxLoaded) {\n  runTsxBootstrap();\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n  const args = {};\n  for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n    const token = argv[i];\n    if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n      throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n    }\n    const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n    const next = argv[i + 1];\n    if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n      args[key] = true;\n    } else {\n      args[key] = next;\n      i += 1;\n    }\n  }\n  return args;\n}\n\nfunction inputError(message) {\n  const err = new Error(message);\n  err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n  return err;\n}\n\nfunction ensureString(args, key) {\n  if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n  }\n  return args[key];\n}\n\nfunction parseOptionalNumber(args, key) {\n  const raw = args[key];\n  if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n    return null;\n  }\n  if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} must be a number`);\n  }\n  const value = Number(raw);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n    throw inputError(`${key} must be a non-negative number`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName) {\n  if (!isRecord(rawConfig)) return null;\n  for (const name of names) {\n    if (!Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(rawConfig, name)) continue;\n    const raw = rawConfig[name];\n    if (raw === undefined || raw === null || raw === '') return null;\n    if (raw === true || raw === false) {\n      throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n    }\n    const value = Number(raw);\n    if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n      throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n    }\n    return Math.floor(value);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName, fallback) {\n  const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName);\n  if (value === null) return fallback;\n  if (value <= 0) {\n    throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be greater than 0`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args) {\n  const merged = { ...(isRecord(rawConfig) ? rawConfig : {}) };\n  const mappings = [\n    ['stallWatchdogMs', 'stallWatchdogMs'],\n    ['maxCostUnitsPerLineage', 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage'],\n    ['maxTokensPerLineage', 'maxTokensPerLineage'],\n    ['maxTokenBudget', 'maxTokenBudget'],\n    ['maxTokenBudgetPerLineage', 'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage'],\n    ['costUnitsPerIteration', 'costUnitsPerIteration'],\n    ['estimatedTokensPerIteration', 'estimatedTokensPerIteration'],\n  ];\n  for (const [targetKey, argKey] of mappings) {\n    if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(args, argKey)) {\n      merged[targetKey] = args[argKey];\n    }\n  }\n  return merged;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeStopPolicy(raw) {\n  if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n    return 'convergence';\n  }\n  if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n  }\n  if (raw !== 'convergence' && raw !== 'max-iterations') {\n    throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n  }\n  return raw;\n}\n\nfunction jsonOut(payload) {\n  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n}\n\nfunction signalExitCode(signal) {\n  return signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : 143;\n}\n\nlet fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = false;\n\nfunction installFanoutSignalHandlers(onStop) {\n  if (fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled) return;\n  fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = true;\n\n  for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n    process.once(signal, () => {\n      try {\n        onStop(signal);\n      } finally {\n        process.exit(signalExitCode(signal));\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction updateLineageSnapshot(snapshots, event) {\n  if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return;\n  const existing = snapshots.get(event.label) || { label: event.label };\n\n  if (event.event === 'started') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'running', started_at_iso: event.at });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'completed') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: 'fulfilled',\n      completed_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'failed') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: event.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'rejected',\n      completed_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n      error: event.error,\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'retry_scheduled' || event.event === 'orphan_requeued') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'requeued', updated_at_iso: event.at });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'progress') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: 'running',\n      updated_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n  return lineages.map((lineage) => snapshots.get(lineage.label) || { label: lineage.label, status: 'pending' });\n}\n\nfunction summarizeSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n  const results = buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots);\n  const succeeded = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'fulfilled').length;\n  const failed = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'rejected').length;\n  return {\n    results,\n    summary: {\n      total: lineages.length,\n      succeeded,\n      failed,\n      all_failed: lineages.length > 0 && failed === lineages.length,\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath) {\n  return path.join(path.dirname(ledgerPath), OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME);\n}\n\nfunction statusForLedgerEvent(entry) {\n  if (entry && typeof entry.status === 'string' && entry.status.trim() !== '') {\n    return entry.status;\n  }\n  if (!entry || typeof entry.event !== 'string') return 'unknown';\n  if (entry.event === 'started' || entry.event === 'progress' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting') return 'running';\n  if (entry.event === 'completed' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting_complete') return 'completed';\n  if (entry.event === 'failed') return entry.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'stopped') return 'stopped';\n  if (entry.event === 'retry_scheduled' || entry.event === 'orphan_requeued') return 'retrying';\n  // Lag-ceiling signals from the pool: a stall warning while work remains pending, or a\n  // forced abort of the stalled attempt. Map both to typed statuses instead of 'unknown'.\n  if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_exceeded') return entry.action === 'abort' ? 'failed' : 'warning';\n  if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_abort') return 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'stall_detected') return 'warning';\n  if (entry.event === 'budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n  return 'unknown';\n}\n\nfunction appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry) {\n  appendStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry);\n  try {\n    appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath), entry, {\n      producer: 'fanout-run',\n      stream: 'orchestration-status',\n      subject: {\n        run_id: entry.run_id ?? null,\n        label: entry.label ?? null,\n        loop_type: entry.loop_type ?? null,\n        spec_folder: entry.spec_folder ?? null,\n      },","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":320,"totalLines":1747,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1782998776487,"end":1782998776490}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_006743334b9993a8016a4666f8561481918f7a6767a48dcc43"}},"id":"prt_f23023a9b001DXAkePUU6QfT4b","sessionID":"ses_0dd080809ffeSxS04s909esZ2m","messageID":"msg_f2301ffd8001NrRk2YQyRqu0ox"}}
